name: Anna Family Healthcare
bio:
Janet S. Wheat, RN ,MS FNP-C  
Jan has been a Registered Nurse since 1993.  She studied at Texas Woman’s University and received her Master’s of Science in 2006 and her Family Nurse Practitioner Certification in 2007.She previously worked at Baylor University Medical Center Dallas as a Neonatal Intensive Care Nurse, Care Flight Transport Nurse and NICU Educator.  She also served as a Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner (SANE) for the state of Texas.  Over the past 7 years, she has been providing healthcare to her patients in McKinney.  Currently, she is an Adjunct Professor in the Master’s of Science Program at Texas Woman’s University with focus on the Family Nurse Practitioner program, serves on the Serenity High School Board in McKinney ISD and provides health care to the uninsured (ages 0-99) at the Children and Community Health Clinic in McKinney.  Jan has loved caring for her patients and is excited about offering “family healthcare” in Anna and the surrounding area.

name: Annapolis Integrative Medicine
bio:
Dr. Alan Weiss serves as the Medical Director of Annapolis Integrative Medicine. He earned his bachelors degree from the University of Virginia and his medical degree from McGill University. He completed his internship in integrative medicine at the University of Hawaii and his residency in internal medicine at St. Elizabeth’s Hospital of Boston.
He is board certified in internal medicine and is a fellow of the American Academy for Advancement in Medicine and the American College of Physicians.
Dr. Weiss has practiced medicine since 1988. His clinical interests have led him to conduct studies and publish various articles relating to diabetes, chronic pain, fibromyalgia and chronic fatigue syndrome as well as authoring chapters in nutritional medicine textbooks.  Dr. Weiss’ goal is to educate and treat his patient by incorporating the latest research in the areas of conventional and alternative medicine. He continues to pursue and educate himself in leading-edge methods of achieving wellness.
Dr. Weiss is also a senior program leader with Landmark Education and has traveled extensively leading breakthrough transformational programs.

name: Arata Medical
bio:
Dr. Michael A. Arata graduated from the University of California, San Francisco School of Medicine in 1994. He completed residency training at Duke University in 1999. In 2000 he returned to California after a fellowship at the Hospital for the University of Pennsylvania. He works in Newport Beach, CA and specializes in Metabolic and Functional Medicine. Dr. Arata is board certified in Radiology with added qualification in Interventional Radiology. He is also board certified in Venous and Lymphatic Medicine. He founded California's largest outpatient based Interventional Radiology group and spent a decade specializing in limb salvage. While saving countless legs from amputation he yearned for a way to help these patients before their feet hit the end of the road. Functional Medicine allowed him to pursue his dream of preventing the need for invasive, limb salvaging procedures. He is the world’s first Interventional Radiologist certified in Functional Medicine.   
Dr. Arata has an insatiable appetite for learning.  All doctors are required to do a minimal Continuing Medical Education to maintain their medical licenses, but Dr. Arata attends several courses per year, constantly adding to his expertise.  He has taken courses on Anti-Aging, Hormones, and is currently completing a fellowship in Metabolic Medicine.  
As a member of the American Society of Bariatric Physicians (ASBP) and is eligible for board certification by the American Board of Obesity Medicine (ABOM). Dr Arata has joined the fight against obesity and is dedicated to the treatment of obesity and associated conditions.

name: Arax Nazarian DO
bio:
Dr. Nazarian completed her medical education and residency training in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of North Texas Health Science Center in Fort Worth, Texas. She has been in private practice in Lewisville, Texas since 1999.
She is committed to individualized care of women at all stages of life, and feels privileged to be involved in the most personal and private aspects of her patients’ lives.  Her special areas of interest are minimally invasive surgery, preventative care, hormone imbalance, and the over-all well being of her patients.
She is a member of the American College of Osteopathic Obstetricians and Gynecologists, is Board Certified, the American Osteopathic Association, and the Texas Osteopathic Association.
Her awards are: The Patient’s Choice Award, Compassionate Doctor Recognition, Patient’s Choice 5th Anniversary, and in 2008 and  2009 in D Magazine, she was voted by her peers as the top physician that they would send their patients or loved ones to.

name: Aria Integrative Health
bio: Sonia Mookherjea, PA- C is a Physician Assistant who is passionate about uncovering and treating the underlying cause of disease for each individual. She graduated Summa Cum Laude with a Bachelor of Science in Biology and Psychology from the University of Hartford and earned her Masters in Physician Assistant studies from the University of Medicine and Dentistry of NJ in 2012. She has devoted her career to developing expertise in integrative and personalized medicine to optimize health and wellness. Sonia brings to our team clinical experience in integrative psychiatry and neurology, functional medicine and bioidentical hormone replacement therapy. In addition, she has experience in educating clinicians and patients how to interpret genetic testing data and tailor personalized medicine treatment strategies accordingly using evidence based nutraceuticals and pharmaceuticals. She has furthered her training through the American Academy of Anti Aging Medicine (A4M), The Amen Brain Health Courses, and BioTe Medical BHRT Training.

name: ARR Medical Group, PSC
address: Torre San Francisco, Suite 609, 369 Calle De Diego
bio:
Ariel Rosado, M.D., has over 12 years experience internal medicine practitioner, diagnosing and treating adult conditions such and diabetes, hypertension and obesity.  He is a graduate of Guadalajara's Autonomous University and trained for internal medicine at the Ramon Ruiz Arnau University in 2005.    
Dr. Rosado is passionate about helping patients to improve their health, giving the proper treatment for their conditions and balancing their hormones.  He has an extensive experience in weight loss, helping male patients with their testosterone levels and helping patients to achieve improvement in their overall health.

name: Arviv Medical Aesthetics
bio:
Dr. Arviv is a caring, compassionate physician who takes the time necessary to educate and evaluate her patients and discuss their concerns. She provides each one of her patients with a comprehensive customized treatment plan that suits their needs. She has been trained in laser skin resurfacing and brings the latest technology to her practice, combined with the skincare necessary for maintaining a healthy and youthful appearance and enhancing one's natural beauty. 

Dr. Tali Arviv is an Aesthetics and Board-Certified Internal Medicine physician. She graduated with honors in 2006 from the University of South Florida with a Bachelor's in Science. She then pursued a degree in medicine and completed her medical education at Ross University School of Medicine in 2011 followed by her Residency at Orlando Regional Medical Center.


Dr. Arviv's passion for aesthetics stems from her love for art, photography, and theater. In high school, she studied architecture, interior designing and graphic designing exposing her creative side which at first encouraged her to pursue a degree in architecture. However, she realized her connection to people and the community and wanted to be more involved and have more interaction with people. She then decided to take a different path in her education. After taking an EMT course at HCC, she felt compelled to pursue a career in medicine. While attending college, she worked as a surgical assistant doing hair transplants, received additional training to become a Certified Medical Electrologist and was trained in the art of Botox and Dermal Fillers, worked part time at as a laser hair removal technician, obtained additional education in aesthetic medicine, and attended conferences and workshops held by the American Academy of Anti-Aging.

Dr. Arviv is the Vice President of Beauty and Health Institute and provides education and courses in aesthetics for other physicians and nurse practitioners. In addition to her aesthetics practice, Dr. Arviv encourages her patients to make lifestyle changes to improve their health from the inside out. She finds it rewarding that she is able to complement patient care with personalized medical aesthetic services that are safe, effective and meet her patients' needs.

name: Arviv Medical Aesthetics
bio:
Dr. Arviv is a caring, compassionate physician who takes the time necessary to educate and evaluate her patients and discuss their concerns. She provides each one of her patients with a comprehensive customized treatment plan that suits their needs. She has been trained in laser skin resurfacing and brings the latest technology to her practice, combined with the skincare necessary for maintaining a healthy and youthful appearance and enhancing one's natural beauty. 

Dr. Tali Arviv is an Aesthetics and Board-Certified Internal Medicine physician. She graduated with honors in 2006 from the University of South Florida with a Bachelor's in Science. She then pursued a degree in medicine and completed her medical education at Ross University School of Medicine in 2011 followed by her Residency at Orlando Regional Medical Center.


Dr. Arviv's passion for aesthetics stems from her love for art, photography, and theater. In high school, she studied architecture, interior designing and graphic designing exposing her creative side which at first encouraged her to pursue a degree in architecture. However, she realized her connection to people and the community and wanted to be more involved and have more interaction with people. She then decided to take a different path in her education. After taking an EMT course at HCC, she felt compelled to pursue a career in medicine. While attending college, she worked as a surgical assistant doing hair transplants, received additional training to become a Certified Medical Electrologist and was trained in the art of Botox and Dermal Fillers, worked part time at as a laser hair removal technician, obtained additional education in aesthetic medicine, and attended conferences and workshops held by the American Academy of Anti-Aging.

Dr. Arviv is the Vice President of Beauty and Health Institute and provides education and courses in aesthetics for other physicians and nurse practitioners. In addition to her aesthetics practice, Dr. Arviv encourages her patients to make lifestyle changes to improve their health from the inside out. She finds it rewarding that she is able to complement patient care with personalized medical aesthetic services that are safe, effective and meet her patients' needs.

name: Ascend Medicine
bio: Shara Hansen, FNP-C is a Board Certified Nurse Practitioner specializing in Family Medicine. Shara earned her undergraduate degree in Nursing from Bradley University in Peoria, Illinois and her master’s degree as a family nurse practitioner from the University of Colorado.  Shara has been practicing in family medicine for over 15 years.  She has advanced training in Clinical Nutrition, Acupuncture, Medical Aesthetics, Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy, and in Executive Leadership.  Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Pellet Therapy, from BioTE Medical, is a safe and effective way for women and men to regain a happier and healthier lifestyle. Shara joined Altitude in 2010 and has had a major role in influencing Altitude’s direction.  Shara believes in providing quality, patient- centered, holistic care to every patient. Shara is married to her childhood sweetheart and has 2 beautiful daughters.  She enjoys spending time with her family and spending time outdoors hiking, biking, running, swimming, snowshoeing, and snowboarding.

name: Ascend Medicine
bio:
Dr. Doug Hansen, M.D. is the CEO and Medical Director of Altitude Family and Internal Medicine, a multiple location, multispecialty, wellness-based medical clinic in Denver, Colorado.  In addition to being recognized as a Level 3 Patient Centered Medical Home, Altitude Family and Internal Medicine is one of fewer than 500 highly innovative practices nationwide to be recognized by the Department of Health and Human Services in the Comprehensive Primary Care Initiative.
Dr. Hansen earned his medical degree with honors at the University of Illinois College of Medicine and completed his residency training at St. Anthony Hospital in Denver.  Dr. Hansen is the only triple board-certified Primary Care Physician, Clinical Lipidologist, and Nutrition Specialist in the United States.  Dr. Hansen also has advanced training in Acupuncture and Bioidentical Hormone Replacement therapy for men and women.  Dr. Hansen has been practicing in Denver since 1999, and in addition to his clinical practice, serves as Professor of Medicine at the University of Colorado School of Medicine, on the board of directors for Colorado Health Neighborhoods, and on the medical executive board for Fullwell.
Dr. Hansen is a nationally-featured expert on heart disease, hypertension, cholesterol, diabetes, nutrition, and longevity.  He has been featured on NBC’s TodayShow.com and MSNBC and has contributed to many books and publications including Breakthroughs in Natural Healing 2012 and Building Foundations for Change from the bestselling “Wake Up and Live the Life You Love” Series.
For his clinical work, Dr. Hansen is proud to be distinguished as a Patients’ Choice Award winner, an honor bestowed to the top 5% of physicians in the United States as voted by patients, for the past 8 years.
Dr. Hansen is married to his childhood sweetheart and has 2 young daughters.  He enjoys spending time outdoors being active and spending quality time with his family.

name: Ascend Medicine
bio:
Dr. Ashleigh Sartor, MD is a graduate of Swedish Medical Center Family Medicine Residency. Prior to moving to Denver for residency, she received her medical degree from Wayne State University in Detroit, and undergraduate degrees in Chemistry and Biology from Hope College in Michigan.Dr. Sartor enjoys the opportunity that Family Medicine provides for forming therapeutic relationships with a large variety of patients. Dr. Sartor brings a broad scope of care to Ascend Medicine and active in all aspects of medicine including Women’s Health.
Dr. Sartor is currently completing a second board certification in Functional Medicine.  Functional Medicine uses a “whole person” approach to address the underlying causes of disease, engaging both patient and practitioner in a therapeutic partnership.  She embraces healthy living and healthy cooking and brings this expertise to her patients and as the director of the ‘Elite Medical Weight Loss’ program at Altitude Family and Internal Medicine and Ascend Medicine.

name: Ashford Medical Center
bio: Founded Instituto Ginecologico in 1988. Graduate of UCC Medical School PR 1983 and Class Valedictorian. Received specialty training at Jackson Memorial Hospital and graduated OB/GYN University of Miami 1987. Board Certification OB/GYN started 1989. Board Certified Clinical Densitometry. Attending Physician Auxilio Mutuo Hospital, Presby Hospital

name: Ashford Medical Center
bio: Yurizam Ramirez-Ojeda is a doctor in medicine, and is also board certified in the specialty of Obstetrics and Gynecology.  She graduated from San Juan City Hospital in 2011 and became a fellow of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists in 2015.  She is part of the faculty in charge of the residency program in the San Juan City Hospital.

name: Ashland Integrative Medicine
bio:
About Jeannine Parikh, M.D.
It is an honor to introduce myself to you. I grew up in Becket, Massachusetts, a small town in the Berkshires. I have been blessed to have wonderful parents who have given me the support and strength to follow my dreams and taught me strong family values.
Being a doctor is a desire that I’ve had since I was 12 years old. I graduated from St. George’s University School of Medicine in 1997 and completed my medical student rotations in Brooklyn New York and my residency training in at St, Joseph’s Medical Center in Yonkers, NY in 2001. My passion to provide comprehensive healthcare and to use wellness to keep away illness led me to choose family practice as my discipline. I became board-certified in family medicine in 2003.
I met my husband in medical school and have been happily married since 1996. We moved to Ashland, Kentucky with our two boys in 2005. I enjoy the small town atmosphere and strong sense of community this area has to offer. I have had the privilege of working for almost 10 years in the Kings Daughters outreach clinic in South point Ohio.
It has long been a desire of mine to provide a whole body approach, to not just treat illness but to promote overall health, happiness and well-being. Throughout my career I saw the negative effects that obesity has on the body, mind and spirit. I myself have struggled with obesity my entire life. I also saw the toll that addiction has in our community, many times afflicting young people just as they are getting into the prime of their life.
I along with my husband opened our practice, Ashland integrative medicine in 2014 to provide a private, comfortable, family-friendly environment where patients can feel free to address the sensitive issues and help us guide them towards a healthier, more productive life.
It is my honor and a privilege to serve all your healthcare needs.

name: Aspen Institute for Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine
Aspen Thrive Wellness
bio:
Lisa Wagner is a Family Nurse Practitioner (FNP), and the owner and operator of Aspen Thrive Wellness, Hydration, and Aesthetics. Lisa first moved to Aspen in 2003. Seeing a need for primary care providers she left the valley to pursue her education goal of Nurse Practitioner, with the intent of returning to Aspen to help meet the health needs in our community. Lisa receive her BSN at The University of Texas Health Science Center in Houston, and her MSN, specializing in Primary Care Family Practice, at Samuel Merritt University. 
 
She was an active member of the Student Government Organization at UT as the Chair of Philanthropy. Her background in nursing is in the Cardiovascular Intensive Care Unit at the renowned DeBakey Heart and Vascular Center at Houston Methodist in the Texas Medical Center. 
 
Lisa has experience in Bio-identical Hormone Replacement Therapy, IV hydration, Platelet Rich Plasma (PRP) Therapy, and vitamin supplementation to support health and wellbeing. She believes that a proactive approach to health & wellness is imperative to maintaining a healthy life balance.

name: Assure Wellness Group
bio:
A compassionate and patient center clinician who is a graduate of Arizona School of Health Sciences, earning a Master of Science in Medicine in 1997 with follow on certification in primary care and psychiatry by the National Commission on the
 
Association of PAs (NCCPA). As a life long learner, has earned multiple graduate degrees including a Masters of Business Administration and Doctorate in Health Administration. Seeking to further refine clinical knowledge with bio-identical hormones and wellness, completed an American Academy of Anti-Aging fellowship in functional and regenerative medicine with certification by the American Board of Anti-Aging Health Practitioners (ABAHP). He has been practicing bio-identical hormone replacement optimization and pellet therapy since 2008.

name: Assure Wellness Group
bio:
A compassionate and patient center clinician who is a graduate of Arizona School of Health Sciences, earning a Master of Science in Medicine in 1997 with follow on certification in primary care and psychiatry by the National Commission on the
 
Association of PAs (NCCPA). As a life long learner, has earned multiple graduate degrees including a Masters of Business Administration and Doctorate in Health Administration. Seeking to further refine clinical knowledge with bio-identical hormones and wellness, completed an American Academy of Anti-Aging fellowship in functional and regenerative medicine with certification by the American Board of Anti-Aging Health Practitioners (ABAHP). He has been practicing bio-identical hormone replacement optimization and pellet therapy since 2008.

name: Atagi Aesthetics
bio:
As a young girl growing up on a farm in rural Oregon, Dr. Atagi developed an early appreciation for mechanical ingenuity and devices.  It is not surprising that this youthful inclination led her into medical product design, medicine and ultimately plastic surgery. 
An ambitious student, Dr. Atagi earned dual undergraduate degrees in Design and Product Design engineering at Stanford University.  After graduation, she worked as a biomedical engineer designing and prototyping medical devices.  She was awarded a patent for one of her developments.
Her biomedical engineering experience convinced her to pursue her interest in medicine.  She completed a post-baccalaureate curriculum in chemistry and biology at Harvard.  She then returned to Stanford, where she was accepted into medical school and received her doctorate of medicine in 1994.
Realizing that plastic surgery was the perfect way to blend many of her professional interests and talents, Dr. Atagi completed an integrated residency training program in plastic and reconstructive surgery at Barnes-Jewish Hospital in St. Louis.  Advanced training followed, including a plastic surgery research fellowship at Washington University in St. Louis, and aesthetic surgery training at Grossman Plastic Surgery in Denver.
As a female physician in a typically male dominated specialty, many patients find the option of choosing a board certified woman physician for their care more appealing.  Along with performing many cosmetic surgical procedures, Dr. Atagi has a special interest in breast reconstruction surgery for women with breast cancer.
In a survey conducted by 5280 magazine, Dr. Atagi was voted by her peers as one of Denver’s top reconstructive surgeons in 2003, and as both top plastic and reconstructive surgeon in 2004, 2005 2006, 2007, 2008, and 2009.  Dr. Atagi is the author of several articles for professional publications and has conducted research studies on breast implants, breast modeling and related psychological outcomes testing.
Dr. Atagi is a member of the Arapahoe Douglas Elbert Medical Society.  Married to a physician, she and her husband have three daughters.

name: Atagi Aesthetics
bio: Rebecca (Becky) Barkey, PNNP, MSN has been a Nurse Practitioner since 2001.  She received her nursing degree at Bethel College (MN) in 1994 and her graduate degree at Regis University (CO) in 2001. She has spent the majority of her career specializing in Women’s Health and specifically the management of high-risk pregnancies.  She joined Dr. Atagi’s practice in the summer of 2013 to help manage the BioTE hormone pelleting program. Becky and her husband live in Parker, Colorado and have 2 daughters.

name: Atagi Aesthetics
bio: Susan has been a part of the Denver medical community since attaining her degree from Emory University in 1999. Before arriving at Atagi Plastic Surgery and Skin Aesthetics, Susan gained experience in a variety of different fields, including plastic surgery, general surgery, urology, ophthalmology, and dentistry, giving her a diverse outlook on cutting edge medical techniques and methodology. She is a strong believer in personalized and individualized treatments for each patient. Susan joined our team in 2015 and is our full time bio-identical hormone replacement and wellness provider. In her spare time, Susan enjoys hiking, golfing, attending concerts, and international travel.

name: Atlas Medical Center
bio: Heather Darnell recently joined Atlas Medical Center, in Colorado Springs, Colorado, an Integrative Clinic whose focus is on treating patients as a whole and working with the body to enable its natural ability to heal.  She is originally from Florida and received her Bachelor's Degree in Nursing from Florida State University in 1997. Ms. Darnell then received her Master's Degree in Nursing from University of South Alabama in 2002.  As a military spouse, Heather has had the privilege of working throughout the country including Rhode Island, Texas, Alaska, Virginia, Arizona, and now Colorado. She has practiced both as a RN and NP in varied areas of medicine over the past 20 years, and brings a wealth of knowledge to Atlas.

name: Audrain Orthopaedics
bio:
Kathleen Weaver, MD has 25 years of experience in musculoskeletal surgery.  With additional training, she has expanded her clinical practice to include non-invasive aesthetic procedures to help reduce the cosmetic effects of aging, as well as hormone optimization to reduce the physiologic effects of aging.  After medical school at the University of California, Irvine, Dr. Weaver completed orthopaedic residency training in Phoenix, AZ, and has additional fellowship training from Honolulu, Hawaii and Hanover, Germany.  She is Board certified by the American Board of Orthopaedic Surgery and is a Fellow of both the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgery and the American College of Surgery. She is a certified BioTE ® provider for hormone optimization.
OUR SERVICES INCLUDE:
Orthopaedic evaluation and surgery
Microdermabrasion
Intense Pulsed Light (IPL) for hair removal, skin rejuvenation, and acne
Radio frequency fat sculpting and skin tightening
Laser treatment of nail fungus and spider veins
Fractional CO2 laser skin resurfacing
Injectable dermal fillers
Botulinum toxin cosmetic injection
Hormone evaluation and optimization (BioTE ® pellets and techniques)
Call to schedule a consultation:
Central Missouri Aesthetics / Audrain Orthopaedics
626 E Summit St, Suite B
Mexico, MO 65265
(573) 582-0444

name: Aurora Medical Weight Loss
bio: My name is Theresa Rickert. I grew up in Dallas, TX. I have received my Bachelor of Science in Nursing (2008) and Doctorate of Nursing Practice (2017) both at the University of Arkansas in Fayetteville. My degree is Adult/ Geriatric Acute Care Nurse Practitioner. I lived in Arkansas for 9 years through school. I recently moved to Denver, CO in March of 2017. I work part-time at the Aurora Medical Weight Loss/ Hormone Replacement Clinic. I also treat geriatric psych patients in communities throughout Denver. I enjoy hiking, camping, skiing, volleyball, and painting.

name: Austin Med Spa
bio:
Suzette Smith graduated from University of Texas at El Paso in 1995 with a Bachelors degree in Nursing. Suzette started her nursing career in Austin as Hemodialysis nurse and worked as a Charge Nurse in that area for about 8 years.In 2004, Suzette re-focused her education and experience to pursue her passion as a Medical Aesthetic Nurse Specialist and started Austin Med Spa. She was trained by and has worked closely with several top plastic surgeons in Texas and around the country. She is an expert aesthetic nurse injector in Botox, Dysport, Xeomine, Artefill, Sculptra, Beletero, Juvederm, Restylane, and Radiesse. She has extensive experience and advanced training in state-of-the-art lasers and non-surgical cosmetic procedures, such as IPL, laser hair reduction, laser and non laser skin resurfacing, SkinPen, skin
tightening, body contouring and is also well educated in anti-aging products. Suzette attends numerous advanced training courses and seminars annually as she believes on-going education is important to mastering the most up-to-date procedures in advanced skin care and aesthetics. Suzette also helped found and is a member of Texas Association of Aesthetic Nurses.Suzette takes her time with each client, gives them a thorough consultation and believes in educating them on each service so she can help guide them on deciding what treatments are best for them. Suzette has a natural compassion and ability to listen to her patients needs and treats everyone exactly the way she would expect to be treated. Suzette and her husband, Tim, can usually be found on the football, baseball and soccer fields cheering on their three kids.

name: Avance MD
bio:
Neal Carl, MD is an accomplished general practitioner in Richmond, Virginia who has been practicing medicine for the past 17 years. Born and raised in Richmond, Va. he graduated from The Collegiate Schools then accepted an athletic scholarship to the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. After college he worked in his family’s real estate and construction business for several years, but, ultimately decided his true interest and passion included medicine and patient care. Subsequently, he applied to and was accepted to the Medical College of Virginia.
Following medical school Dr. Carl did his internship and residency at Chesterfield Family Practice where he had the opportunity to train with multiple specialists including cardiology, pulmonary, orthopedics, endocrine, and rheumatology. He served as chief medical officer in his assigned hospital during his residency, therefore, was responsible for all after hours medical emergencies.
After residency, Dr. Carl practiced family medicine for several years and with the help of his partner developed a busy and successful clinic. Because of his interest in advanced lipid testing and preventive cardiology he modified his practice by joining forces with cardiology. This multi-specialty clinic offered general family practice and cardiology services and testing including treadmill ECG’s, stress echocardiograms, carotid Doppler, and nuclear heart studies.
More recently, Dr. Carl has been the lead physician at Chippenham Family Medicine and due to his interest in geriatrics served as the chief medical officer at Beaufont Health and Rehabilitation Center, an 120 bed assisted living facility. Dr. Carl also enjoys teaching medical students for the past decade and is an Assistant Clinical Professor at Virginia Commonwealth University.
Dr. Carl recently joined with Dr. Tara Dall who is a renowned lipid specialist and diagnostician. Together, they formed AvanceMD which is a membership based concierge clinic specializing in personalized medicine. By understanding each patient’s individual cardio-metabolic risks, Dr. Carl and Dr. Dall are able to determine and treat the root cause (not just the symptoms ) of a patient’s metabolic imbalances which ultimately lead to disease. Suggestive therapies may include traditional and/or natural treatment options. The clinics primary goal is to prevent and/or reverse accelerated cellular aging and associated chronic disease such as heart disease, diabetes, and dementia via sophisticated assessment and elegant solutions. Dr. Carl is currently working on a fellowship in anti-aging medicine.

name: Ave Medical Laser Clinic
bio:
Paula A. Hicks, M.D. received her training at the Mayo Clinic in Rochester, Minnesota.  She is board certified in Ophthalmology, board certification member of the American Society of Cosmetic Physicians and holds active medical licenses in Iowa, Nebraska and South Dakota.  Dr. Hicks has over 18 years of experience in facial cosmetic surgery including Botox and Fillers.  She has also completed additional training and is certified in laser procedures and liposuction, training with some of the country’s top surgeons.  Ave Medical Laser Spa’s medical team has a cumulative of 25+ years’ experience in the women’s health arena.  Dr. Hicks is a very caring physician who is very excited to bring state of the art skin rejuvenation technology to her patients in a beautiful spa setting

Thank you!

name: Aveda Integrative Medical Center
bio: At Aveda Integrative Medical Center, we believe that true health is not merely the absence of diseases, but rather the presence of optimal physical, mental, and emotional well-being. Dr. Saxena thrive to find the root cause of the medical problem either by state-of-the-art testing or using vast knowledge of treating thousands patients with similar symptoms.

name: Aveda Integrative Medical Center
bio:
Dr. Sushma Bahl, M.D. has over 20 years of medical experience in clinical practice. She is board certified in Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine and is a fellow in Anti Aging, Regenerative and Functional Medicine (AARFM). Her philosophy is to promote optimal health and slow the progression of age related degenerative diseases by balancing body systems. Dr. Bahl's expertise is to integrate traditional medicine and natural therapies. She helps her patients not only manage their symptoms, but also address the root cause of disease. Dr. Bahl is a strong advocate for prevention through lifestyle changes.
In addition to her medical experience, Dr. Bahl is also certified in facial aesthetics, botox, fillers, acne treatment, and laser treatment. Her added expertise in aesthetics helps her patients achieve excellent skin care results.

name: Aviva Woman
bio:
I BELIEVE THAT EVERYONE DESERVES AN INDIVIDUAL APPROACH TO THEIR CARE THAT CATERS TO THEIR UNIQUE NEEDS.  MY GOAL IS TO GIVE YOU THE KNOWLEDGE THAT ALLOWS YOU TO MAKE CHANGES THAT WILL IMPROVE YOUR HEALTH, WELL-BEING AND QUALITY OF LIFE.
Since the age of five, I knew I wanted to be a nurse. I loved caring for my classmates that injured themselves on the playground. In Junior High and High School, I would hide in my grandmother’s spare bedroom and read from her medical textbooks. I enjoyed learning about how the body works and attempting to diagnosis my cousins with the conditions I’d read about. 
In high school, I had the opportunity to take a course to become a certified nursing assistant and this was the start of my nursing journey. I worked in various settings and had the opportunity to care for people of all ages throughout the lifespan.  
My passion has always been women’s health. Just before starting nursing school, I took a course and became certified with the Doulas of North America. I enjoyed being able to work with laboring women and their husbands in their journey to parenthood.  After becoming a registered nurse, I had the opportunity to continue my work in labor and delivery.  The experience of assisting families as they made the transition of adding a new member has left an unforgettable impression upon me.  
I chose to pursue an advanced nursing degree and broadened my scope of practice to include caring for the entire family unit. I had the privilege of attending Frontier Nursing University in Hyden, Kentucky. While there, I learned to embrace a holistic approach in seeking and maintaining wellness.  I believe that everyone deserves an individual approach to their care that caters to their unique needs. My goal is to give you the knowledge that allows you to make changes that will improve your health, well-being and quality of life. 
I have worked in a variety of settings including, medical aesthetics, helping to educate nursing students, bio-identical hormones, and urgent care. These opportunities have allowed me to develop a wide-range of experience in helping to better the lives of those around me. I strive to understand the concerns of those seeking my help and together construct a plan that is attainable. 
I am thankful for an extremely supportive husband who has always encouraged me to purse my passions.  I am the blessed mother of seven children; five daughters and two sons. I enjoy spending time with them and attending their various activities. I enjoy crocheting, sewing, gardening, canning and playing the piano and organ. I also enjoy serving in a special needs activity program once a week and appreciate the opportunity to mingle among and learn from such amazing people!
I believe there is something to learn from every person that we meet.
Certification and Education
•	Salt Lake Community College, AAS, Registered Nurse 2006
•	Frontier Nursing University, MSN, APRN 2013
•	Family Nurse Practitioner, 2013
•	American Nurse Credentialing Center Family Nurse Practitioner Certification
•	BioTE certification, 2017
•	Basic Life Support Healthcare Provider
*       CPR Certified

name: Avondale Wellness
bio:
Dr. Garima Prasad is a partner at Avondale Family Care. She received a Bachelor of Science degree at Houston Baptist University in biology and chemistry. She received a medical degree from University of North Texas Health Science Center in Fort Worth Texas. Her residency
 was completed at UT Houston Health Science Center. She is board certified in family medicine .She is truly excited to be a part of the BioTE  program and to have the tools to help change lives through bio-identical hormone therapy through pellet therapy.

name: Avondale Wellness
bio:
Amanda Rosales is certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners. She obtained her Bachelor’s degree in Nursing from The University of Texas at Austin and completed her Master’s in Nursing degree from Texas Woman’s University in Houston. She is currently working on her Doctor of Nursing Practice degree at Texas Christian University. Amanda has experience in family medicine and women’s health. Amanda enjoys being a Nursing Practitioner because it allows her to build long-term relationships with patients and to be a partner in their journey to a healthier life. 
In her free time Amanda enjoys exercising, camping, reading, Texas Longhorn sports, and spending time with her husband and 3 dogs.

name: AZ Spine Disc and Sport
bio:
Dr. Jonathan Komar received his medical degree at Wayne State University in Detroit, Michigan.  He then completed the Residency Program in Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation (PM&R) at the University of Washington, one of the top programs in the nation for his specialty.  He then went on to successfully complete a Fellowship Program at Southwest Spine & Sports in Scottsdale, Arizona.  This extra level of training has helped him to gain skill and expertise in the area of state-of-the-art, non-surgical care for spine and musculoskeletal conditions.

Specializing in men’s care, he is the “go-to” doctor for the “weekend warriors.” Inundated by the busy work week schedule, men often use the weekends to pursue high impact and physically demanding outdoor sports activities.  However, when injuries occur, this can start a negative domino effect, leading to a decline in function.  This can be the cause of missed opportunities, not only on the golf course and tennis courts, but in home and work life as well.  Dr. Komar’s rehabilitation approach is to treat the whole person, which includes optimizing physical, nutritional and mental health.  Physiologically, men and women are different, and men are prone to some injuries more than women.  Additionally, in the area of men’s health, there is no “one-size fits all” approach to treatment, and this is why personalized care for each patient is an essential part of his approach.

As a Physiatrist, Dr. Komar’s goal is to help improve your level of functioning, reduce pain, and get you back to doing what you love to do.  Over the past 13 years, he has developed and perfected his skills by taking a multi-faceted approach to patient care.  Treating musculoskeletal conditions requires incorporating effective and proven tactics, as well as more modern state-of-the-art medicine in a multi-disciplinary approach.  


Dr. Komar also has great passion for Regenerative Medicine, particularly because he has personally witnessed the success of this kind of treatment on many of his own patients for a variety of musculoskeletal conditions.  Over the past seven years,he has performed hundreds of Platelet Rich Plasma (PRP) injections, long before it became a world-wide trend.  Also, as a Clinical Instructor for the Fellowship Program at Southwest Spine and Sports, he provided hands on instruction to numerous physicians in the training program.   

Dr. Komar’s other areas of expertise include spinal injections of the cervical, thoracic and lumbar regions using x-ray guidance.  He has also performed tens of thousands of peripheral joint injections under ultrasound guidance.  Additionally, he has conducted thousands of exams using Electrodiagnostic Medicine (EMG) throughout his career.  The EMG exam, when performed properly, can guide the clinician to give an accurate and thorough diagnosis, which leads to more effective and appropriate treatment options.  Lastly, Dr. Komar has personally trained and instructed nearly a dozen physicians through each of their year-long intensive training programs, and all of them are successfully utilizing these skills in their own practices and clinics.

Dr. Komar has received numerous awards as a physician.  Patients' Choice honored him with the prestigious Compassionate Doctor Certification, one of a select few physicians, for both 2008 and 2011.  Also, he earned the Phoenix Magazine Top Doc for 2011, 2012 and 2014.  

Giving back to the community, he helped bring PM&R practitioners together by volunteering his time to serve as the Educational Chair for the Arizona Society of PM&R for four years, and then as the President for another two years.  In addition, he previously held the position of Adjunct Clinical Assistant Professor at Midwestern University from 2006 – 2016.  In his free time, he enjoys volunteering for The Boy Scouts of America, which his sons are active members of.

name: Back to Basics
bio: Dr. Patterson has been a Family Doctor, practicing in Sanford, NC since 1981. Hormonal imbalance issues have always been a special interest of his. He started working with bio-identical hormones (BHRT) about 25 years ago and has been considered an area authority on their use. Dr. Patterson graduated from UNC (74), and then the UNC School of medicine (78) and did his residency in Charlotte, NC. He entered a private practice as a board certified family physician in 1981, growing it into one of the largest family medical practices in NC. He left that practice in 1996, wanting to have a smaller, more personal practice, where he could truly focus on his individual patient needs. That is when Back to Basics was born. He has spent time in his BHRT career studying under such greats as Dr. Jonathan Wright, Dr. Eldred Taylor, and the late Dr. John Lee.

name: Back to Health Physicians Group, LTD
bio:
Lyndsay graduated in 2005 with a Bachelor’s degree from Eastern Illinois University. She went on to complete her degree in Nursing from Illinois State in 2008.  She began her nursing career at Sarah Bush Lincoln Health Center in 2009 and started her graduate program in 2013.
In 2016, Lyndsay completed her Master’s degree in Nursing at Indiana Wesleyan University and became a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner.  Lyndsay is certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners. Lyndsay was employed at Sarah Bush Lincoln Health Center as a Weight Management Nurse Practitioner and at Lakeview College of Nursing as an instructor. Lyndsay joined Back to Health in April 2017. Lyndsay holds the title of APN, FNP-BC and is the Director of Nursing at the clinic. 
Lyndsay believes that health care requires a holistic and individualized approach that is focused on treating the underlying cause of the disease. She enjoys educating her patients, giving them the tools and information necessary to be active and informed participants in achieving health and wellness. Lyndsay is passionate about disease prevention, health promotion, and wellness.

name: Balance Health
bio:
Dana Morgan was born and raised in Montana.  She attended undergraduate at the University of Montana graduating with high honors, with a major in Microbiology and a minor in Chemistry.  She attended medical school at the University of Washington in Seattle, Washington.  After graduating from medical school, she chose a Family Medicine residency program in Fort Collins, Colorado.  She has practiced family medicine for the past 18 years.  She has had further training in cosmetic medicine and in 2004 she opened a cosmetic clinic with a colleague.
As a family physician she has struggled with helping women to maintain a balance during the years that their hormones levels are declining.  Since finding BioTE she is excited about the possibility of helping men and women feel better, live healthier and proactively prevent the development of disease.  She continues to practice both family medicine and cosmetic medicine and feels that BioTE compliments both of these areas perfectly.  In her personal life she is raising three amazing children with her husband, Dr. Frank Morgan.  She enjoys sewing, crafting, crocheting, reading and hanging out with her family.

name: Balance Health
bio: Frank Morgan, M.D. graduated from the University of New Mexico school of medicine in 1996. In 1999 he graduated from the North Colorado Family Medicine residency program. He is married to Dana Morgan M.D. and has five children. The formation of Balance Health is the fulfillment of a long-held dream of Dr. Morgan and represents his vision towards providing the highest quality medical service. Dr. Morgan is particularly interested in disease prevention through healthy lifestyles. Outside of medicine, Dr. Morgan enjoys working on his small hobby farm just outside of Greeley. He plays guitar, sings, and enjoys woodworking. Dr. Morgan also loves to study the Bible and has been known to teach Bible studies from time to time.

name: Balanced Wellness Medical Clinic
bio: Jan Nelson is a board certified nurse practitioner with previous experience as a hospitalist caring for many chronic and acute illnesses. Her passion to help her patients  achieve a more healthy productive life led her to become certified in anti-aging medicine through the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine in Boca Raton, Florida. She is now the president and founder of Balanced Wellness Medical Clinic, offering a medical approach focusing on hormonal balance using bio-identical hormone corrective therapies, life style changes and esthetic treatments. “We believe many disabilities associated with normal aging are caused by physiological dysfunction which in many cases are ameliorable to medical treatment, such that the human life span can be increased, and the quality of one’s life improved as one grows chronologically older.” In addition to her passion for optimal wellness, Jan also enjoys camping, river rafting, snowshoeing and generally enjoying the outdoors in the Pacific Northwest where she was born and raised

name: Balanced Wellness Solutions, LLC
bio:
Scott E. Davis, M.D. is the founder of the integrative health center, Balanced Wellness Solutions, in Knoxville, Tennessee. Dr. Davis provides outstanding primary care integrated with individual approaches to getting healthy and staying healthy. His clients learn what they need to know to get back and maintain a healthy lifestyle. His blueprint covers four essential keys to resolving the underlying stressors that lead to the breakdown of health including your endocrine system, detoxification, nutrition and fitness. Hormone imbalances can also contribute to high cholesterol, diabetes, Alzheimer’s, heart disease, osteoporosis and cancer. Offering bio-identical hormone replacement therapy through BioTE is just one more way to help people obtain optimized hormone balance that relieves chronic fatigue, musculoskeletal pain, weight gain, low sex drive, vaginal dryness, hot flashes, mood swings, hair loss, brain fog, dry skin, and erectile dysfunction all while improving your quality of life! At our integrative health center, we explain details about the causes of poor health and what you can do about it. You don’t have to “just live with it” and you’re not “just getting older.”   
 
       Dr. Davis has been a featured speaker at Harvard and sharing the stage with Suzanne Somers while discussing bio-identical hormone replacement therapy as well as receiving standing ovations at West Point after sharing his approach to health and disease reversal. He has future speaking events at Coca-Cola, Microsoft and Nasdaq corporations.  
 
      Outside of taking care of his clients, Dr. Davis’ favorite hobbies are flying small aircraft and raising Suffolk draft horses on his farm in the Tennessee Valley. Dr. Davis graduated medical school from East Tennessee State University in 1992 and he is a veteran of the Tennessee Army National Guard. Dr. Davis loves spending time with his wife, children and grandchildren, and attends church in Oak Ridge, Tennessee.

name: Balcones Woods Family Practice
bio:
Laurelin joined our office in 2002. She has trained closely with Dr. Hausman-Cohen and is detail-oriented and thorough. Laurelin has a special interest in the treatment of chronic health issues such as diabetes, high blood pressure, and elevated cholesterol. She loves seeing the "numbers drop" on lab follow-ups after a patient has made lifestyle changes or when a new medication is working well - her excitement is contagious.

Laurelin graduated from the University of Texas at Austin with her Bachelor of Science in Nursing in 1997. She gained nursing experience in the nephrology/neurology unit at North Austin Medical center and in the pediatric emergency department at Brackenridge Hospital. In 2000 she returned to UT for her Master of Science in Nursing and certification as a Family Nurse Practitioner, receiving awards for academic excellence. She enjoys working with patients of all ages, and especially cherishes the rapport that develops over the years between patients and their providers in family medicine. She loves spending time with her husband and energetic son.

name: Balcones Woods Family Practice
bio:
After working in a large group setting for four years, Dr. Hausman-Cohen opened Balcones Woods Family Medicine in 2001 to practice the "Art of Medicine."

Dr. Sharon Hausman-Cohen obtained both her Master's and Medical Degree from Harvard Medical School. She enjoys staying current in the medical field and spends a tremendous amount of time reading medical literature to keep the office up-to-date. Some of her favorite topics include nutrition, cardiac health, osteoporosis, mental health, and more. She also enjoys office orthopedics and musculoskeletal complaints, and endocrinology - including thyroid issues and stage of life hormonal changes.

Although dedicated to science and evidence-based medicine, Dr. Hausman-Cohen, like all of our providers, has a special emphasis on emotional and personalized needs for patients. She also has a strong interest in alternative and complementary medicine which she shares with the practice as a whole. She is the mother of 3 children in their teens and 20s.

name: Barrick Family Medicine
bio:
Dr. Steven Barrick grew up in rural Iowa and received his bachelor’s degree at Luther College. He earned his medical degree from Kirksville College of Osteopathic Medicine in 1985. After finishing a general medicine internship in Florida, he went on to complete a residency in family medicine at Des Moines General Hospital.

Dr. Barrick cares for patients of all ages with routine and complex medical problems. He is an advocate of preventative medicine, including Bio-identical Hormone Replacement Therapy (BHRT). Dr. Barrick has received extensive training in the BioTE Method of BHRT. The BioTE Method has been proven to be safe and effective in hundreds of thousands of patients over many years. This therapy is designed to address symptoms and health concerns produced by declining hormone levels in both women and men. The BioTE Method helps patients feel much better and reduces many of the concerning symptoms patients feel as the aging process occurs, such as night sweats, hot flashes, low libido, sleep difficulties, low energy, anxiety, depressed mood, join pains, lack of mental focus plus many more. It also provides many long term health benefits that are documented in the medical and scientific literature which can lead to a higher satisfaction in life. A simple blood test will reveal whether you are a candidate for this therapy and if it could work for you. 

Dr. Barrick is one of the few physicians in Colorado that practices a non-surgical injection therapy called Prolotherapy. The very most rewarding part of Dr. Barrick’s medical practice however, is the many wonderful relationships has with his patients.

Dr. Barrick has lived and practiced medicine in Colorado Springs for 27 years. He enjoys golfing, biking, and hiking with his family. His proudest accomplishment is raising five wonderful sons with his wife, Sarah.

name: Basu Center for Aesthetics and Plastic Surgery
bio:
Board certified plastic surgeon, C. Bob Basu, MD, MPH, FACS, is the founder and managing partner of Basu Center for Aesthetics & Plastic Surgery - a thriving plastic surgery practice based in the Houston metropolitan area. As an innovator, Dr. Basu created Houston’s first “virtual group” private practice model which employs technology to improve supply chain management over multiple providers, in multiple locations, including two AAAASF accredited surgical centers - a new paradigm in practice management in plastic surgery. His private practice, currently comprised of 90% cosmetic surgery and 10% breast cancer reconstruction/microsurgery, has achieved performance at the top 1% compared to national benchmarks in plastic surgery as per Allergan Practice Consultants. Given his extensive experience in cosmetic breast surgery, Dr. Basu has established one of the few Allergan Black Diamond private practices in the region. He is also a top ranked plastic surgeon in Houston by Realself.com. He was recognized with the Realself100 award – placing him in the top 2% of cosmetic providers in the nation. 

Dr. Basu is a national leader in his field. He has served on the Board of Directors of the American Society of Plastic Surgeon (ASPS). He has also served as the Chair of the Patient Safety Committee for the society. Given his expertise in patient safety in cosmetic surgery, he also serves on the Board of Directors of The American Association of Accreditation for Ambulatory Surgical Facilities (AAAASF) – the entity that certifies the safety and quality of cosmetic surgery centers. As a recognized expert in practice management, he is also a member of the Board of Directors of Plastic Surgery Practice Solutions - the private subsidiary of the American Society of Plastic Surgeons. Locally, Dr. Basu serves as the Chief of Plastic Surgery and a partner in one of the nation’s most successful 100% physician-owned acute-care hospitals/health systems, North Cypress Medical Center.

name: Be Balanced 365
bio:
Dr. Lopez is a native of San Antonio and attended undergraduate studies at  the University of Texas at San Antonio where she graduated with a BS in biology. She received her Doctor of Medicine from the University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio in 1987 and then moved to Oklahoma city for both her internship and residency in Internal Medicine. Dr Lopez is Board Certified in Internal Medicine.   
Dr. Lopez has been in practice for 25 years. She was initially a PCP with Wellmed Medical Group for 12 years then became a hospitalist. She is currently a hospitalist with Sound Physicians and based at Santa Rosa Westover Hills campus.  In September of 2002, she opened New Beginnings Diet Clinic to follow a desire to practice bariatric and preventive medicine. Dr Lopez had herself gone through life changing lifestyle changes which allowed her to lose 100 lbs!! In August of 2010, the name was changed to Be Well 365 and this has become her passion.. to teach patients better health through better nutrition , lifestyle changes, and more natural modalities.   
Dr Lopez is married, has two daughters and a son, and is very active in the community. She volunteers for Meals on Wheels, is a team doctor for the Crossmen, and a physician for US Figure Skating events. She, herself, took up figure skating while losing weight and medaled at the 2006 Adult Figure Skating National Championships and is now a US figure skating judge. She is on the Board of PFT, INC, a nonprofit, and working on community wellness initiatives.

name: Beaumont Internal Medicine & Geriatrics Associates
bio: Dr. Hammett graduated from the University of Texas Medical, Galveston, Texas and completed his residency at John Peter Smith Family Medicine Program in Fort Worth, Texas. He specializes in Family Medicine and Emergency Medicine as well as Bio-Identical Hormone Replacement Therapy with BioTE Medical.

name: Beaumont Internal Medicine & Geriatrics Associates
bio: Kathleen's specialty is as a Family Nurse Practitioner. She completed her Bachelor's in Nursing at Lamar University in Beaumont, Texas and her Masters at UTMB in Galveston, Texas.

name: Beaumont Internal Medicine & Geriatrics Associates
bio:
Dr. Jeremy Huff
Board Certified in Internal Medicine
Dr. Huff received his Bachelor Degree from Lamar University as Summa Cum Laude. He attended medical school at University of North Texas Health Science Center – Fort Worth, where he graduated 7th out of 150 graduates. He completed his residency in Internal Medicine at University of Texas Health Science Center – Houston, where he was 1 of 4 selected as Chief Resident out of a class of over 100 residents.

name: BeautyLogic at Beau Visage
bio:
Dr. Elizabeth (Beth) Phillips graduated from The University of the South ( otherwise known as Sewanee) with a BS in Biology in 1991.  She earned her MD in 1995 at the University of Alabama School of Medicine in Birmingham, AL.  She served as a General Medical Officer in the United States Navy, including four years of operational medicine on two different ships, as well as an additional year of training in Internal Medicine.  In 2003, Dr. Phillips completed her residency in Emergency Medicine at LSU Baton Rouge, and has been practicing EM in both rural and urban communities, as well as in academic appointments.

Dr. Phillips is Board Certified by the American Board of Emergency Medicine, and is a Fellow of the American College of Emergency Medicine.  She is also a Fellow of the Academy of Wilderness Medicine, and in 2008 she completed her Master’s in Business Administration through Auburn University.

While Emergency Medicine provides a challenging and important part of the healthcare spectrum, Dr. Phillips became interested in also offering medical services that address the preventative aspects of wellness, as well as the confidence-bolstering benefits of aesthetics.  Through advanced training in bio-identical hormone replacement therapy and therapeutic nutrient therapy, Dr. Phillips intends to help her patients manage or even prevent issues related to aging, including cardiac disease, brain function, endocrine disease (i.e. diabetes, thyroid disorders), and weight management.  She believes that the proactive management of these age-related sources of illness and injury, and balancing key hormone regulatory systems, will allow her patients to avoid the need for multiple medications and surgeries.

name: Bedford Family Medicine
bio:
Dr. Cook moved to the HEB area in 1982 after completing medical school and residency in family medicine. He is married and has 4 children. 
Dr. Cook is a FAA Senior Aviation Examiner. He has special training in aviation medicine and performs pilot medical exams. 
Dr. Cook donates his time at the GRACE clinic and was the volunteer of the year for 2012. Dr. Cook enjoys teaching medical students and is an associate professor of Family Medicine at UNT/TCOM in Fort Worth and the University of Texas at Galveston Medical School. 
Dr. Cook is a BioTE certified practitioner. He has specific training in BioTE hormone therapy and can discuss its benefits to your health.

name: Bel Viso of El Paso, LLC
Bel Viso of El Paso, LLC
Bel Viso of El Paso, LLC
Bel Viso of El Paso, LLC
Béla S. Kenessey, MD
bio: Béla S. Kenessey, MD is a Diplomate of the American Board of Family Medicine and a Fellow of the American Academy of Family Physicians.  After graduating from the  University of Southern California School of Medicine in 1989, he attended the USC-PIH  Family Practice Residency Program where he served as Chief Resident from 1991-92. There, he was honored with the Resident Teacher Award by the Society of Teachers of Family Medicine. Dr. Kenessey is a Clinical Associate Professor with the Department of  Family Medicine at Keck School of Medicine of USC. He holds a bachelor’s degree in Economics/Business from the University of California, Los Angeles, and has served on several boards, including at his local hospital, as well as CFO for a community nonprofit organization and CEO and CFO of a sleep diagnostics center. Dr. Kenessey was elected to the Cooperative of American Physicians Board of Directors in 2009 representing over 12,000 California Physicians, and has served as its President and Chair since 2013.  He also served as a Fellow to Board of Directors of the Physicians Insurance Association of America. His family medicine practice is located in Danville, California where he also resides.  His primary focus has been on prevention and wellness and has incorporated multiple modalities including nutrition and supplements, as well as medically supervised weight loss with his Choose2LoseIt™ Ideal Protein clinic, and most recently bio-identical hormone replacement therapy with BioTE™ pellet therapy.

name: Belcara Health
bio:
Kevin L. Carr, MD is a Board Certified Internal Medicine physician who has specialized training and certification in Bio-Identical Hormones and Anti-Aging, Cosmetic and Procedural Medicine, Medical Weight Loss, and Hospital Medicine.
 
After a 4-year tour as a US Marine, Dr. Carr graduated magna cum laude with High Honors from Howard University where he was active in biomolecular research. He completed his medical training at the University of Chicago and Yale University in 2003.
 
He is the former Medical Director of a busy clinic in Baltimore City where he served for 6 years in the National Health Service Corps—providing medical care to the underserved. He has won numerous awards in the practice of Medicine and has a bedside manner that puts patients at ease.
 
As the founder of Carr Medical Specialties, Dr. Carr offers services with the view that clients are whole beings—offering a full range of services including Internal Medicine, Urgent Care, Hormone therapy, cosmetic fillers and Botox, Cosmetic Lasers, Medical Weight Loss, and the HCG diet. Pioneering new medical approaches, many of our clients can be seen in the clinic, at home, or by video with their smart phone or computer.
 
Dr. Carr lives in Lutherville with his wife Elizabeth and their 4 children. He is an active supporter of the Arts and Theater in Baltimore.

name: Belfiore Salon and Spa
bio: Dr. Duchamp is a graduate of the University of North Texas Health Science Center at Fort Worth. He completed a residency in Orthopedic Surgery at Mount Clemens General Hospital in Michigan.  Being an orthopedic surgeon and having treated patients with fractures due to thin bones, he developed an interest in bio-identical hormone therapy as being a solution to help the body increase the strength of its bones.  Studies show that normal bone mass will increase while a person is being treated with bio-identical testosterone and estrogen.  Not only will they help the bones, but the bio-identical hormones protect the heart, brain, and breast.  Dr. Duchamp is excited about helping his patients to have a better and fuller life.

name: Bella Medici Medical Spa
bio: Christine H. Gosch, M.D. is the co-founder and co-medical director of Bella Medici Medical Spa. She is certified by the International Association of Physicians in Aesthetic Medicine in Aesthetics and Medical Weight Loss. She is board certified in Emergency Medicine and has practiced Emergency Medicine for over 20 years including the emergency departments at Cox Branson currently, Mercy Springfield for 16 years and Heartland Hospital for 2 years. She completed her residency in Emergency Medicine at Truman Medical Center in Kansas City, serving as chief resident. She graduated Magna Cum Laude from her medical education at the University of Nebraska Medical Center in Omaha, Nebraska. She is a member of the International Association of Physicians in Aesthetic Medicine as well as American College of Emergency Medicine. Dr. Gosch is married and has three children, all teenagers. She loves to travel, especially visiting the beach. Her hope is to travel more abroad in the future. Other hobbies of hers include shopping, reading and spending time with her family including movies, day trips, float trips, visits to the zoo, etc. It is the desire of Dr. Gosch to make Bella Medici the premier medical spa for the Ozarks region, offering an extensive array of services and expanding as patient needs change. Dr. Gosch will provide a wide array of treatments including Neurotoxin injections for cosmetics and pain control, Dermal Filler Injections, Chemical Peel Treatments, Laser Therapy for Skin Rejuvenation and Treatment, Laser Tattoo Removal, Physician-managed Weight Loss, Skin Tightening and Adipose Reduction. “I want my clients to feel and look the best they can – I want to bring out the best in all of them that I can! It is my inspiration to create a wellness and rejuvenation destination and it is my utmost desire to provide my clients with the best in Aesthetic Medical Care in this geographic region.”

name: Bella Mia Medical
bio:
Linette Rivera, MD is double board-certified in internal medicine as well as endocrinology and metabolism. She offers expert guidance in bioidentical hormone therapy and aesthetic medicine at Bella Mia Medical Aesthetics and Laser Institute in Tampa, Florida. A native Puerto Rican, she speaks fluent Spanish and English and offers all men and women the compassion and time necessary to help them achieve their health and aesthetic goals. She believes the secret to achieving a healthy lifestyle and a better quality of life is restoring hormone balance and preserving beauty and confidence at any age. Dr. Rivera specializes in bioidentical hormones, medical weight loss, testosterone replacement, and thyroid dysfunction.
Dr. Rivera got her undergraduate degree from the University of Puerto Rico, then went on to pursue a degree in medicine at UCC School of Medicine, also in Puerto Rico. She did her residency in internal medicine and her fellowship training in endocrinology at the University of South Florida in Tampa. In addition to her medical expertise, Dr. Rivera has extensive training in alternative medicine, allowing her to design treatment plans that combine the best of both fields. She believes each patient is unique and deserves a comprehensive, customized treatment plan that suits their needs and concerns.
Multiple certifications in neuromodulators, dermal fillers, and laser therapies make Dr. Rivera skilled in treating your stretch marks, scars, and melasma. She’s also experienced in skin resurfacing and anti-aging therapies. She offers products, such as Botox®, Juvéderm®, Radiesse®, and Kybella®, and top-of-the-line skin care products to enhance your natural beauty and help you maintain a youthful, healthy look.

name: Bella Mia Medical
bio:
Pina Panchal, MD is a native Canadian with a strong passion for working with women. Trained in a variety of aesthetic services and skilled in the medical management of weight loss and hormone deficiencies, she offers her services to both men and women of Tampa, Florida, at Bella Mia Medical Aesthetics and Laser Institute. Dr. Panchal believes a woman is at her best when she feels her best. She takes pride in helping her patients feel happy, healthy, and confident.
Dr. Panchal is board-certified in family medicine. She completed her bachelor’s degree in health sciences at the University of Western Ontario in Canada. She went on to study medicine at the University of Sint Eustatius School of Medicine in the Netherlands. Dr. Panchal completed her residency in family medicine at the Medical College of Georgia, then served as Assistant Professor at the Medical College of Georgia. She enjoyed working with medical students and residents in this teaching capacity.

name: Bella Natural Women's Care & Family Wellness
bio:
Dede Chism is the co-founder and Executive Director of Bella Natural Women’s Care.  Her passion for women and their dignity led her to a career in nursing.  She earned her Master’s Degree in Nursing with a specialty as a Perinatal Nurse Practitioner from Regis University in Denver, Colorado.  Dede has worked as a Nurse Practitioner specializing in high risk pregnancies for over 18 years with Obstetrix Medical Group and Swedish Medical Center prior to the conception of Bella. Dede participated in extensive continued medical education offered through the Pope Paul VI Institute.
Dede’s career in Nursing has taken her from critical care obstetrics and transporting pregnant women in helicopters with AirLife to authoring “The High-Risk Pregnancy Sourcebook” in 1997 through Lowell Publishing House, to expert medical consulting and to the high Andes of Peru coordinating medical missions.   An active member of the Christian Life Movement, Dede served on their council from 2009-2012 and participated as a US delegate and presenter for the Christian Life Movement at the International Plenary Assembly in Guayaquil, Equador in 2009 and has been asked to return as a US delegate for  the next Plenary Assembly Arequipa, Peru in 2015.
Dede has a 30 year history in youth ministry and has been able to combine her nursing and youth ministry skills at World Youth Days in Denver, Paris and Toronto as well as serving for over a decade at Steubenville Youth Conferences. Dede was a contributing author on a book on Prayer published through LifeTeen.  Dede and her husband Ken have been married for 36 years and are blessed with 3 grown children, their spouses and 9 grandchildren.  Dede and Ken love wine and chocolate!  They love to travel, spend time in the outdoors hiking, biking, snowshoeing, fishing, reading and enjoying God’s majestic beauty from mountains to seas.

name: Bella Natural Women's Care & Family Wellness
bio:
Abby is the co-founder and Associate Director of Bella Natural Women’s Care.  She graduated from the University of Colorado with her Masters in Science and is a Board Certified Women’s Health Nurse Practitioner. After receiving her undergraduate degree from Regis University, Abby worked as a Labor and Delivery nurse for seven years.  Abby has completed the Nurse Practitioner Medical Consultant training through the Pope Paul IV Institute and is a Creighton Model Practitioner Intern and is committed to excellent obstetric and gynecologic care that promotes the dignity of Women.
Abby’s passion for preserving the dignity of women started long before her career in medicine.  She has been involved in youth and young adult ministry since high school.  Abby served for a year as a missionary with the National Evangelization Teams (NET Ministries) and has spoken at conferences throughout the country to young women affirming their beauty and dignity.  As a teenager, Abby had the opportunity to see the birth of a baby where she “felt as if angels were dancing around the room.”   She was drawn to the way the medical team worked in cooperation with the woman and family.  One of these team members was her mom, Dede.  She knew that one day she would be a part of that team.
Abby and her husband Justin are missionaries at heart and have served with the Christian Life Movement’s medical missions in Ayaviri, Peru.  Not only does her work and ministry life focus on women’s issues, but Abby and her husband have three young daughters Olivia, Madelynn and Mary Belle.  Abby is blessed among women!  Abby enjoys camping, swimming, snowboarding and being surrounded by the ones she loves.

name: Bella Natural Women's Care & Family Wellness
bio:
Leigh Bauer is a board certified Obstetrician and Gynecologist. She attended undergrad at the University of St. Thomas in St. Paul, Minnesota and then went on to medical school at Des Moines University. Dr. Bauer was blessed with the opportunity to do her obstetrics and gynecology rotation with Dr. Hilgers in Omaha, NE which helped her decide that she wanted to specialize as an OB/GYN. Dr. Bauer embraced helping women figure out their menstrual cycles and helping them as they worked through infertility. After a four-year residency in Buffalo, New York, Dr. Bauer accepted a position in a hospital based OB/GYN practice in Northern Minnesota for three years prior to coming to Colorado.
Dr. Bauer was drawn to be a prolife physician as a teenager when her primary care doctor thought it was her obligation to council her about safe sex and being on birth control. It was frustrating for her and her mother when they assured the doctor she was committed to abstinence until marriage and the doctor told them all teenagers are sexually active. Dr. Bauer then met a wonderful family physician who encouraged abstinence until marriage and believed in them and their commitment to wait for marriage. It was so refreshing to have such a great doctor. This physician then invited her shadow her at a prolife clinic and Dr. Bauer witnessed the compassionate care to women from all walks of life that she herself desired as a physician.
Dr. Bauer and her husband, Jordan, are originally from Minnesota. They have three children: Seamus, Virginia and Danika. They are so excited to be living in Colorado and are having so much fun exploring the city of Denver and getting out into the mountains for hiking and exploring. Dr. Bauer is an avid runner and loves to spend as much time as she can in the beautiful Colorado sunshine!

name: Bella Natural Women's Care & Family Wellness
Bella Natural Women's Care & Family Wellness
bio:
Dr. Hodack is the family medicine physician at Bella Natural Women’s Care and Family Wellness. Sarah received her undergraduate degree from Colorado State University (Go Rams!) and she attended medical school at Creighton University. Dr. Hodack worked at a family medicine clinic in Greeley, Colorado for 5 years before joining the Bella team in 2016.
 
She pursued medicine because she finds the human body fascinating and she loves helping others through their medical issues so that they can live life to the full. Dr. Hodack views her job as a physician as a mission to serve every patient with dignity as a beloved child of God.  She is certified in family medicine and loves the wide variety of patients she is able to see all across the lifespan. She especially enjoys caring for obstetric and pediatric patients. 
 
Dr. Hodack has been married to her husband, Troy, for five years. They have three children: Lucy, Finn and Clare. She is originally from Buena Vista, Colorado and loves reading, running, swimming and traveling.

name: Bella Natural Women's Care & Family Wellness
bio:
Sharon is a Colorado native and was raised in Loveland CO with her three sisters. She graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in nursing in 1982 from the University of Northern Colorado. Initially, Sharon worked as a Labor and Delivery Nurse until entering her graduate program through Regis University, she graduated in 1992 as a Perinatal Nurse Practitioner.
 
For 25 years, she worked with high risk obstetrical patients in both the inpatient and outpatient setting. Sharon enjoyed the joys and challenges in managing complicated pregnancies to provide the best outcome possible for every pregnancy.
 
Sharon began working for Bella in Oct 2016. She especially enjoys educating pregnant women in promoting maintenance of healthy lifestyle, not only during pregnancy, but throughout a woman’s lifespan.
 
Sharon and her husband John have been married for 30 years and have three grown children. They enjoy spending time with their children and large extended families, as well as spending time in the great Colorado outdoors hiking, sailing, snow shoeing and traveling to new places. Sharon also enjoys gardening, cooking and reading.

name: Bella Rose MediSpa, LLC
bio: Laika Rodriguez, ND of Salem Wellness Clinic and Bella Rose MediSpa, has a goal to provide a foundation for a healthy lifestyle through ongoing wellness and longevity protocols that include the principles of naturopathic medicine.  She addresses all aspects of adult health with a special interest in hormonal balance, gastrointestinal health, sexual health and enhancing energy and vitality.  Dr. Rodriguez felt becoming a certified BioTE provider was a great fit with her goals and helping patients feeling better and age healthier

name: Bella Vita Med Spa
bio:
Dr. Jeffrey J. Smith graduated from the University of Nebraska School of Medicine, where he also completed his gynecologic/obstetrics residency.
Dr. Smith received his fellowship in Gynecology Oncology at the 
University of California in Los Angeles in 1983 then moved his family to 
Oklahoma and practiced at the University until 1990 when he opened 
his private office.
Dr. Smith currently proctors other physicians on new surgical 
procedures and serves as preceptor for the University of Oklahoma 
Medical Residents.

name: Belladonna Medical Wellness

bio:
Dra. Evelyn Cintrón Pagan, MD, FAARM, ABAARM 
Belladonna Medical Wellness


La Dra. Evelyn Cintrón ejerce medicina desde hace 15 años y es propietaria de las Clínicas: Belladonna Medical Wellness. La mismas tienen como misión ganar la confianza de los pacientes haciéndolos sentir que son parte vital para nosotros. En las clínicas se ofrecen servicios de Medicina Familiar, Bariatría o Medicina de la Obesidad, Terapia Física, Cirugía Menor, Medical Spa con Tratamientos de Estética como Botox, Juvederm, Voluma, Radiesse, Rejuvenecimiento Facial, Anti-Celulíticos y Antienvejecimiento entre otros. 
La doctora Cintrón es diplomada por el Board Americano de Medicina Anti-Envejecimiento y Medicina Regenerativa donde se especializó en Terapia de Remplazo de Hormonas BioIdénticas y ademas posee un Fellowship en Medicina Metabólica y Nutricional.
Ademas participa activamente en la radio, prensa y televisión llevando temas educativos de interés sobre la salud de la mujer.
Hoy dia es Colaboradora de programas de TV como: "Ellas y Tus Noches” TeleOro, "Viva La Tarde” en Wapa America y “Vive Tu Nite” en ABC llevando la voz a mujeres sobre temas de Anti-Envejecimiento, Terapia de Remplazo de Hormonas BioIdenticas, Medicina Nutricional entre otros para empoderarse de su salud. Ademas es fundadora de la Organización “Red Dress Belladonna” para concientizar a las mujeres a proteger sus corazones de las Enfermedades Cardiovasculares.
