name: Life Cycle OB/GYN, LLC
bio: Melissa G. Jones, CNM, is a native of Henderson, Tenn. She received her Master’s of Science in Nursing (Midwifery) from Vanderbilt University in 2003. She enjoys high risk obstetrics and gynecology as well as low risk. Melissa empowers the community through education, sound clinical practice, and an outstanding understanding of family and alternative lifestyles. Hobbies include family, travel, cycling, gardening, and vegetarianism.

name: Life Cycle OB/GYN, LLC
bio: My name is Heidi Pham. I have a Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP) degree in the specialty of Nurse-Midwifery. I graduated from the University of Washington in 2016. I now practice as a Certified Nurse-Midwife at Life Cycle OB-GYN and provide obstetrical and GYN care to women of all ages. As a BioTE-trained provider, I can offer comprehensive hormone replacement support to my clients, improving their quality of life.

name: Life Styles Solutions
bio:
MSN, FNP-BC
 
Linda was born in Central Louisiana.  She has been married for 29 years. She and her husband have been blessed with two children. Their family has resided in Tyler since 1989.
 
Linda is a Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner with more than 30 years of health care experience.  She began her medical career in 1981, after graduating from Northeast Louisiana University with a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing.   She earned a Master of Science degree in Nursing from the University of Texas at Tyler in 1998.  The following year, she completed a Post-Master's Family Nurse Practitioner Certification Program at the University of Texas at Arlington. At UTA, Linda was awarded the “University Scholar for Superior Academic Achievement” award for excellence in both academic and clinical practice.  Since completing board certification as a Family Nurse Practitioner in 1999, Linda, who is also an Adjunct Faculty member for Georgetown University, has practiced in the Tyler area for many years. Her practice has focused on the health care needs of adult patients in both Family Practice and Internal Medicine.  She maintains additional certification in the practice of hormone replacement therapy.
 
Linda’s extensive knowledge base translates into expert care for her patients.  Her motto of “life lived well” is transformational for those patients she serves.

name: Life Time Fitness
bio:
Markeita L. McIntosh-Banya , DD MPAS PA, is a Nebraska native physician assistant with nearly two decades of OB/GYN clinical experience . She earned her doctorate from American Institute of Holistic Theology where her studies with Drs. Andrew Weil and Christine Northrup honed her holistic medicine approach. In addition, she had  intensive  hormone replacement  therapy training with Dr. Neil Rouzier. 

Her commitment to alternative health founded in her own personal challenge with traditional medicine. For six years, she apologized to patients for her cold hands and sat in her office with a heater on blast throughout the year. Many doctors recognized her symptoms as a thyroid condition.  When her thyroid lab tests showed normal range, she was denied  any treatment by several well respected doctors until finding a fellow colleague willing to prescribe bio-identical hormones including thyroid and testosterone.  Life with bio-identical hormones has gone from good  to GREAT!

Dr. Markeita L. McIntosh-Banya is the founder and CEO of Well Woman based in Atlanta, GA.   A sought - after transformational speaker on raising the awareness of your personal health and health related matters, she speaks to audiences around the country. She advocates that health integrates oneness of your spirit, mind and body  utilizing spiritual and scientific principles of healing.  She passionately delivers that message and is dedicated to empowering individuals and organizations to enjoy great health every day.  Patients and audiences alike resonate with her life saving clinical approach to real -time issues that affect their immediate and long term health.

She is the former CEO of Opportunities Unlimited.  Under her stewardship, the company became the first  Georgia Minority Supplier Diversity Council's health and wellness organization. She began Opportunities Unlimited as an independent contractor and later became the Clinical Director for several medical practices and was awarded a $8 million dollar government facility contract.

Over the years, Dr Mac has gained considerable respect and influence with patients and organizations as well as  her colleagues. Answering the nation's call to action with Saving Promise, she unified with her Atlanta community and the country in the national movement to change  intimate partner violence and sexual violence in America.   She tackles not so popular topics including sexual health and sexual well-being as a published medical journalist and medical liaison of the third largest laboratory in the United States, BioReference Laboratory located in New Jersey.  She builds personal health tool kits to grow, restore, and expand a legacy of positive health habits for families and communities.

name: Lifestyle Medicine of Central Oregon
bio: In the Fall of 2012, Mary Huntsman MD opened her new practice where she can follow her love of Integrative Medicine in the setting of Women’s Healthcare.  She is a Board-Certified Gynecologist and obtained her MD and completed her residency at Loma Linda University School of Medicine.   She is also a follower of the Functional Medicine approach, an up and coming new way of assessing and treating many different kinds of conditions by looking for their root cause rather than treating just the symptoms.

name: Lifetime Spine Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation
Light Facial Plastic Surgery & Aesthetic Center
bio:
ABOUT DR. LIGHT
Dr. Ben Light is a skilled, highly regarded facial plastic surgeon who takes the time to develop a relationship with each patient that enters his office.
He is certified by both the American Board of Otolaryngology (Head & Neck Surgery) and the American Board of Facial Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery. Located in Decatur, Alabama, Dr. Light is the only board-certified and fellowship trained facial plastic surgeon between the Birmingham and Nashville areas.
EDUCATION AND TRAINING
After earning his medical degree at the University of Illinois College of Medicine in Chicago, Dr. Light completed a head and neck surgery residency at the University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine. He then returned to his alma mater in Chicago to complete a fellowship in facial plastic and reconstructive surgery with the renowned Dr. Dean Toriumi.
EXPERIENCE
Prior to opening his facial plastic surgery practice, Dr. Light served at the University of Florida as Chief of the Division of Facial Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery and as Director of the University Aesthetic Center.  In his capacities at the University of Florida, he performed hundreds of advanced facial plastic and reconstructive surgeries and also trained other plastic surgeons.  Dr. Light is a published author and has lectured across the country on rhinoplasty and facial rejuvenation.
AFFILIATIONS
Dr. Light completed a rigorous examination process, including peer review, to become double board-certified. In addition to his membership in the American Academy of Otolargyngology and the American Academy of Facial Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery, he is a Fellow of the American College of Surgeons. Dr. Light is also a member of the American Medical Association, the American Board of Otolaryngology, the American Head and Neck Society, and the Medical Association of the State of Alabama.

name: Linden Life Center
bio:
Dr. Ted Trimble was born and raised in Wylie, Texas.  He did his undergraduate study, medical school and Family Practice Residency at Oral Roberts University in Tulsa, Oklahoma. He and his family moved back to Wylie in 1985 after becoming board certified in Family Practice. He joined his father, Terrill M Trimble, MD’s practice and they worked together until 1998.  He then joined the Family Medical Center of Tulsa medical staff and was an attending physician with the In His Image Family Practice Residency out of Hillcrest Medical Center for the next four years. He and his family returned to East Texas in 2002, moving to Pittsburg, Texas to work with East Texas Medical Center. In 2007 he gave up his clinic practice and became a full time hospitalist with the ETMC Pittsburg Critical Access Hospital. March, 2012, he joined the medical staff at the Linden Good Shepherd Medical Center (GSMC) and resumed a full Family Practice with Good Shepherd Medical Associates (GSMA), caring for both clinic and hospitalized patients. 
PhyNet, a non-profit healthcare corporation took over management of the Linden GSMA clinic when GSMA closed the Linden hospital.
Dr. Trimble has enjoyed being a part of PhyNet’s network of primary care clinics that are “committed to providing advanced medical technology in coordinated services, focusing on personal care, patients’ total wellness, with quicker and easier access in underserved neighborhoods.”
He became interested in functional medicine in 2012 after realizing the failure of current medical care: typically a doctor moving from patient to patient writing multiple prescriptions, “a pill for every ill” and “a drug for every bug,” with the goal of seeing as many patients as possible.
In general, medical doctors diagnose and manage disease; where functional medicine seeks to addresses the underlying causes of disease, engaging both patient and practitioner in a therapeutic partnership. Dr. Trimble is working to shift the traditional disease-centered focus of medical practice to a more patient-centered approach. He would like to recapture the essence of being a doctor, which originates from the Latin verb doc?re 'to teach'. 
Training and certification in BioTE has been refreshing for Dr. Trimble’s practice of medicine. He is realizing his desire to practice functional medicine. He now can assist his patients to create health by providing care that restores the necessary components needed by the body to age in health. It is his desire for people to stay healthy and active for the rest of their life.

name: Lindsay McBride DO
bio:
Dr. Lindsay McBride was born and raised in Liberty, Texas. She attended college at Texas A&M University-Corpus Christi where she earned a bachelor of science in biology with a minor in chemistry. She also played collegiate women’s golf for the university. After college, she obtained a Master’s degree in Medical Science from the University of North Texas Health Science Center. For medical school, she attended Texas College of Osteopathic Medicine in Fort Worth, Texas. She completed her OB/GYN internship & residency at John Peter Smith Hospital in Fort Worth, Texas. 

Dr. Stamatis and Dr. McBride were colleagues in residency and have continued on establishing their private practice in Weatherford, Texas. Dr. McBride has been in private practice since 2009. She is an active member of the staff at Weatherford Regional Medical Center. Dr. McBride has special interests in adolescent/teen care, natural hormone management for perimenopause/menopause, incontinence and other gynecologic surgeries (including in office endometrial ablations). Surgical interests include, pelvic floor reconstruction for prolapse and bladder incontinence, operative laparoscopy, and vaginal surgery. Dr. McBride's husband tells others that what sets her apart in her field is her “big heart”. Her patient’s personal time and schedule is important. She placed a high priority on giving individualized, timely, and comprehensive care. 

Dr. McBride was selected by her peers as “Physician of the Year” at Weatherford Regional Medical Center in 2011. She is a member of the Weatherford Rotary Club and the Medical Director for Grace House Ministries/The Option Clinic. She is a member of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, American Medical Association, Texas Medical Association, and Texas Association of Obstetricians and Gynecologists.

Dr. McBride lives in Weatherford with her husband, Michael and 2 children, Taylor and Cash. Her hobbies include golfing, kayaking, reading, and traveling with her family.

name: Lisa Koche, MD
bio:
Originally from Memphis, TN, she graduated with her Masters from University of Tampa.  She went on to complete her doctorate in nursing from Union University.
She is responsible for emergent visits as well as established patients. She is certified in Botox administration, fillers and vampire facials. She performs complete physical examinations including PAP smears and performs the Ultroid procedure which is a non-invasive procedure for hemorrhoid removal. She is available for same day visits if needed.

name: Lisa Koche, MD
bio:
Dr. Koche is triple boarded in Internal med, bariatrics, and alternative medicine.
Ever since her own exposure to the medical field due to childhood leukemia she has been focused on finding the CAUSE of issues instead of treating the symptoms.  She attended Emory Medical School and completed her internal medicine residency at USF in Tampa.  She started her practice focusing on preventing cardiovascular diseases and obesity. That experience led to further training in alternative medicine and nutrition and eventually a comprehensive clinic focusing on all aspects needed for total body healing. She has a team of gifted healers that all work together to create individualized treatment plans and has created a signature program, the Koche Approach, which  is a 12 week comprehensive course to get patients optimally functioning on all levels.
She has lectured nationally, been featured on numerous television segments, and is almost finished with her first book.

name: Lisa M. Jukes MD
bio:
Lisa M. Jukes, M.D., is a Board Certified OB/GYN who opened her South 
Austin practice in 2004, and then moved the practice to its current 
location in Westlake Hills in December of 2008. She graduated from UT 
Southwestern Medical School in Dallas in 1996, completed residency in
2000 and spent the subsequent years at a multi-physician practice in 
North Austin, before embarking on her own.

No longer delivering babies, Dr. Jukes focuses on all gynecological 
services. She specializes in menstrual problems including too heavy or 
frequent bleeding, irregular bleeding, severe cramps, endometriosis, 
ovarian cysts, uterine fibroids, urinary incontinence, pelvic organ 
prolapsed, peri- and post menopause issues, as well as diagnosis of 
infertility. Both non-surgical and surgical treatment options are 
offered by Dr. Jukes. She is a highly trained and well-experienced 
minimally invasive surgeon, who believes in helping patients with 
shorter recovery times.

Dr. Jukes is now a proctor (teacher of other physicians) for daVinci 
Robotic Laparoscopic surgery. She loves helping patients with minimally 
invasive procedures including daVinci Laparoscopic and hysteroscopic 
procedures and has performed over 1000 of these and over 400 daVinci in 
the last 3 years. Dr. Jukes has been named Director, Womens' daVinci 
Program at Westlake Hospital, and is the Gynecological Representative 
for the Robotics Steering Committee at South Austin Medical Center.
Dr. Jukes is also a speaker for Warner-Chilcott regarding hormonal 
contraception. Recently, she appeared on FOX 7 "Good Day Austin"
program to discuss Menopause.
Dr. Jukes wants patients to know the benefits of in-office treatments 
and provides in-office endometrial ablation to treat heavy bleeding and 
cramps, in-office Essure transcervical sterilization to provide 
non-incisional, non-hormonal permanent contraception. Both done in the 
office under local anesthesia with little to no downtime. Her goal is 
to keep you comfortable, improve your quality of life and get back to 
your activities the same day or soon thereafter.

Born in England, growing up in Marble Falls, and residing in Lakeway 
with her husband, Harry, Dr. Jukes is active in the Austin community.
As a mother of two school aged children, she spends much of her time 
with school activities. She understands the concerns of women as they 
juggle their healthcare needs with the needs of their families.

Highly trained, compassionate, and kind, Dr. Jukes is a gynecologist 
who listens well and offers competent, up-to-date treatment options for 
the gynecological needs of her patients. Her enthusiasm for her 
patients and their improved health has resulted in a very successful 
practice. She also offers convenient appointments in Marble Falls and Lakeway locations.
Dr. Jukes looks forward to helping women with their gynecological 
healthcare needs and truly believes "every patient matters."

name: Lisa M. Jukes MD
bio:
Kelli is a board certified Women’s Healthcare Nurse Practitioner who has years of experience in providing care for women. Kelli received her nursing degree from Southern Arkansas University in Magnolia, Arkansas and her Master’s Degree from Emory University in Atlanta, Georgia. In 2005, after receiving her degree from Emory, she joined Natchitoches Women’s Care in Natchitoches, Louisiana, as Women’s Healthcare Nurse Practitioner.  She held this position until 2014.  She joined the practice of Dr. Lisa Jukes in November 2014.  Kelli has extensive experience in the diagnosis and management of complex women’s health issues. 
Kelli is a member of the National Association of Nurse Practitioner’s in Women’s Health, American Society for Colposcopy and Cervical Pathology, and Texas Nurse Practitioners. 
Kelli grew up in Magnolia, Arkansas.  Kelli is married to husband Danny and they have a precious daughter, Stella.  Kelli enjoys gardening, cooking, running, scuba diving and spending time with her family.

name: Lisa Wasemiller-Smith, MD
bio: My patients are like family to me. When one is hurting, I hurt too. I believe that being a good physician means you practice medicine from the heart. When you’re not at your office seeing patients you are thinking about ways to improve your skills so you can care for them in the best way possible.

name: Lisandra Pagan, MD
bio:
Dr. Pagan was born and raised in Puerto Rico, where she received her medical degree. She then moved to New York and completed her Obstetrics and Gynecology training at Richmond University Medical Center. During residency, she served as administrative chief resident and was awarded for Excellence in Female Pelvic Medicine and Reconstructive Surgery. 
Dr. Pagan believes there is no other specialty as rewarding as OBGYN. “Not only does it allow me to take care of women’s health issues, to guide them during pregnancy and to help them transition through menopause; but it also give me the opportunity to educate them and become a figure of trust in their lives”

Dr. Pagan major interests are Menopause, Infertility, Pelvic Pain, and Minimally Invasive Surgery.

name: Littleton Gynecology and Wellness
bio:
Jeannie Key is a Board Certified Nurse Practitioner specializing in Women's Health Care. She has advanced training in Colposcopy, Cervical Pathology and Female Sexual Dysfunction. She has also completed advanced training and certification in Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy. BHRT pellet therapy, from BioTE Medical, is a safe and effective way for women and men to regain a happier and healthier lifestyle. Jeannie has dedicated her life to Women's Health Care starting out as an obstetrical nurse in labor and delivery and ultimately moving into a supervisor role before pursuing her certification as a Nurse Practitioner.  Jeannie joined Littleton OB/Gyn in 1996 and has had many roles in influencing where we are at today.      
 
As a Colorado native, Jeannie grew up in Craig, married her high school sweetheart and moved to Denver.  She is the mother of three grown children and is the number one fan of her two beautiful granddaughters and grandson.  Jeannie has a passion for culinary wonders... we all enjoy the fruits of her labor!!

name: Littleton Gynecology and Wellness
bio:
Dr. Watson spent most of his youth in Arkansas, and earned his undergraduate degree in Zoology from the University of Arkansas. He then attended medical school at the University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences. Dr. Watson graduated in 1988, having received the Elvin Shuffield Award in Excellence. In 1992 he completed his internship and residency at St. Joseph Hospital in Denver, Colorado.  His private practice career started in this very office with his first partner Dr. David Ricca until Dr. Ricca's untimely death in 1996. Dr. Bruce Dorr then joined him in 1997. That spirit of partnership continues to thrive today, not only between Dr. Watson and the office staff, but with his patients as well. Many patients actively share in their care as a result. Dr. Watson certified in performing robotic surgery with the DaVinci method.

Dr. Watson was married in 1988 and now has two boys, JJ and Jake. His family is the most important aspect of his life and he considers his office staff as part of that family (for which we are all grateful!) That spirit is exemplified in the interactions between the staff and the patients. He thoroughly enjoys all that Colorado has to offer. Dr. Watson is an avid bicyclist and skier and he has formally logged over one million vertical feet of heli-skiing!  Welcome!

Personal message from Dr. Watson…
I have been an OB/GYN for over twenty-five years and have promoted healthy lifestyles with diet and exercise as part of my practice. My mantra has always been “It’s not what you could do, it’s not what you can do, but what you will do when you are 90.”  However, I found that something was missing, that eating well and activity were not enough. We have struggled with traditional forms of hormone treatments and doing what we were told, but this wasn’t working either. It was through a series of these frustrations that I happened upon BioTE Medical. I am excited to be finally able to offer something to my patients (and their husbands!) that can bring back that spark in life. I have promoted “bioidenticals” for a long time, but the delivery mechanisms and often the products were substandard.  I feel we now have both issues addressed so we can achieve that Right Balance.

name: Littleton Gynecology and Wellness
bio:
Dr. Bruce Dorr is a native of Detroit, Michigan, but has lived in Colorado for over 25 years. He majored is Chemistry and Biology, minored in German and Psychology at Hope College in Holland, Michigan. He trained in OB/Gyn at the University of Colorado Health Science Center from 1990 to 1994. He then became a locum tenens physician – performing temporary physician work around the country – primarily in underserved areas of Arizona, Oregon, Washington, Virginia, New York and Michigan. He then joined the faculty of Denver Heath. Serving as an assistant professor, he ran the urogynecology clinic and studied under Dr. Peter Sand and G. Willy Davila to further strengthen his incontinence and bladder disorder training. 
     Dr. Dorr has been board certified in OB/Gyn since 1996 and recently became board sub-specialized in Female Pelvic Medicine and Reconstructive Surgery..  Dr. Dorr is a member of AAGL and is minimally invasive trained for laparoscopy and robotic surgery. He performs advanced procedures such as DaVinci sacrocolpopexy single incision hysterectomy.  
You will find that Dr. Dorr has many passions--whether or not it’s guiding you through your first pregnancy or through menopause or contemplating complex surgery or hormone replacement therapy.
     Dr. Dorr joined Dr. Watson in 1997 to use his teaching skills in the private practice setting. With their longstanding relationship, the office is a second family--some of the employees have been there 20 years or longer.  Most patients feel this warmth and closeness the minute you walk through the door.  He recently became chairman of the Department of Ob/Gyn at Littleton Hospital to make a difference in the administrative realm as well.
     Our latest passion and offshoot of our practice is Right Balance Health Center, LLC.  It is about optimizing health and wellness for women and men.  In addition to nutritional and supplement counseling, we offer bio-identical hormone replacement of BioTE estrogen and testosterone--making a difference in how you feel at any stage of your life.  
     Dr. Dorr has been married since 1994 and has two children, Nicole and Alex. He loves to travel, run marathons,  ski, do triathlons and Crossfit. Spending quality time with his family, whether that’s his wife and kids or you, his patient , is what life is all about.

name: Littleton Gynecology and Wellness
bio:
Kate is a Nurse Practitioner working in Women’s Health since 1996. She obtained a Bachelor’s degree in Biology before deciding nursing was her calling. She then went on to receive a Bachelor’s degree in Nursing through Regis University and worked as an RN on Labor and Delivery and postpartum. In 2005, Kate graduated from the University of Colorado Health Sciences with a Master’s of Science- Women’s Health Nurse Practitioner. Kate is passionate about partnering with patients to achieve wellness and to feel their best from adolescence through menopause.  She received her certification as a BioTE provider in 2015 and is pleased to personally witness the incredible results this method of hormone optimization has given her patients.
Kate is a Colorado native with a son and daughter who keep her busy! In her free time she enjoys skiing and mountain biking.

name: Live Well at Warner Family Practice
bio:
Merle Turner was born in Wisconsin but raised in Southwest Kansas. A true Kansas native, he attended elementary school, middle school and high school all in Kansas. When he graduated from high school in 1966 he attended undergraduate college in Anderson, Indiana at Anderson University, graduating in 1970. He continued his education at Kansas City University of Medicine and Biosciences and graduated in 1975 with his medical degree in Osteopathic Medicine.
Merle decided at a young age to become a doctor – though it was through tragic circumstances. While in the second grade, he discovered a young mother next door, who lived in his same neighborhood, had taken her own life. The thought entered his mind, “If I had known what to do I could have saved her.” Through this neighborhood tragedy, Merle Turner was determined to one day become Dr. Turner so that he could help people through the various stages of mental and physical health.
For Dr. Turner, patient care takes many forms, however, he is particularly passionate about the practice of preventative care. Though his passion for preventative care is all-encompassing, he sums it up with the simple philosophy of, “Preventing a problem is better than trying to cure a problem.”

name: Live Well at Warner Family Practice
bio:
Dr. McConnell was born in Phoenix, Arizona but has also lived in many places in Arizona, Texas, New Mexico, Utah and Washington, the last two as an adult. Although it may seem like she was a city girl, Dr. McConnell grew up on a farm. In fact, her medical experience began on her family’s farm with the medical care of her animals.
“I passed out cold the first time I saw my Dad give our cat vaccinations.”
This experience allowed Dr. McConnell to realize that she wanted to help people. It was as a teenager that she got interested in science and worked as a veterinary technician. The fascination of science, nature and the human body and how perfectly orchestrated it all is was the reason she chose the medical field.
Practicing medicine has many rewards as Dr. McConnell will tell you.
“Making the patient feel better when they are certain they won’t. Giving back a quality life so they can follow their bliss, which is the purpose of our lives.”
Dr. McConnell, just like the rest of the Warner Family Practice staff, knows the importance of preventative care. When you put an emphasis on preventative care, it offers a longer, higher quality life and empowers a person to pursue what matters in their life.
For Dr. McConnell, practicing medicine is more than her job, it’s about improving and fostering human connections. Deeper human connections teach us about life, love and ourselves.
“My goal is honest, genuine connections with people everyday.”
When you build these relationships with the patient, you are able to speak truthfully about all your past health choices, no matter what they are. Dr. McConnell will tell all her patients, “that was you then, you are not that person now.” The past is a lesson to learn and improve on. It’s knowledge just like anything else. Focusing on the future and not your past is when you move forward.
Outside the office, making time for herself is Dr. McConnell’s top priority. That one aspect is different from day-to-day.

name: Live Well at Warner Family Practice
bio:
Paul Borgesen, Jr. is originally from South Dakota but was raised primarily in the greater Phoenix area. Growing up, Paul would spend time with his father, a physician, making rounds at the hospital. It was during this time that he first displayed an interest in working in medicine. In 1999, Paul went on to earn his Bachelor of Medical Science from Midwestern University.
As a child and even into adulthood, Paul’s parents stressed and impressed upon him the need to be helpful to other people. Both of his parents were in healthcare and, to Paul, entering the same field seemed to be the best way to serve others. In 2004, Paul followed in the footsteps of his parents and earned his Master of Science from the University of Nebraska College of Medicine.
“Medicine has been so rewarding because I’ve been able to see patients utilize health screenings and preventative medicine to improve their overall health and well-being.”
Because he realizes the benefits of treating patients with a preventative medicine mind set, Paul looks for the most medically appropriate and patient-centric preventative methods to help them prevent potential conditions or delay conditions which may be inevitable. Ultimately it’s about helping patients be at their best, day in and day out.
“Success is seeing patients feel better physically. Success is witnessing the changes they make in their lifestyles to improve their health.”
When patients visit with Paul, he knows each one comes from a unique health background, having made a variety of good or bad health choices. No matter the consequences of those choices, he sees “now” as the best possible time to start making new life decisions for the benefit of the patient’s health.
Paul lives in Gilbert with his wife, Beth. Together they enjoy exercising, listening to music and traveling. They also enjoy attending their local church together.
When Paul has free time, he often enjoys it fishing lakeside or shooting sporting clays (target shooting) outdoors.
What Paul Wants You to Know About Him
“I like to share my own experiences with my patients in the arenas of disease screening, prevention and health improvement. I’m a human being, just like everyone else.”

name: Live Well at Warner Family Practice
bio:
Stephanie was born in Eugene, Oregon but grew up in Gilbert, Arizona, graduating from Gilbert High School. Growing up, she was involved in many after school activities, including gymnastics, theater, speech and the debate club. This love of activities has been passed on to her children, who also are involved in sports and theater arts.
After graduating from high school, Stephanie attended Arizona State University. At first, she declared her major as Psychology, but it was not soon after that she decided to change it to the medical field. The opportunity for lifelong learning where she could make a difference in other people’s lives was too difficult for her to pass up and she has not looked back.
“The most rewarding part of practicing medicine is the ability to help others.”
Stephanie, just like the rest of Warner Family Practice, knows the value of placing an emphasis on preventative care. She wants to give the patient the power to control their outcomes to positively impact their health.
It’s this journey that brings joy to Stephanie. Everybody comes with different situations, some good and some bad. Bad choices may have been made in the past; when you focus on what you can do now, you can overcome these struggles and move forward.
“When I see a patient in a follow-up and they are feeling better, their labs are better or they overcome their obstacle in their journey to health, that’s what I define as success.”
Outside of the office, Stephanie enjoys spending time with her family and friends. Her main focus is raising her children, always putting the effort towards making sure they have opportunities with sports and theater arts.
What Stephanie Wants You to Know About Her
“I truly care for my patients. I like to work with my patients as a team, involving them in their health care.”

name: Live Well at Warner Family Practice
bio:
Neil Sheth grew up in the suburbs of Chicago and when he was in high school moved to San Diego. There he continued his education enrolling at the University of San Diego and in 1998 earned his Bachelor of Science in Biology with emphasis on Cellular and Molecular Biology.
Early on in elementary school, Neil realized he wanted to work in the health industry. As a child, he often spent time in the hospital for respiratory difficulties as well as sports injuries. After graduating from San Diego State University, he was accepted into the Ross University School of Medicine and in 2004 earned his Medical Degree fulfilling his childhood desire to become a health practitioner.
“The most rewarding part of practicing medicine is knowing that I am helping to improve outcomes of not only individual patients, but across entire families.”
When it comes to caring for patients, Dr. Sheth places great emphasis on preventative care. He sees the active practice of preventative care as a way to diagnose problems early and make necessary changes. These changes help his patients prevent diseases such as diabetes, heart disease and strokes.
“I approach every patient with an open mind and will do my best to help improve their health. As one of my patients has said, ‘there is no shame or secrets in your exam room.’”
Dr. Sheth is multilingual speaking Gujarati and Spanish. His favorite pastimes are sports (basketball and football), enjoying outdoor life, hiking and golfing.
Prior to having children, Dr. Sheth and his wife traveled the world together. Since having children, he places high priority on simply spending time with family.

name: Living Well Dallas
bio:
Dr. Cory Rice, a native Texan, graduated from Baylor University in Waco with a bachelor’s degree in forensic science and completed medical school at Arizona College of Osteopathic Medicine in Glendale, Arizona. He attended Methodist Medical Center of Dallas for his internship and residency in internal medicine. He was chosen as Chief Resident of his internal medicine residency program. 
Dr. Rice’s professional interests include nutrition based chronic disease management. He’s  passionate about giving his patients options, not just prescription medicines! Dr. Rice is extremely knowledgeable in the areas of chronic disease, such as diabetes, obesity, high blood pressure/cholesterol, hormone imbalance, etc. His main focus is on wellness and prevention.
Dr. Rice’s free time is spent with his family and friends, watching all sports (Go Baylor!).

name: Living Well Dallas
bio:
Margaret “ Miggy “ Scott PA-C is a certified Physician Assistant with a passion for helping people achieve optimum health through  body, mind and spirit  with integrative medicine.  She has a B.S. in Microbiology from the University of Texas at Arlington and received her Physician Assistant training at UT Southwestern Medical Center.  She has a Fellowship in Integrative Medicine from the University of Arizona Center for Integrative Medicine.  She is pursuing advanced studies in Botanical Medicine with one of her mentors, Tieraona Low Dog MD . Miggy lives with her husband, Steve, 2 dogs and 2 cats. They have a grown son. Miggy enjoys yoga, the out of doors, weight training and reading. She is also a volunteer with SearchOne Rescue Team.
Organizations: American Academy of Physician Assistants, Texas Academy of Physician Assistants, Wilderness Medical Society

name: Living Well Dallas
bio:
Dr. Carol Villanueva completed her bachelor’s of arts in psychology from Boston College, followed by a year of volunteer social service in Portland, Oregon, helping people with HIV and AIDS. She then attended medical school at Nova Southeastern University, obtaining a Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine and a master’s degree in Public Health. After graduation she did her internship and residency in internal medicine at Methodist Medical Center of Dallas.

The practice and services at Medical Family Circle have evolved and changed in great part with credit to its patients, who have pushed her to explore more and research other potential options and treatment plans.   

Outside of medicine, nutrition and wellness, Dr. Villanueva enjoys spending time with her family, playing soccer, and traveling.

name: Living Well Medical Center
bio: Living Well Medical Center has offered quality healthcare to the Kanawha Valley and surrounding areas since 2001. Dr. W. Jarrod Chapman is trained and certified to perform a variety of medical and aesthetic services. In 2009 and 2011, he was voted Charleston Newspaper’s “Best Doctor of the Kanawha Valley.” Our fully trained clinical and administrative staff is committed to providing the highest quality service to our patients. Living Well Medical Center provides an on-site, full service laboratory, bone densitometry, joint injections and minor dermatological procedures.

name: Lloyd James, MD
bio:
Dr. Lloyd James attended medical school at Ross University School of Medicine and graduated in 2001 having 14 years experience.  Dr. James specializes in Family Medicine with an emphasis on hormone optimization in women and men.

SPECIAL EXPERTISE
-Diabetes
-Diabetes Complications
-Hormone Therapy

name: Lone Star Bioidentical Hormone
bio:
Robert G. Stroud, D.O., F.A.C.O.S., is a third generation Texan, born in Austin and raised in Fort Worth. He has been providing cutting edge urologic care with Texas pride to patients since 1993.

With his Texas pride and local roots, it was a natural decision for Dr. Stroud to stay and practice in his hometown. Dr. Stroud truly understands the importance of community and family and has incorporated that spirit into his practice approach.

Board Certified in Urologic Surgery, Dr. Stroud provides his patients the finest urologic care by managing both the medical condition and any surgical interventions that may be called for. By offering fully comprehensive care, Dr. Stroud's patients are most often able to have all their urological care under one roof.

Additionally, Dr. Stroud's comprehensive hometown urologic care has been recognized by the Tarrant County medical community voting him as "Top Doc" 2012 in Urology in Fort Worth, Texas - The City's magazine.

Dr. Stroud's hospital and surgery center affiliations include: Baylor Surgical Hospital, Grapevine Surgicare, Baylor All Saints, Plaza Medical Center and Baylor Medical Center.

Dr. Stroud is proud to serve on the Baylor Quality Alliance, contributing to the clinical integration, quality improvement and cost reductions for the patients and communities served by Baylor Health Care System.

name: Lone Star Bioidentical Hormone PLLC
bio:
Robert G. Stroud, D.O., F.A.C.O.S., is a third generation Texan, born in Austin and raised in Fort Worth. He has been providing cutting edge urologic care with Texas pride to patients since 1993.

With his Texas pride and local roots, it was a natural decision for Dr. Stroud to stay and practice in his hometown. Dr. Stroud truly understands the importance of community and family and has incorporated that spirit into his practice approach.

Dr. Stroud is proud to serve on the Baylor Quality Alliance, contributing to the clinical integration, quality improvement and cost reductions for the patients and communities served by Baylor Health Care System.

name: Lone Star Surgery
bio:
Dr. Robert Lenington
Board Certified Surgeon
Who is Dr. Robert Lenington?
Since beginning his medical career, Dr. Robert Lenington has toiled relentlessly to bring quality care to every patient attending his practice. Raised in the Dallas area, Dr. Lenington decided to attend Texas Tech University. Excelling as a student during his undergraduate studies, Dr. Lenington earned his bachelor's of science degree in the field of Biochemistry. Once that was completed, he made the decision to continue on the path toward a career as a medical doctor.
Earning his medical degree while studying at Houston’s University of Texas Health Science Center, Dr. Lenington completed his formal education before moving on to his residency. His first stop was serving his surgical internship with the staff of the University of Tulsa at Oklahoma. In an effort to expand his professional experience and understanding, Dr. Lenington applied and was accepted to complete his residency program at Florida’s Orlando Regional Medical Center. While there, Dr. Lenington continued to excel, being selected as the chief resident of the surgery department.

name: Lone Star Surgery
bio:
Dr. Robert Lenington
Board Certified Surgeon
Who is Dr. Robert Lenington?
Since beginning his medical career, Dr. Robert Lenington has toiled relentlessly to bring quality care to every patient attending his practice. Raised in the Dallas area, Dr. Lenington decided to attend Texas Tech University. Excelling as a student during his undergraduate studies, Dr. Lenington earned his bachelor's of science degree in the field of Biochemistry. name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio:
Dr. Linares has been in practice in the Denver area since 2000. She completed medical school at Howard University College of Medicine in Washington, D.C. followed by a family medicine residency program affiliated with Mount Sinai Medical School in New York City. She is Board Certified in Family Medicine and has completed the AAFP course in Advanced Life Support in Obstetrics and Advanced Cardiac Life Support. She is currently serving her second term as Chief of Family Medicine at Sky Ridge Medical Center. Dr. Linares enjoys obstetrics as part of her professional interests. Most of her patients receive their obstetrical care as well as their other medical care at Lone Tree Family Practice.  

Dr. Linares is married with three beautiful girls. She enjoys hiking in the mountains, skiing, tennis and a good glass of red wine.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio:
Michelle graduated from the Physician Assistant Program at Marquette University in 2007 after completing her undergraduate degree in Biomedical Sciences. Upon graduation, she moved to Colorado and has gained valuable experience working as a Primary Care Provider in the Denver area and loves all that this beautiful state has to offer. She thoroughly enjoys the medical specialty of Family Practice and its concern for the total health of the individual as well as the family. She loves getting to know her patients and their family and watching them grow through the years.

As a Midlevel Provider she sees patients for acute care, physicals, as well as chronic disease management. Within this area, Michelle has developed specific interests in health maintenance by helping patients form an interest in their own health through the use of preventative screenings and encouragement of a vigorous, healthy and well-balanced lifestyle and nutrition. Her professional interests include pediatrics, women’s health, and sports medicine, and she is able to see all ages we see here at Lone Tree Family Practice.

Outside of work you may see Michelle out running, on her bike, or an area hiking trail. She also enjoys participating in Triathlons and has a fond enjoyment of travel.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio:
Lynn received her Master of Science in Nursing/Family Nurse Practitioner degree at the University of Colorado Health Sciences Center in 2007. Three years earlier, she completed her Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree from the University of Iowa. She gained valuable experience as a Medical/Surgical nurse in the hospital setting during graduate school and loved living in Colorado so much, she stayed to pursue her NP career.

She worked for 6 years in an outpatient endocrinology clinic where she gained valuable experience and became an expert in managing a variety of diabetic and thyroid patients. She worked extensively on weight management and counseled patients on healthier lifestyles with diet and exercise. She has advanced experience using Armour and Cytomel in addition to Synthroid for thyroid hormone replacement.

She is board certified by the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC) and is excited to be back in family practice. In this setting, she still specializes in thyroid diseases and diabetes, but also manages a variety of medical conditions for all ages. She has experience in diagnosing and treating acute and chronic conditions across the lifespan, as well as performing physical exams. She likes to focus on preventive medicine and education to help patients live their best lives.

In her free time, she loves traveling with her fiance and spending time with her dog. She also likes skiing, exercising, reading, and socializing with friends and family.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio:
Dr. Cedars practiced in Denver for thirty years prior to opening Lone Tree Family Practice with Dr. Linares in 2003. He graduated from University of Texas Southwestern Medical School in Dallas and completed two years of surgical residency prior to going into family medicine. He enjoys surgical procedures including vasectomies, skin lesion removals, biopsies and orthopedic procedures.
 
Dr. Cedars has also been board certified in family medicine. He is a pas president of the Clear Creek Valley Medical Society. Currently he is a Delegate of the Colorado Medical Society and a member of the AMA and AAFP. He is on the Board of Directors of the Colorado Academy of Family Physicians and represents the CAFP on the multi-group committee on Patient Centered Medical Home. In addition to seeing patients, his duties include management of the office.
 
He is married, has five grown children and seven grandchildren. His hobbies include flying, scuba diving and traveling with his family.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio:
A native of Colorado, Monica moved to northern Wisconsin where she earned her undergraduate degree from the University of Wisconsin education system in Eau Claire, WI.  In 2006, Monica moved to Iowa City to earn her Master’s Degree in Physician Assistant Studies from the University of Iowa and has been practicing as a Certified Physician Assistant in Colorado since August 2008.
Since beginning her practice, Monica dedicated her first 5 years of practice to serving the under and un-insured population of the Denver Metro area with Metro Community Provider Network (MCPN).  In early 2009, while still with MCPN, Monica partnered with Dr. Jose Castillo-Mancilla, MD of the University of Colorado to staff the MCPN HIV clinic and has since developed a deep interest and dedication for caring for those living with HIV and AIDS as well as addressing the primary prevention of HIV.  She then joined Lone Tree Family Practice in late 2013 to expand her practice and experience, be closer to home, and free up some of her time to spend with family and friends.
Monica’s professional skills and interests include the management and prevention of HIV/AIDS (including HAART and PrEP prescription); and she is skilled and trained in performing basic office procedures including the placement of IUDs and general dermatologic procedures.  She has also been through specialized hormone evaluation and replacement training for both males and females.  Her professional interests and priorities include preventive and proactive health care, nutrition, diet and exercise counseling, and educating patients on how to best care for themselves to live a more healthy and well-balanced and active lifestyle.
An avid runner, weekend yogi, suburban gardener, budding snowboarder and evening “chef” – she lives locally in Highlands Ranch with her husband, Bryan and small dog, Mocha.  She considers Colorado her true and forever home and in her spare time can be found enjoying the beauty of nature, reading a good book, sipping a cup of coffee or enjoying the occasional glass of wine or local craft microbrew beer.

name: Lone Tree Family Practice
bio:
Tammy has been a Certified Adult Nurse Practitioner since 1998.  For 15 years, she worked in Endocrinology developing her expertise in diabetes care, thyroid disease and management and hormone replacement therapy.  From the first elevated blood sugar to intensive insulin pump therapy, Tammy partners with her patients to achieve the best control they can.  Well versed in multiple thyroid preparations, including Armour Thryoid and T3 products, she works closely with the patients to find safe and optimal levels to help patients feel their best.   She believes health care is a partnership between the provider and the patient facilitated by information, education and empowerment.
She received her Bachelor’s of Science in Nursing from the University of Texas and her Masters of Science in Nursing for Adult Primary Care from the University of Colorado Health Science Center.  Tammy has worked in health care since 1986 in the areas of critical care, geriatrics and general medicine.
Tammy, a native Texan, is married and has raised her two sons here in Colorado.  She enjoys traveling, reading about traveling, and talking about her travels.  She loves to paint and read and has been known to enjoy a nice glass of wine on occasion.

name: Lone Tree OBGYN
bio:
Mary has provided health care services to women for the last 20 years first as a women’s health nurse and now as a certified nurse midwife (CNM). She is passionate about helping women through all phases of their life and wants to ensure that her patients age gracefully. She became very interested in hormone replacement therapy (HRT) as a way for her to have additional tools to deliver excellent care to her patients.

Through this pursuit, Mary is also skilled in assisting men with hormone issues that when addressed correctly can affect their physical and mental health as well as their longevity: Mary has consistently pursued higher education as a means to deliver better care to her patients. She is constantly striving to improve the care for her patients.

name: Lone Tree OBGYN
bio:
Barbara Slocum is a board certified Women's Health Nurse Practitioner and a full scope Certified Nurse Midwife. While growing up in a military family and living in many different locations, she considers Colorado home.
She graduated from Air Academy High School in Colorado Springs and went on to attend Saint Mary's College in Notre Dame, Indiana, where she received a Bachelor of Science in Biology (with a minor in German). Barbara then completed the Accelerated Nursing Program at the Catholic University of America in Washington D.C. earning a Bachelor of Science in Nursing.
Following graduation, she received a position at the prestigious Washington Hospital Center New Graduate Fellowship Program in high-risk labor and delivery. Upon completion of the fellowship program, she returned to Colorado.
Barbara continued her work in high-risk OB care at various hospitals in Colorado. In 2012, she began work on her Masters of Science in Nursing at Georgetown University. This unique and difficult program provided an expanded focus on care for women and newborns that enabled her to sit for both the Women's Health Nurse Practitioner boards and the Certified Nurse Midwife board examinations. Barbara completed the clinical hours required for her Masters at Lone Tree OB/GYN & Midwives and began working with the practice in 2014. She delivers at Skyridge Medical Center and Castle Rock Adventist Hospital.
Additionally, Barbara VanDersarl Slocum is a published author! She was asked to write a chapter for the book, Pharmacology for Women’s Health while in graduate school. Lone Tree OBGYN is thrilled to announce this book was recognized by the American Journal of Nursing as a Book of the Year and it received the top award in the Maternal-Child category. This is a notable accomplishment in nursing circles. Barbara is hopeful the information in the book will benefit more providers and make a difference for women around the world.
Barbara and her husband John have three children. They enjoy spending time outdoors, running as well as playing and watching sports. Her ultimate goal of OB care is to provide compassionate, quality care that results in a healthy mom and a healthy baby.

name: Lone Tree OBGYN
bio:
Wayne C. Furr, MD of Lone Tree OB/GYN & Midwives, is a board-certified obstetrician and gynecologist who's been practicing for over 30 years. He attended Loma Linda University School of Medicine and did his residency at White Memorial Medical Center in Los Angeles.
The multicultural nature of his residency experience has proven beneficial over the years of his practice, and his learning of Spanish has assisted him in mission trips to clinics in South and Central America. Dr. Furr served in active reserve U.S. Air Force from 1980-1982, Edwards AFB, California, and was honorably discharged in 1982 as Major.

name: Longevity Health & Wellness
bio:
Board Certification – American Academy of Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine
Board Certification – American Board of Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation with a sub-specialty in Pain Medicine
Fellowship – Baylor University Medical Center, TX
Fellowship – St. Anthony Hospital, OK
Residency – Carolina’s Medical Center, NC
Internship - Walter Reed Army Medical Center, DC
Medical School - Medical College of Virginia, VA

Darryl D. Robinson, M.D. was born and raised in Richmond, Virginia. He obtained his undergraduate degree from Howard University in Washington, D.C. where he graduated Phi Beta Kappa, Magnum Cum Laude in 1991. He then went on to the Medical College of Virginia, Richmond, Virginia where he was awarded both the Alumni and Health Professional Scholarships, graduating in 1995.

In 1995 Dr. Robinson was commissioned as a Captain into the United States Army and completed an Internship at Walter Reed Army Medical Center in 1996. From 1996 through 1998 he worked as a General Medical Officer at Winn Army Community Hospital, Fort Stewart, Georgia. He resigned his active duty commission in 1998 and continued in the individual ready reserves through 2004.

Dr. Robinson completed a Residency in Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation at Carolinas Medical Center, Charlotte, North Carolina in 2001. From 2001 through 2002 he completed a sub-specialty Fellowship in Pain Medicine via Baylor University – Saint Anthony North Ambulatory Surgery Center, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma.

Dr. Robinson became a member of Oklahoma Sports Science and Orthopedics in 2002 and is Board Certified by the American Board of Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation with a sub-specialty in Pain Medicine.

After more than a decade of providing comprehensive, state of the art treatment for pain syndromes, Dr Robinson in 2012 was acknowledged by Castle Connolly as one of the region’s top physicians. One thing that has become apparent is that pain programs that rely primarily on conventional pharmaceutical medications are limited. For this reason Dr. Robinson began to search for treatment alternatives that would expand his comprehensive approach and improve clinical outcomes. This approach focuses on optimizing the body’s natural functional and restorative capacity via the tenants of nutrition, hormone optimization, and wellness.

In pursuit of the most heavily researched and vetted approaches, he became a Certified Fellow and Board Certified by the American Academy of Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine. These concepts have served as his inspiration as medical director of Longevity Health, Beauty, and Wellness. In 2012 Dr. Robinson was also selected into the inaugural class of “Pink Tie Guys” by the Susan G. Komen affiliate in Central and Western Oklahoma to serve as an ambassador for women’s health in the fight against breast cancer.

name: Longevity Health & Wellness
bio: Grant Roberts, Physician Assistant, has been working with Dr. Robinson since 2003. Under the supervision of Dr. Robinson, Grant treats patients in the clinic and is available to see patients Monday-Friday 8:00 to 5:00. Grant graduated from the University of Oklahoma Physician Associate Program in 2001. He is a member of the National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants (NCCPA). Grant is also a member of the Oklahoma Academy of Physicians Assistants (OAPA).

name: Longevity Health & Wellness
bio: Michelle Wray is a graduate of East Central University where she received her Bachelors of Science degree in Physics. She completed her masters of Health Science at the University of Oklahoma college of medicine and is a certified Physician Associate by the National Commission on certification of Physician Associates. Prior to receiving her Physician Associates degree, she worked in a laboratory performing DNA analysis for prostate cancer as well as fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) analysis to detect chromosomal abnormalities associated with bladder cancer. Her professional memberships includes the Oklahoma Academy of Physician Assistants as well as the American Academy of Physician Assistants. Her interests as a Physician Associate include; diet, exercise and overall health and wellness.

name: Longevity Health & Wellness
bio:
Amber Stachmus, PA-C
My belief is that keeping a positive attitude is the key to Longevity. I am a Board Certified and Oklahoma State licensed physician assistant who specializes in medical aesthetics with a focus on state-of-the-art laser procedures, fillers and injectables. I have a proven background in aesthetics, and a passion for minimally invasive techniques for clients wanting a non-surgical approach to self-improvement. In my free time I like to spend time with my kids, and animals.
Master’s of Health Science, University of Oklahoma, College of Medicine.
Bachelor’s of Biologic Sciences, Oklahoma State University.
Memberships include: The National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants (NCCPA); The Oklahoma Academy of Physicians Assistants (OAPA); American Academy of Physician Assistants (AAPA).

name: Los Alamitos Family Health and Wellness
Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Lafayette
Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Lafayette
bio: Dr. Ben Palombo is a native of Lafayette, LA in the heart of Cajun Country. He has a Bachelor of Science from Louisiana State University, and a Masters of Science as well as a Medical Degree from the American University of the Caribbean School of Medicine. After graduation, he obtained his post-graduate residency training in Family Medicine at LSU Health Sciences Center in Shreveport, LA, where he was also first introduced to Aesthetic Medicine. He relocated to Pineville, LA, where he established Premier Care Family Medicine as well as Faces Medical Spa and Wellness. One year into practice, he began to experience extreme fatigue, foggy thinking, decreased libido, and weight gain. His investigation into his own symptoms led him to discover the power and importance of proper hormone levels. He has continued to educate himself on this subject and now uses this knowledge to help his patients receive symptom relief. His journey has now led him a more effective treatment for hormone therapy: bio-identical hormone pellets.

name: Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Lafayette
Louisiana Hormone Replacement Specialists of Pineville
bio: Dr. Ben Palombo is a native of Lafayette, LA in the heart of Cajun Country. He has a Bachelor of Science from Louisiana State University, and a Masters of Science as well as a Medical Degree from the American University of the Caribbean School of Medicine. After graduation, he obtained his post-graduate residency training in Family Medicine at LSU Health Sciences Center in Shreveport, LA, where he was also first introduced to Aesthetic Medicine. He relocated to Pineville, LA, where he established Premier Care Family Medicine as well as Faces Medical Spa and Wellness.
