*Employed as a registered nurse for 20+ years prior to obtaining NP degree. I had mainly worked in specialty areas i.e. newborn ICU, operating room, 
recovery room, emergency room.
 
My thesis was on exploring hormonal changes during menopause. 
“Sexual Dysfunction and Management Issues in the Aging Woman.” 
I have been interested in hormones and their function in the body for many years. I feel this is an area lacking in the medical field. I feel the medical community at large know very little about the thyroid gland and the brain. These two amazing organs are so complex and drive many or all of the functions in the human body. The information given me in NP school about the thyroid gland and how to manage it was so elementary.  I have since taken the initiative to study and learn all I can about the thyroid and sex hormones so I can help my patients have a higher quality of life. I have seen bio-identical hormones make a huge difference in how my patients feel and embrace life. Improving the quality of life in my patients is so enriching to me. Improving the quality of my own life with bio-identical hormone has been such a positive journey.
Preventative health makes so much more sense than fixing what’s broken. 
I know the path I have chosen is where I need to be. I know bio-identical hormone

name: Medical Wellness Center
bio: Edwin James Dean, M.D. is Board Certified in Emergency Medicine.  He is currently the Medical Director of the Medical Wellness Center located in Naples, FL.  He is a graduate of Cornell University and Cornell Medical School and completed his residency in Emergency Medicine at LA County/USC Medical Center.  Dr. Dean has over 30 years of experience in medicine including emergency medicine in Los Angeles, Miami and the Florida Keys. He directed a busy urgent care and traveler’s clinic for 15 years before pursuing his passion in preventative medicine and healthy aging.   In addition to Bio Identical Hormone optimization, his special interests include medically assisted rapid weight loss, early detection and reduction of common health risks and nutritional assessment and optimization.  Dr. Dean refers to this as Preventative Emergency Medicine.  He likens this treatment form to helping prevent the CRASH rather than trying to put the broken pieces back together after the WRECK.  Healthy aging is simple; however, it is a personal decision.  If you are interested in improving your overall health and your life, Dr. Dean is here to help.  It is amazing and rewarding to see how much better people feel and function, on all levels, when their hormones are optimized and balanced.  It puts life into their years.  You only have one life to live – you owe it to yourself to live it well.

name: Meliora Integrative Medicine
bio: Dr. Chua  is a board-certified neurologist with a special interest in Integrative Medicine. She completed her neurological training at Northwestern University and a fellowship in Integrative Medicine at the University of Arizona, under the supervision of Dr. Andrew Weil. Her focus is on taking care of the whole person, rather than treating a specific symptom, through nutrition, mind-body approaches, and balancing the neurohormonal, immune and digestive systems.  She guides patients in discovering the body’s innate capacity to seek wellness, look for balance, and heal itself, and works as a partner in identifying treatment options that reflect a patient’s unique needs and life circumstances

name: Melisa Weaver, APRN-CNP, PLLC
bio:
Melisa received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing from the University of Oklahoma in 1999. Following graduation from OU until 2002 she was attending the University of Tulsa in the Legal Nurse Consulting program and an emergency room staff and charge nurse at St. John Medical Center. From 2002 to 2005 Melisa, was working to obtain her Masters Degree in Nursing with a specialty in family practice at the Medical College of Georgia. Simultaneously she was working as an ER nurse at a Level I Trauma Center.
In 2005, Melisa moved back to Oklahoma and joined an Internal Medicine Practice with Tulsa Health Group. She started a Coumadin clinic, continuity practice, acute care practice and began work as a Hospitalist for SouthCrest Medical Center. In 2006, she joined New Beginnings Medical Weight Loss. There she started and administered a medical managed weight loss practice while also providing primary care for bariatric patients. Melisa joined the WeightWise Bariatric Program in March of 2013.

name: Melisa Weaver, APRN-CNP, PLLC
bio:
Marquis was raised in Oklahoma. Destined to go to the University of Oklahoma, she graduated there with a bachelor’s of arts in psychology in 2007. She continued her education with the University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center with a bachelor’s of science in nursing in 2008 and a masters in nursing in 2012. While working on her master’s degree she worked at Oklahoma Heart Hospital as a registered nurse in the progressive coronary care unit.
Since graduation from her master’s program she has been working in the primary and urgent care setting providing quality care to patients across the lifespan. Marquis joins WeightWise Bariatric Program in June of 2016. She is very excited to be a part of the WeightWise team and looks forward to being directly involved in patient care as they continue their remarkable journey towards a healthier lifestyle.
In her spare time Marquis enjoys spending time with her family and friends, playing tennis, and spending time with her two dogs.

name: Men's Health & Wellness
bio:
Betty Bowers, MD, received her medical degree from the University of Minnesota. After medical school, she did 39 months of general surgery residency at Hennepin County medical center in Minneapolis and then did 24 months of anesthesia residency at Mayo Clinic in Rochester Minnesota. She is board-certified in anesthesia.   In addition to managing patients in the intensive care unit, she has also taken care of patients in her pain management clinic and in her preoperative clinic. This experience has made her realize that many of the very seriously ill people that she cared for would not have been in that situation if they had made different choices in their lives.
Over 20 years ago during a lecture at an anesthesia meeting she was introduced to the concept of preventive aging. The speaker presented peer-reviewed studies that demonstrated slowing of the aging process and even some reversal by doing certain things. Since that time she has practiced his recommendations and continued to follow the literature and change her behavior accordingly. 
During these last 20+ years, this information has become more mainstream and people are out there searching for the secret to living longer and living better. In spite of this, the general health of the population has become significantly worse and for the first time in recorded history the next generation may live for a shorter period of time than the previous generation. 
About 2 1/2 years ago she was given the opportunity to start practicing a form of medicine to help people understand their individual risk factors for disease and guide them through a plan to prevent these diseases from affecting their future.
Recently she has opened a new office focusing on men’s health, and of course, bio-identical hormone replacement therapy.

name: Mendez Family Care
bio: Cassie Greer has been a nurse since 2002 where she worked in many different specialties including long term care with traumatic brain injuries, pediatric hematology and oncology at Arkansas Children's Hospital, bone marrow transplant at the Mayo Clinic, as well as inpatient and outpatient Surgical Oncology as a Masters Prepared Nurse Practitioner from the University of Cincinnati in 2010. She has enjoyed hormone replacement in all its forms, physical medicine, oncology research, and family medicine. Certifications include women's health and biote certified practitioner for performing pellet implant procedures. She has a love for preventative medicine, learning, and overall wellbeing while in practice. Cassie loves spending time with her family at the beach, hiking, riding bikes, or just working in the yard.

name: Menopause and Hormone Specialty Center
bio: Tammi Herkey is a Board-Certified Women’s Health Nurse Practitioner practicing in Shreveport, Louisiana at the Menopause and Hormone Specialty Center, LLC.  Originally from Knox, Pennsylvania, Ms. Herkey received her Bachelor’s Degree in Nursing from Daemen College in 1996 and her Masters of Science Degree from State University of New York in 1998.  While living in Buffalo, she met her husband and moved to Shreveport so he could pursue his career in law enforcement.  In addition to running her successful practice, she is the proud mother of a fourteen-year-old daughter and twin six-year-old boys.  She has always been very passionate about women’s health and helping to restore their hormones to optimal levels.  Ms. Herkey has 10 years ‘ experience in hormone replacement therapy including utilization of pellets and finds great reward in being able to improve the quality of life in her patients.  Becoming a certified BioTE provider was affirmation of her years of experience and research in hormone optimization, and she is excited to incorporate the BioTE medical method into her practice.

name: Mercy Clinic Kingfisher
bio: Medicine is not just a job for me, but a passion. Not only is my goal to treat illness and injury, I want to focus on wellness and disease prevention so that my patients have the best life possible. I know my patients are busy and may have a lot going on in their personal lives, but I want them to always remember how I made them feel. I want them to see me as a friend who just so happens to provide them with medical advice.

name: Meria Aulds MD
bio: Dr. Aulds graduated from UT Southwestern Medical School, Dallas, Texas in 1987. She spent four years on active duty with the United States Air Force as an Internal Medicine Physician and is board certified in Internal Medicine. She now lives Wise County and practices in Decatur, Texas. Dr. Aulds has very specific treatment goals for her patients, the most important being that they feel healthy and are as healthy as they can possibly be. She accomplishes this high health standard by providing for her patients BioTE® Hormone Pellet Therapy for both men and women. The goal is to lower peoples cardiovascular risk factors. She also evaluates and treats diabetes, fatty liver, and all forms of the Metabolic syndrome. I believe that for people with a high risk of cardiovascular events, such as stroke, heart disease, aortic aneurysms, peripheral vascular disease, if they can identify and make adjustments in their own personal bio markers, then they can lower their own personal risk of cardiovascular events, says Dr. Aulds.

name: Metro Health and Wellness, LLC
address: 2950 Stone Hogan Connector, Building 3, Suite B
bio:
Dr. Kirstie Cunningham (@iamdrkirstie) and her team at Metro Health and Wellness, LLC serve patients who live in and around the Atlanta, Georgia area. The doctor offers a full line of services that pertain to women's health and wellness, including hormone imbalance, abnormal bleeding, weight loss, PMS, PCOS and prenatal care.  Dr. Kirstie also offers individualized treatment plans to both women and men for hormone therapy, weight loss and teen gynecology.  Dr. Kirstie treats patients of all ages and welcomes new patients on a regular basis. She has over 22 years of experience in her chosen field of practice.
An Atlanta native, Dr. Kirstie graduated from Duke University and attended medical school at Wake Forest University School of Medicine. After receiving her medical degree, she completed her internship at Aurora Sinai Samaritan Medical Center. She performed her residency at Mercy Hospital and Medical Center.  Dr. Kirstie is a Board-Certified physician specializing in both Obstetrics and Gynecology.  Dr. Kirstie is also Assistant Professor at Morehouse School of Medicine where she serves as Director of Maternal Child Health. The doctor frequently attends classes and seminars to stay abreast of the latest technological advancements in her field.
The most rewarding part of her practice is her ability to stay true to her values of spending quality time with her patients. Outside of the office, Dr. Kirstie enjoys biking and singing jazz and gospel, and she is committed to giving back to her community. Dr. Kirstie resides in Atlanta, GA with her husband of 25 years, and 2 children.   Follow Dr. Kirstie on Instagram, Facebook and Twitter @iamdrkirstie

name: Metroplex Women's Care
bio:
After receiving her undergraduate and medical degree from the University of Kansas in 1992, Dr. Potter completed her residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at The University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio in 1996.
 
Dr. Potter has lived in Rockwall and practiced in this area for over 16 years.
 
Dr. Potter, along with Dr. Gillean, established Metroplex Women's Care to move her office to the heart of Rockwall's medical community.
 
Board certified in obstetrics and gynecology, Dr. Potter is a Fellow of The American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. Dr. Potter is married to Trey, a natural chef and green energy innovator, and has two boys, Stuart and Samuel both attending Rockwall RISD Schools.

name: Metroplex Women's Care
bio:
Dr. Gillean is a native Texan, growing up in San Antonio, TX. She received her undergraduate degree from The University of Texas in Austin in 1990.
 
She graduated from The University of Texas Southwestern Medical School in Dallas in 1998 with her Medical Degree. She completed her residency training in Phoenix Arizona in 2002.
 
Dr Gillean has lived in Rockwall and practiced in the area for over 10 years. She is Board Certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology, and is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.
 
She and her husband, Michael,a local businessman, have a combined four children attending Rockwall schools.

name: Metroplex Women's Care
bio:
Amy Hantes, NP received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Baylor University in 1996.  She began her nursing career at Presbyterian Hospital of Dallas, where she developed an interest in women’s health.
 
In 2001, she completed her Master of Science and Nurse Practitioner degree from Texas Woman’s University. Amy has been practicing in the Rockwall area since 2001.
 
Amy is a member of the North Texas Nurse Practitioners Association, Society of Urologic Nurses and Associates, and the National Association of Nurse Practitioners in Women’s Health. Amy, an avid dog lover, has 2 shih tzus, Bentley and Sophie and volunteers with the local shih tzu rescue.
 
Amy is active with the youth in her church and enjoys running, traveling, snow skiing, and spending time with family and friends.

name: Metroplex Women's Care
bio:
Dr. Slabas is originally from Hawaii and she received her undergraduate degree from The University of Michigan in 2003.  In 2005, she received her Masters degree from Loyola University in Chicago.  
She attended Medical School in Chicago at the University of Illinois where she received her Medical Degree in 2010.  From there she completed her residency training in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania in 2014.  
Dr. Slabas is a Board Eligible, Junior Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.  She is certified in Davinci Robotic Surgery and provides Obstetrical services as well.  
Dr. Slabas and her husband, Jeff, live in Rockwall with their puppy, Scooter.

name: Miami Anti Aging Institute
bio:
Dr. Zayed’s interest in Regenerative Medicine began when his 80-year-old father, also a physician and professor of medicine, began to experience declining health. In his search for answers, Dr. Zayed began consulting with a fellow physician and expert in the field of anti-aging. This introduced Dr. Zayed to anti-aging supplements, which produced an immediate and dramatic improvement in his father’s health.  He realized that there is a lot to be done to help patients from a preventative and functional approach, rather than the conventional approach geared towards symptomatic treatment as opposed to preventing disease. As a result of this experience, Dr. Zayed began to absorb everything he could find about anti-aging medicine. Now, years later, Dr. Zayed's Regenerative Medicine has become a leading Miami anti-aging medical clinic.
Dr. Zayed was born in Alexandria Egypt where he earned a British High School Diploma from an international school. He received his medical degree from the Alexandria Faculty of Medicine. From there he moved to the United States where he received his double Board Certification in Anesthesiology and Echocardiography. Dr. Zayed practiced Anesthesiology for several years before dedicating to Regenerative Medicine.
The Zayed Regenerative Medicine approach involves:
•	Compassionate, personalized, integrative and preventative care
•	Cutting-edge, evidence-based medical knowledge and technology
•	Supplements to reinforce and/or replace lost nutrients and hormones
•	Legal performance enhancing supplements for athletes who require the replacement of essential nutrients and hormones lost during intense training
Dr. Zayed was also the Chairman of The Young Philanthropists of Baptist Health. He believes that everyone should give back to their communities. Dr. Zayed also holds a position as a voluntary Assistant Professor at the Florida International University Medical School where he shares his experience and expertise with young future physicians.
*This is not accredited by the American Board of Medical Specialties. Mr. Zayed's Regenerative Medicine approach involves a compassionate, personalized, integrative and preventative care; cutting edge, evidence-based medical knowledge and technology; supplements to reinforce and/or replace lost nutrients and hormones. 
Dr. Hatem Zayed’s credentials include:
•	Masters in Functional Medicine, USF Tampa Medical School 2017
•	Board Certified, American Academy of Anti-aging and Regenerative Medicine
•	Advanced Fellow of the American Academy of Anti-aging and Regenerative Medicine
•	Anesthesiology: Residency completed in 2003 at the NYU Medical Center
•	Anesthesiology: Board Certification 2004
•	Echocardiography: National Board of Echocardiography 2005

name: Miami Center of Excellence for Obstetrics & Gynecology
bio:
Dr. Fink is Medical Director and Managing Partner of the Miami Center of Excellence for Obstetrics & Gynecology.
Creating an environment where the very best of medicine and gentle gynecology is practiced and where patients come first has always been his goal, and the Center of Excellence has been his dream since arriving in Miami in 2001. Dr. Fink completed his Obstetrics & Gynecology training at Brown University/Women & Infants’ Hospital of Rhode Island, and medical school at the Medical College of Virginia. He attended graduate school at the University of Pennsylvania, and received his undergraduate degree from The American University, in Washington, DC.
________________________________________
Prior to entering medicine, Dr. Fink was a professional actor. He has numerous credits from the big screen, from the soaps and prime time television, in commercials, and on stage. In medicine, he has channeled those interests by consulting for news agencies on both the local and national levels. He has also produced medical television, and is a frequent on-camera medical consultant. A quick Google search will show you that Dr. Fink is often sought out by media because of his unique ability to make even complicated subjects easy to understand.
His clinical interests include women’s wellness & sexuality, sexually transmitted infections, contraception, hormone management, minimally invasive treatments for heavy menstrual bleeding, and general obstetrics. He is fortunate to work with his beautiful wife Stephanie, and has two wonderful sons at home, Max & JB. He enjoys photography, and is an avid private pilot.
Dr. Fink is a recipient of the Deans’ Award for Teaching Excellence from Brown University, is Certified by the American Board of Obstetrics & Gynecology, and is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetricians & Gynecologists. He has been named one of “America’s Top Obstetricians & Gynecologists”, and is an honored recipient of the Patient’s Choice award.

name: Miami Center of Excellence for Obstetrics & Gynecology
bio:
Stephanie graduated from the nurse midwifery program at the University of Miami in 2011. Stephanie has also been a Women’s Health Nurse Practitioner in private practice for over 15 years and prior to that she was a labor & delivery nurse for 3 years. In her early 20’s, while Stephanie was in her labor and delivery rotation in nursing school, she attended a birth that changed her life.
“Assisting a woman through a normal, natural laboring process was amazing! I knew at that instant when the mother I helped labor grasped my arm and said ‘thank you’, that I would dedicate my life to women’s health.” 
Stephanie has a large private practice, and is known for being thorough, gentle, and having great expertise on the most current trends in women’s health. A main focus for Stephanie is to empower women with a greater knowledge of their bodies, and to encourage a more active role in their healthcare decisions. This relates to birthing choices, birth control, use of hormones, women’s sexuality, and preventative care.
Stephanie is a mother of 3 beautiful children Max, JB, and Ruby. Stephanie has been a volunteer girls basketball coach, she loves Pilates, flying, and swimming. She is a member of Florida Nurses Association, Nurse Practitioners in Women’s Health, American College of Nurse Midwives, Femfessionals, and the South Florida Chapter of Nurse Midwives. Stephanie is on medical staff at Baptist Hospital

MiBella Wellness Center
bio:
Dr. Mia Cowan is Founder and Medical Director of MiBella Wellness Center. A native of Birmingham, AL, Dr. Cowan received both her Bachelor of Science degree in Biology and Master of Arts degree in Health Education and Promotion from the University of Alabama. She completed her Doctorate of Medicine and residency training in Obstetrics and Gynecology from the Medical College of Wisconsin. Dr. Cowan is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. She received her training as a Bariatric Medicine Specialist from the Center for Medical Weight Loss and has a Master of Business Administration degree from Auburn University.
Dr. Cowan provides exemplary care to adolescents and women of all ages for their gynecology care.  She has special interests in hormonal balance for women and men, holistic medicine and minimally invasive surgery.  In addition, she also provides comprehensive weight loss programs, Smartlipo and other aesthetic procedures in her office.  Her goal is to provide superior patient care to promote lifelong health and wellness.

name: Michael DuChamp DO
bio: Dr. Duchamp is a graduate of the University of North Texas Health Science Center at Fort Worth. He completed a residency in Orthopedic Surgery at Mount Clemens General Hospital in Michigan.  Being an orthopedic surgeon and having treated patients with fractures due to thin bones, he developed an interest in bio-identical hormone therapy as being a solution to help the body increase the strength of its bones.  Studies show that normal bone mass will increase while a person is being treated with bio-identical testosterone and estrogen.  Not only will they help the bones, but the bio-identical hormones protect the heart, brain, and breast.  Dr. Duchamp is excited about helping his patients to have a better and fuller life.

name: Michael DuChamp/Jones
bio: Dr. Duchamp is a graduate of the University of North Texas Health Science Center at Fort Worth. He completed a residency in Orthopedic Surgery at Mount Clemens General Hospital in Michigan. name: Michael J. McCauley, M.D., P.C.
bio: Dr. Michael J. McCauley has been practicing pain management and general anesthesia in the East Valley for over thirty years. He is a diplomat of the American Board of Anesthesiology and an active member of the International Spinal Injection Society, American Academy of Pain Management, Arizona Society of Anesthesiologists and the Association Society of Interventional Pain Physicians. He completed his studies and finished his internship and residency at the Medical College of Wisconsin. Following this he moved the Phoenix and has been practicing here ever since. He performs diagnostic and therapeutic spinal procedures at the Arizona Spine and Joint Hospital and Banner Desert Surgery Center.

name: Michele L. Neil DO
bio:
Dr. Neil graduated as a Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine from the Oklahoma State University College of Osteopathic Medicine in 2002. She is a Board Certified Internist and completed her Internal Medicine Residency at Tulsa Regional Medical Center, Tulsa, Oklahoma in 2005. She is also Board Certified Sports Medicine and completed her Fellowship through the University of Tulsa, Tulsa, Oklahoma in 2006.
 Dr. Neil focuses on Age Management Medicine, Naturopathic and Functional Medicine, Acupuncture, First Line Therapy- Lifestyle coaching. She is certified in the Functional Movement Systems, provides soft tissue modalities of Osteopathic Manipulative Therapy, nutrition/supplementation, exercise prescription, rest, stress management and hormone balance.
Dr. Neil has an extensive fitness and athletic background in Martial Arts (brown belt- Judo, Black belt Tae-Kwon-Do, Strength Training/Bodybuilding (multiple state and national titles), Russian Kettlebell System (RKC Certified, CK-FMS Certified), and Anusara/Iyengar Yoga Methods.

name: Michelle Anson, M.D., PLLC
bio: Considering there are literally hundreds of doctors practicing medicine in San Antonio, for Dr. Michelle Anson to have been chosen as one of the top doctors in San Antonio by S.A. Doctors Best of 2013 is quite an outstanding honor. To Dr. Anson’s patients, that accomplishment is no surprise. She is known for her warm and friendly style. Dr. Anson is deeply committed to the practice of medicine and is a devoted mother of three who enjoys spending her free time with her family. As a physician, she carries this love of family into the clinic where she helps ensure the total wellness of patients and their loved ones. Dr. Anson’s philosophy of patient care involves empowering patients with knowledge of their health conditions and helping them achieve the best quality of life. She received her undergraduate degree from the University of Texas at Austin where she was inducted into the Phi Beta Kappa honor society and then attended medical school at The University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio. She served as chief resident at CHRISTUS Santa Rosa before opening her own practice.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio:
Jessica (Jessie) Siemers is a board certified Women’s Health Nurse Practitioner.  Jessie received her Bachelor of Science in nursing from the University of Nebraska Medical Center  in 2008. She then went on to complete her Master’s in Nursing from the University of Nebraska Medical Center in 2012. She was a labor and nursing nurse prior to joining Dr. Hedrick’s practice.  
Jessie is certified in Electronic Fetal Monitoring. Jessie is a member of the Association of Women’s Health – Obstetrics and Neonatal Nursing and Sigma Theta Tau.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio:
Cindi Tripp is a board certified Women’s Health Nurse Practitioner. She attended Creighton University and received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing, and then went on to the University of Nebraska Medical Center to complete her Master of Science in Nursing. Prior to joining Dr. Sjulin at Mid-City OB-GYN she worked as a Nurse Practitioner in Gynecology/Oncology.
Ms. Tripp is a member of the Nebraska Nurse Practitioners as well as The American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio:
Cece Norton is a certified nurse midwife with over 20 years of midwifery and women’s health experience.  Currently she is practicing as a Nurse Practitioner in collaboration with Dr. Bill Kuyper.    She received her undergraduate education at the University of Texas Health Sciences Center at Houston.  She attended the University of Colorado Health Sciences Center completing a master’s degree in Maternal Fetal Nursing. She also attended Frontier School of Midwifery, now Frontier University, earning a post-graduate certificate in midwifery.
Her clinical experience includes all areas of OB and women’s health.  During her career she has practiced as a staff nurse, clinical nurse specialist and educator.  She joined Mid-City OB-GYN, P.C. in 2015.  In addition to practicing women’s health she is on the faculty at Clarkson College in the graduate nursing program. 
She holds certification from the American College of Nurse Midwives.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio:
Dr. Seeman was born and raised in Nebraska, growing up in the outskirts of Lincoln, NE. She did her undergraduate training at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln where she was a collegiate athlete for the Cornhuskers receiving many awards and honors. She has a Bachelor of Science degree in Exercise, Nutrition and Health Sciences and has a special interest in this area. She then attended the University of Nebraska School of Medicine where she received her Doctor of Medicine degree. She then went on to complete her residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Nebraska Medical College serving as a Chief Resident.
Dr. Seeman takes care of women of all ages with a full range of gynecology and obstetrics in her practice. She really enjoys taking care of pregnant patients and offers care including low risk, non-intervention pregnancies and high risk as well. VBACs are welcomed in her practice under the current guidelines. She offers minimally invasive surgery including Davinci Robotic surgery and in office procedures. She has special interest and training in breast feeding medicine and lactation support. She is passionate about offering these services to all of her patients. She is a member of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, Metro Omaha Medical Society and The American Academy of Breast Feeding Medicine.
Dr. Seeman is married to her husband Ben who works in law enforcement and was also born and raised in Nebraska. She has three young daughters and values her time being a mother, wife and physician. She enjoys fitness, traveling, music, crafting and spending precious time with her family and friends.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio:
Elizabeth (Liz) McIlree is a family Nurse Practitioner. She attended the University of Nebraska Medical Center and received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing. She then went on to University of Texas – Southwestern Medical Center to complete her Master of Science in Nursing. Upon completion of her Master’s degree, she began working with Dr. Ann Sjulin at Mid City OB-GYN as a Nurse Practitioner.
Ms. McIlree is a member of the Nebraska Nurse Practitioner’s as well as The American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio:
Tedette Ellis is a nurse practitioner in Omaha, Nebraska. Ms. Ellis is licensed in the state of Nebraska. She attended Clarkson College of Nursing in Omaha, Nebraska to complete her Bachelor of Science in Nursing. She then went on to University of Texas – Southwestern Medical Center to complete her Master of Science in Nursing. Upon completion of her Master’s degree, Ms. Ellis worked for the American Red Cross and Omaha OB-GYN Associates before joining Dr. June Wedergren at Mid City OB-GYN, P.C, a private practice clinic in Omaha, Nebraska.
She is a member of Nebraska Nurse Practitioners and the National Association of Nurse Practitioners in Women’s Health.
In her spare time, she enjoys spending time with her family, friends and dogs.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio:
Juli Eckert is a board certified Physician Assistant. She attended Bellevue University where she received her Bachelor of Arts degree. She then attended The University of Nebraska Medical Center where she received her Masters degree in Physician Assistant studies. Since joining the practice at Mid-City OB-GYN, P.C. in 1996, she has also received advanced training in colposcopy through the University of Texas Southwestern Medical Center in Dallas, Texas.
Ms. Eckert is board certified by the National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants. She is a member of the American Academy of Physician Assistants, and the Nebraska Academy of Physician Assistants.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio:
Dr. Siemers is a board certified obstetrician/gynecologist. He attended the University of North Dakota in Grand Forks, North Dakota for his undergraduate and Medical Doctorate. His residency program in Obstetrics and Gynecology was spent at the University of Nebraska Medical Center in Omaha, Nebraska. In 1989, Dr. Siemers and Dr. Lonny Legino started Mid City OB-GYN, P.C, a private practice clinic in Omaha, Nebraska.
Dr. Siemers is a member of the Metro Omaha Medical Society, Omaha OB/GYN Society, Nebraska Medical Association, American Medical Association, and a Fellow in the American College of OB/GYN.

name: Mid-City OBGYN
bio: Dr. Kuyper is a board certified Obstetrician/Gynecologist who grew up in Southern California. He completed his undergraduate education from the University of California, San Diego where he graduated with honors. He received his medical education at the University of California, San Diego School of Medicine. Dr. Kuyper completed his residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Santa Clara Valley Medical Center in San Jose California where he also served as Chief Resident for his last year of training. Dr. Kuyper joined Mid-City OB-GYN, P.C. in 2000.

name: Mid-Florida Age Management
bio:
The traditional medical view has been that aging is a process with inevitable complications such as cardiovascular disease, diabetes, cancer, and dementia, as well as the steady decline of physical and cognitive abilities. The newer approach seeks to prevent these disorders and possibly slow the process of aging, not just treat its complications.

Dr. Turner is a board certified physician, advanced fellowship trained in Regenerative and Functional Medicine and a diplomate of the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine, with over 25 years of clinical experience. Dr. Turner graduated from the University of Arizona and received residency training at Vanderbilt University. He is the Medical Director of Mid-Florida Medical Suite.
Dr. Turner uses conventional, nutritional, complementary and alternative modalities to help heal patients of their various diseases. He specializes in hypertension, lipid disorders, prevention and treatment of cardiovascular disease, nutritional and weight management, clinical age management, general medicine and Bio-Identical hormone replacement. He has a special interest in anti-aging medicine for which he uses a combination of natural and prescriptive therapies.

name: Midwest Internist Limited
bio: Dr. Padamjit Singh has been practicing medicine for over 20 yrs.  She is a board certified Internal Medicine Specialist and is currently on staff at two prestigious area hospitals, Good Samaritan Hospital & Edwards Hospital.  She has been nominated three times in the area as Most Compassionate Physician.  She has an excellent office staff team.  She is a proud member of the BioTE group of providers .

name: Miggy Scott PA-C
bio:
Margaret “ Miggy “ Scott PA-C is a certified Physician Assistant with a passion for helping people achieve optimum health through  body, mind and spirit  with integrative medicine.  She has a B.S. in Microbiology from the University of Texas at Arlington and received her Physician Assistant training at UT Southwestern Medical Center.  She has a Fellowship in Integrative Medicine from the University of Arizona Center for Integrative Medicine.  She is pursuing advanced studies in Botanical Medicine with one of her mentors, Tieraona Low Dog MD . Miggy lives with her husband, Steve, 2 dogs and 2 cats. They have a grown son. Miggy enjoys yoga, the out of doors, weight training and reading. She is also a volunteer with SearchOne Rescue Team.
Organizations: American Academy of Physician Assistants, Texas Academy of Physician Assistants, Wilderness Medical Society

name: Mihills Webb
bio:
As a native of North Texas, Dr. Cody Mihills is excited to bring quality medical care to the Southlake area. He graduated L.D. Bell High School and went on to earn his Bachelor of Arts Degree in Biology, magna cum laude, from Texas A&M University in College Station. He attended Baylor College of Medicine in Houston and did his residency with The University of Texas Southwestern Medical Center at McLennan County Medical Education and Research Foundation in Waco. Dr. Mihills was named chief resident for his final year there.
Dr. Mihills is a Diplomat of the American Board of Family Medicine and holds current licensure in Texas and Louisiana. His medical interests include preventative care, chronic disease management, office procedures, and clinical trials.
Dr. Mihills deeply believes in giving back to the community and the world. Locally, he has served as a volunteer physician for Carroll Independent School District’s Medical Academy since 2004. Globally, he has been on seven medical mission trips to help the needy in Nicaragua, Kenya and Peru.
Dr. Mihills and his wife Cayce enjoy spending time with their growing family, travel, and community involvement. Dr. Mihills looks forward to enriching the lives of his patients with health and wellbeing.

name: Miles Hormone Healthy
bio: Regina Miles received her undergraduate degree as well as her Masters of science in nursing from the University of Northern Colorado. She has worked in a variety of settings including the emergency room, wound care, burn care, intensive care and hyperbaric medicine. She is board certified as a family nurse practitioner through the ANCC.  She loves Colorado and enjoys hiking, skiing, snowshoeing, fishing, camping and baseball. Regina believes in sitting down and  listening to her patients. She strives  to help patients in a holistic manner and is very passionate about improving their quality of life.

name: Millennium Laser and Aesthetics Center
bio: Dr. Scott Gulinson founded the Millennium Laser and Aesthetics Center in Glendale, Arizona in 2008. He is a fully trained and Board-Certified Women’s Healthcare expert in and has been in practice since 1999 in the Valley of the Sun. He trained in prestigious University settings in the Denver, Colorado and San Antonio Texas Health Sciences Centers and has earned an outstanding reputation for excellence in Women’s Healthcare. Having listened to the concerns and desires of women in his practice for over 11 years and continuing through this day, Dr. Gulinson has become especially attuned to their condition and is able to offer his patients knowledge, choices and alternatives in their medical and cosmetic healthcare. In 2005, Dr Gulinson expanded to incorporate aesthetic surgical procedures and has received extensive training in these including lip sculpting from some of the world’s most renowned and most experienced cosmetic surgeons.

name: Minal Mehta, MD
bio:
Dr. Minal Mehta is a board certified physician who specializes in the fields of obstetrics and gynecology. The doctor and her staff serve the residents of Fountain Valley, California and many nearby communities, including Huntington Beach, Costa Mesa, Newport Beach, Westminster, Santa Ana, and Anaheim. She has over 18 years of experience serving the community as licensed OB/GYN. At her office, the doctor uses state of the art diagnostic tools and treatment options to provide her patients with the best medical care possible. She performs deliveries at Hoag Hospital, Orange Coast Memorial and Fountain Valley Regional. 
Dr. Mehta received her medical degree in 1998 when she graduated from Chicago Medical School. At that time, she turned her interest toward her chosen area of practice. She specializes in treating OB/GYN patients who are high risk as well as those who have problems with fertility and conception

name: Mind and Body Wellness Spa
bio: Dr. Fath is a Board Certified Laparoscopic General and Bariatric Surgeon. A native Texan, Dr. Fath went to medical school at the University of Texas Health Science Center in San Antonio and graduated in 1993. He completed his surgical residency at Indiana University in Indianapolis, Indiana in 1999 and became Board Certified in Bariatrics in 2002. Dr. Fath practiced General and Bariatric Surgery in Seguin, San Antonio and Odessa, Texas and ultimately Gisborne, New Zealand. He has been married to his wife and business partner, Teresa, for 22 years and they have three children.

name: Mind Body Spirit Care
bio:
Dr. Shemesh graduated Magna Cum Laude from Rutgers College with highest distinction in Biochemistry and membership in Phi Beta Kappa. He then attended New York Medical College, followed by a residency at New York University Medical Center, where he completed a fellowship in pelvic surgery. He served as a clinical instructor at NYU Medical Center prior to moving to Tampa Florida. After having surgery for malignant melanoma in 1993, he became disenchanted with the conventional medicine model approach to understanding disease causes and prevention. After practicing obstetrics and gynecology for more than 10 years, he then turned his attention to holistic and integrative medicine, and expanded the universal holistic approaches of healing to men and children as well. He founded Mind Body Spirit Care, an integrative and Holistic Medical Center with offices in Carrollwood and South Tampa, providing a partnership with patients for individualized care using evidence based modalities for healing. Dr. Shemesh is Board Certified by the American Board of Integrative Holistic Medicine, the American Academy of Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine, and the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology, with certification in medical acupuncture from Harvard Medical School. He is a contributing author to the medical textbook "Food and Nutrients in Disease Management". He is married and has 4 wonderful children.
Dr. Shemesh focuses on identifying the root causes of health imbalance by testing for hormones, nutritional deficiencies, and other imbalances using cutting edge diagnostic and predictive functional measurements. He then creates individualized care plans that incorporate natural hormone replacement, diet and lifestyle modifications, physician grade supplements, stress coping tools, and eastern medicine practices including acupuncture, Ayurveda, medical qigong, therapeutic yoga, and mind-body-spirit connectivity, to support conventional medicine in addressing the healing of all interconnected aspects of our well-being – mind, body, and spirit.

name: Mind Body Spirit Care
bio: Born and raised in Sarasota Florida, Michelle attended Western Carolina University where she obtained her BSN in nursing, graduated with Cum Laude and joined the Air Force Nurse Corps in 1986.  There, she began her love of women’s health as an OB nurse, manager, and educator.  In 1997, she graduated from Georgetown University with a Master’s in Nursing specializing in OB/GYN and Midwifery, dedicating her life to listening to women and ensuring that each of them had the education necessary to make decisions for their own individualized plan of care.  In 2001, she retired from the Air Force as a Major after 15 years, worked in Georgia, and returned to Florida in 2003 where she provided OB/GYN care to the New Port Richey/Tarpon Springs, Florida areas.  She also trained in Botox and facial fillers with extensive education and experience, providing over 1000 treatments to include eye brow lifting, restoring cheek volume, and her special favorite, restoring  lips to their prior natural appearance.  In 2011, after listening to patient complaints of fatigue, mood swings, weight gain, and hair loss, she became interested in bio-identical hormone therapy, thyroid management, and adrenal fatigue and joined Dr. Shemesh,  expanding her practice in integrative medicine to include natural hormone pellet therapy.  Michelle has become passionate about improving quality of life and preventing disease with the intent to enable men and women to feel vibrant on the inside as well as look great on the outside.

name: Mitch Moskowitz MD
bio:
Dr. Mitch Moskowitz is a board certified Urologist practicing in Dallas and Plano. After completing his training in New York, Dr Moskowitz joined Dallas Urology Associates in 1993. Dr. Moskowitz treats adult and pediatric patients, men and women. He has special interests in prostate disease, kidney stones, infertility, vasectomy, and all areas of Urologic cancer.
Over the past several years, Dr Moskowitz has been aware of the increasing needs of his patients in treating testosterone imbalance as this effects both the mind and body. Hormonal replacement therapy is a common treatment modality that allows Dr Moskowitz to treat the whole patient.

name: Mitchell Medical
bio: Dr. James Keith Mitchell, MD earned his Bachelor of Science degree from the Henderson State University and graduate degree from the University of Arkansas of Medical Sciences.  His greatest goal as a physician is to provide patients with healthy alternative choices to enhance health and well being.  He feels it is important for patients to take control of and responsibility for their own health.  He works with his patients to lend support and discuss all options with regard to their own healthcare.  Dr. Mitchell is pleased to be a part of the wonderful BioTE family of select physicians across the country.  He believes in restoring and balancing ones hormones to make a significant difference in the quality of life.

name: Mobility Spine and Sports
bio:
Medical Director and Founder of MOBILITY SPINE AND SPORTS, with its new location in the iconic
Round Building at 3101 N federal highway, Suite 201 in Oakland Park, Fort Lauderdale. Offering bio-identical hormone replacement therapy, complete
musculoskeletal, nonsurgical orthopedics, interventional spine, interventional joint, regenerative medicine,
as well as osteopathic family medicine to patients ranging from the very young to the very experienced. Dr.
Bush has been serving, treating and healing the South Florida region since 2003 and we are proud to announce
the opening of our new center - MOBILITY SPINE AND SPORTS. Look us up online or give us a call, our
friendly staff is looking forward to welcoming you into our family.

name: Modern Health Clinic
bio:
Dr. Agnieszka (Anna) Wolyn was born in Poland, where she graduated from medical school in 1990. With the collapse of the “Iron Curtain”, she and her husband Robert Wolyn, MD, came to Detroit area to be reunited with Robert’s mother.
Dr Anna Wolyn completed her residency at William Beaumont Hospital, Royal Oak, Michigan and was certified by the American Board of Pediatrics in 1996. Anna Wolyn, MD had always an interest in integrative medicine. She follows functional medicine approach utilizing integrative and conventional treatments. She sees patients (all ages) with chronic problems including GI issues, hormonal problems , chronic fatigue syndrome, fibromyalgia , migraine headaches, ADHD, ASD, obesity, thyroid disorders, metabolic syndrome, allergies, asthma, MS, autoimmune disorders and many others.
Dr Wolyn was trained in DAN! Protocol and develops individualized treatments for each patient. While pursuing her passion for functional medicine she was also trained in LIVING YOUNGER -anti aging system- where she learned how to achieve an optimum health through lifestyle changes and personalized preventive program.
Dr Wolyn has a daughter and son, loves singing, hiking and practicing yoga. In her spare time she goes to an opera, symphony or ballet. Dr Wolyn along with her husband Robert and their kids relocated to Flagstaff in pursuit of career and lifestyle opportunities in Northern Arizona

name: Modern Rejuvenation Center
bio:
Dr. Jocelyn Bush

Dr. Jocelyn Bush is a board-certified anesthesiology and pain management physician at the Center for Pain Management.  She brings an extensive background and commitment to the practice in the field of  interventional pain management.  Dr. Jocelyn Bush is a Harvard & University of Chicago trained physician who focuses not only on alleviating patients long-term pain symptoms, but also on providing medical treatment options to patients who are seeking immediate relief from a myriad of life altering symptoms.

name: Modern Rejuvenation Center
bio:
Kevin Neese, M.D., M.B.A., is part of Post-Acute Care Specialists, LLC, (PACS), a group of hospitalists offering integrated and longitudinal healthcare solutions for the medical complexities of today’s patients.
Dr. Neese is the director of the hospitalist program at Community Hospital South — he is also the medical director overseeing all hospitalists at the four southside CarDon communities. He sets the standard for making the transition from the hospital to the senior living community environment a smooth one.

name: Monique Martel FNP
bio:
Monique’s career started with a graduate’s degree from a Business College in Quebec , Canada in the 1950’s. Deciding to move to the United States in the 1960’s, she was then able to pursue what she loved by attending college for a BSN in Denver CO.
After a very fulfilling several years as an RN, she decided to return to school to further her skills in this field. Monique graduated with a Family Nurse Practitioner’s Degree in 1981.
Throughout the following years, Monique has worked in a variety of settings including Emergency, Pre Natal Care, Pediatrics and now specifically, Women's Health Care. With the culmination of all of her hard work, she happily started her own private practice in 2001.
Over the last ten years of her practice, she has been able to place her focus on acute and chronic illness. Monique has found that Bio Identical hormone therapy, including pellet therapy, has been an integral part in helping her clients maintain and lead a healthier lifestyle.

name: Mont Belvieu Urgent and Family Care
Morganstern Urology Clinic PC
bio:
Steven L. Morganstern, M.D. is known as “the doctor who trains doctors.” He is an acclaimed urologist and surgeon specializing in male sexual dysfunction and problems of the urinary tract with a subspecialty in penile implants, enhancement (penis enlargement), prostate cancer, benign prostate problems, HGH treatments, and testosterone pellet therapy.
Dr. Morganstern has been practicing urology in Atlanta, Georgia for over 35 years, and takes pride in continuing to practice medicine in a sensitive, confidential and skilled manner. He is a past director of urological services at Metropolitan Hospital (Atlanta, Georgia). Dr. Morganstern is a national lecturer and has appeared on “Good Morning America”, CNN, “20/20?, and numerous local newscasts. He has introduced many new methods of urologic treatment and also teaches surgical procedures to physicians nationwide.

name: MP Health P.C.
bio: Kristine is a Board-Certified NP. She graduated with her BSN from Goshen College and her MSN from Grand Valley State University. Kris has worked since 2008 as a Family Nurse Practitioner with a strong interest in prevention and promotion of health. She is a previous business owner of a private family practice and Started a "Paths to Wellness" program with our local Amish community women. Kris is very active in state and national professional organizations including CAPNI AANP and ANCC.

name: My Family Physicians
bio:
A native of Southern California, Dr. Zahedi graduated
from the California State University with the highest
honors, where he received dual Bachelor’s Degree in
Biochemistry and Medical Physiology. He attended the
Chicago Medical School where he completed his MD with
Alpha Omega Alpha honors distinction and went on to
complete his surgical training at Huntington Memorial
Hospital in Pasadena, CA – a University of Southern
California (USC) affiliated teaching hospital. Dr. Zahedi
went on to complete post-residency training in Aesthetic
Medicine, receiving Diplomat status through the American
Academy of Aesthetic Medicine. He also completed his
Masters in Public Health (MPH) from the University of
Southern California Keck School of Medicine. Dr. Zahedi
was recruited to the Valencia Medical Center for his
expertise in Aesthetic Medicine and Anti-aging therapies.

name: My Gyn LA
bio:
Dr. Christine Collins is an attending physician  at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center  and has been in private practice since 1996.   She graduated from USC School of Medicine and did her residency training at Cedars Sinai Medical Center.  During medical school, Dr. Collins won the prestigious ARCS (Achievement Reward for College Scientists) Scholarship and graduated as a Dean's Scholar.
Dr. Collins focuses on  nutrition and uses an integrative medical approach in  caring for her patients.  Over the past five years, she has expanded her knowledge base and is board certified in Anti-aging and Regenerative Medicine.   Her main interest is treating women of all ages using an integrative and holistic approach.
Dr. Collins recently became  trained in using the Mona Lisa laser.  This laser is revolutionizing women's healthcare and improving the lives of women experiencing the vaginal dryness and painful intercourse common in perimenopause and menopause.   She is board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a fellow of the American Congress of Obstetrics and Gynecology.

name: MY MD Select
bio:
Jay Marsolan Bio  
Jay was born and raised in Southeast Texas where he discovered his love for helping others early in life.  In 1992, while in high school he completed an Emergency Medical Technician course and began working as an EMT with the local Emergency Medical Service (EMS) in the community where he was raised. While attending college, he continued serving in EMS and became a licensed paramedic. After graduating from Lamar University with a bachelor’s degree in biology, Jay worked full-time as a paramedic. During his 12 years of working in EMS, Jay had the opportunity to serve with several EMS departments throughout the state of Texas and also spent many of those years working as a flight paramedic on EMS helicopters. The wealth of experience he gained and his passion for helping others in their time of greatest need inspired him to continue his education and become a registered nurse.   
Jay and his family moved to Longview, Texas in 2006 where he worked as a nurse for Longview Regional Medical Center in the Emergency Department. Jay graduated from Ball State University in 2011 with a master’s of nursing degree with specialization as a family nurse practitioner. After graduating, he worked as an emergency nurse practitioner alongside an amazing group of emergency medicine physicians. Jay has also worked as a nurse practitioner in urgent care, family practice and occupational medicine settings.

name: My New Balanced Life & Wellness Anti-Aging Institute
bio:
I was born in Laredo,Texas. My dream since I was a child was to be a doctor so I could help others. I did my undergraduate training in Monterrey, Nuevo León Mexico at Universidad de Monterrey where I earned my medical degree. After passing my boards to practice medicine in the United States, I completed my Residency training in family practice at The McAllen Family Practice Residency Program which is affiliated with UT Health Science Center at San Antonio.  Family Practice & Obstetrics is my passion and the residency program I completed provided excellent training in these two areas. I have been in practice now for aprox 13 years with my best friend as my partner and I wouldn't change a thing. I have been truly blessed to be able to do what I love surrounded by people who I care about and who share my same values. During the early part of my formation I started to develop an interest in Aesthetics and have had the privilege of opening a Medspa and dedicating some of my time to grow in this area as well. Recently my focus has been preventative medicine and focusing on helping my patients live healthier and happier lives. I was recently appointed as chairperson for the Preventative Medicine Committee at one of our local hospitals. Over the years I have seen the main aspects of life which influence our culture and our people and lead them to develop chronic illnesses. . I am currently studying to be a health coach since I would like to dedicate more time to helping people reach their goals in weight loss but most important help them live a more balanced life. I am very interested in hormone testing and natural hormone replacement with bio identical hormones through pellet therapy.
I commit to continue my endeavor of preventing illness through education, change in lifestyle, optimizing patients hormones and most important being there as support to my patients. I am very excited to be the first to bring BioTe medical to the Rio Grande Valley!

name: Natural Bio Health - Austin
bio:
David began his medical career while serving in the United States Army as a Medic. He continued his studies at Southwest Texas State University earning a Bachelor of Exercise and Sports Science degree in 2008. Following his undergraduate studies, David attended Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center where he received his Master of Physician Assistant Studies degree in 2011. 
Prior to joining the Natural Bio Health team, he practiced in family medicine, urgent care and male hormone replacement therapy. David simultaneously serves as a Physician Assistant in the Texas Army National Guard. Currently assigned to 1st Battalion 143rd Infantry Regiment (Airborne), 173rd Airborne Brigade Combat Team. His abiding interests outside of work are spending time with his wife and children, running, resistance training and remaining active with outdoor activities.

name: Natural Bio Health - Austin
bio:
Kimberly Yule joins our team with over 22 years of experience in Women’s Health. Her certifications include:
– Aesthetics Certified
– BioTE Certified
– NCC Board Certified
Kimberly specializes in Bioidentical Hormone Therapy and Aesthetics, and is seeing patients in our Lakeway and Round Rock Clinics.

name: Natural Bio Health - College Station
bio:
Renee is a third generation nurse that comes to us with previous training in weight loss, as well as aesthetic medicine. She graduated with a Bachelor of Arts Degree with a double major in Business Administration and Marketing in 2004 from Houston Baptist University.  Shortly after, she was employed by the world’s largest public relations firm.  In her desire to work in the medical field and work closely with people, Renee decided to return to school to become a registered nurse. 
In 2008 she earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Nursing from Prairie View A&M University to which she put to use in the areas of cardiology, transplant medicine, and aesthetics. In June of 2016, she graduated with a Master of Science degree in Nursing as a family nurse practitioner. Since graduation, she has worked in the areas of weight loss and aesthetic medicine.
Renee is board certified by the American Association of Nurse Practitioners in which she is additionally an active member, and is also a member of Houston Area of Nurse Practitioners. Renee is an international medical missionary worker, as well as a successful entrepreneur in the healthcare field. She also enjoys travelling and backpacking.

name: Natural Bio Health - College Station
bio:
Mr. Gonzales received his training in bioidentical hormone therapy and medical weight loss under Dr. Joseph Feste and is completing certifications from both the Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine and Worldlink Medical.  
Mr. Gonzales is also a BioTe Certified practitioner.
Mr. John Gonzales graduated in 2000 with a Bachelor of Science degree in Exercise Sports Science from the University of Texas at San Antonio.  In 2003 he received a Bachelor of Science degree in Physician Assistant Studies from the University of Texas at Pan American.  He is NCCPA board certified and is a member of both the Texas Academy of Physician Assistants and the American Academy of Physician Assistants.  Mr. Gonzales has over 10 years of family medicine and pediatric experience, emphasizing health & wellness, cardiovascular disease, and diabetes.  
Mr. Gonzales received his training in bioidentical hormone therapy and medical weight loss under Dr. Joseph Feste and is completing certifications from both the Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine and Worldlink Medical.  
Mr. Gonzales is also a BioTe Certified practitioner.
Mr. Gonzales is a two-time Ironman finisher and enjoys helping others reach their training goals by developing personalized diet and training programs for endurance events.  He loves sports and outdoors, but especially loves traveling and spending time with his wife and two children.

name: Natural Bio Health - Denver CO
bio: Sonia Mookherjea, PA- C is a Physician Assistant who is passionate about uncovering and treating the underlying cause of disease for each individual. She graduated Summa Cum Laude with a Bachelor of Science in Biology and Psychology from the University of Hartford and earned her Masters in Physician Assistant studies from the University of Medicine and Dentistry of NJ in 2012. She has devoted her career to developing expertise in integrative and personalized medicine to optimize health and wellness. Sonia brings to our team clinical experience in integrative psychiatry and neurology, functional medicine and bioidentical hormone replacement therapy. In addition, she has experience in educating clinicians and patients how to interpret genetic testing data and tailor personalized medicine treatment strategies accordingly using evidence based nutraceuticals and pharmaceuticals. She has furthered her training through the American Academy of Anti Aging Medicine (A4M), The Amen Brain Health Courses, and BioTe Medical BHRT Training.

name: Nature Coast Wellness Clinic
bio:
Dr. Okoroji, who resides and practices in Tallahassee, Florida, started his medical education and training in Nigeria. Since then, he has developed extensive international medical experience in the field of obstetrics, gynecology, women’s health and primary care. He has been the recipient of numerous awards and honors at both the undergraduate and graduate medical levels.
He is currently the Chairman of the Department of OB/GYN at Capital Regional Medical Center. He is also a fellow of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, American College of Obstetricians & Gynecologists and American Academy of Family Physicians. Dr. Okoroji also serves as a clinical assistant professor in Obstetrics & Gynecology at the Florida State University College of Medicine, Tallahassee Regional Campus.
Dr. Okoroji is happily married with four children, three sons and a daughter. He enjoys his rare time away from work with family and is active in his local church.

name: Nature Cure Clinic
bio: Dr McConnell, while licensed both as Naturopath and Osteopath, is at heart all about treating the cause of disease and suffering.  By maximizing health with diet and exercise/sport, he also offers bioidentical HRT, manual manipulation, and joint/back injections with prolo/PRP/stem cell therapies.  Dr McConnell makes every attempt to wean his patients off of excessive medications.  He and his wife Teresa are opening up the Nature Cure Retreat, an in-patient facility, in Green Valley, Arizona.  They have also opened up the Nature Cure Clinic, three miles away from the retreat, on the south side of Green Valley.

name: NAVA Health and Vitality Center
bio:
As our Medical Director, and one of the first physicians to join the Nava Health & Vitality Center, Dr. Douglas Lord has made significant contributions to our Center and its founding principles. Dr. Lord has helped develop and implement the Nava Method™—Nava’s proprietary approach to total body wellness. He has also been instrumental in liaising with other expert practitioners to successfully implement Nava’s range of therapies, treatments, and products.

In his role at Nava, Dr. Lord is responsible for maintaining Nava’s innovation and for creating the best experience for clients by ensuring they have access to the newest and best advances in integrative wellness. He achieves this by identifying and developing strategic partnerships in the field, and acting as a facilitator between Nava and various providers.

Doug’s passion for health and wellness is evident in both the way he lives his life and in the way he practices medicine. He is eager to share his extensive medical knowledge and experience with other Nava Directors.

Since he was raised to value a healthy, active lifestyle and has always had a strong interest in medicine, it was only natural that Doug chose to become a doctor. After graduating from Loma Linda University Medical School in California, Doug completed his residency program at George Washington University in Washington D.C. Since then, he has acquired over 40 years practicing Obstetrics and Gynecology in the Washington D.C. Metropolitan area where he also introduced the innovative concept of family-centered obstetrics. Over the course of his career, Doug has developed the reputation as a highly respected practitioner and an expert in cutting-edge surgical techniques. 

Along the way, Doug gained exposure to integrative medicine and realized how narrow and limited his view had been as a traditional doctor. Always taught to think outside the box, and with a natural instinct to question everything, Doug became interested in learning more about the field of integrative medicine. He pursued his interest, training at the American Academy of Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine, and went on to study integrative medicine at the Sajune Institute of Regenerative and Restorative Medicine in Orlando, FL. 

Passionate about learning, teaching, and helping people, Doug is very involved in using scientific methods to help individuals lead healthy lives. He is excited about the opportunities for wellness and the extended resources that Nava offers its clients. 

In order to balance out his busy career, Doug maintains an active, healthy lifestyle. He describes himself as an avid golfer and travels regularly with his family, taking adventurous trips around the world to see how the rest of the world lives.

name: NAVA Health and Vitality Center
bio: Dr. Lisa Nguyen has been practicing medicine for twenty years. She focused on general obstetrics as an OBGYN and previously worked with Nava Medical Director, Dr. Douglas Lord. It is through Dr. Lord that she has expanded her protocol to include a passion for integrative wellness. A Maryland native, Lisa stayed true to her roots, securing her undergraduate and medical degree through the University of Maryland. Dr. Nguyen has three children and as a busy working mom, still makes time to support her local Vietnamese community and enjoys spending time with her family following the Maryland Terps.
