name: NAVA Health and Vitality Center
bio:
Kara L Kelly, NP-C, M.Ed.
Kara graduated from Georgetown University in 2014 with a Master of Science in Nursing degree in Family Practice.  She also completed a Master of Education degree from Cleveland State University in Exercise Physiology in 2005.  Kara has been with Nava Health and Vitality Center in Chevy Chase, Maryland since June of 2014.  She is board certified as a Family Nurse Practitioner by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.

name: NAVA Health and Vitality Center
bio: Nayo Wills, M.D. is Board-Certified in Internal and Integrative Medicine.  She earned her B.A. from the University of Virginia and Medical Degree from Thomas Jefferson Medical College in Philadelphia. She completed her residency in Internal Medicine at Washington Hospital Center in Washington, D.C.  She also has extensive training and experience in mind-body medicine, metaphysics, acupuncture, weight optimization and nutritional healing.

name: Nazarian Plastic Surgery
bio:
Dr. Sheila Nazarian, founder of Nazarian Plastic Surgery, is a board-certified, Beverly Hills plastic surgeon trained in cosmetic surgery, plastic surgery, reconstructive surgery, hand and burns surgery. Her top-notch education, experience, commitment and dedication in the field of plastic surgery and to her patients have earned her an excellent reputation. Some of the plastic surgery and non-surgical procedures she specializes in are CoolSculpting®, Fat Freezing, Tummy Tuck, Liposuction, Breast Augmentation(Implants), Kybella, Laser Tattoo Removal and more.
Topnotch Education & Training
In her youth, Dr. Nazarian was accepted by Harvard-Westlake for middle and high school, where she honed her academic and artistic skills. During this time, she was awarded a Bronfman Youth Fellowship in Israel where she received 6 weeks of leadership training. She attended Columbia University in New York and graduated with a BA in economics with a premedical concentration. From there, she matriculated into Yeshiva University’s Albert Einstein College of Medicine. She then matched into a combined plastic surgery residency at the University of Southern California.
Dr. Nazarian earned a Masters in Medical Management (MMM) at USC’s Marshall School of Business during her research years as well. As a result, she developed and launched an organic line of skin care products for pregnant and lactating women. As a mother of three, she felt a need for safe and luxurious skin care products for this time in a woman’s life. These products can be found at www.spamomma.co.
Between her general surgery and plastic surgery years, she served as the Division of Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery’s Clinical Research Fellow for two years where she published multiple journal articles and presented at national meetings. She continues to serve as a mentor at USC in her work as assistant professor.
Natural Looking Outcomes Through Patient-Centered Approach & Artistry
Dr. Nazarian understands that appearance and self-confidence interplay. She enjoys improving a patient’s appearance as this often improves quality of life. Her meticulous eye for detail reflects the artistry that distinguishes Dr. Nazarian’s work as a plastic surgeon and her commitment to achieving natural-looking outcomes that blend well with the patient’s overall facial or body proportions. Dr. Nazarian is always available to answer any questions and is dedicated to helping you feel comfortable about your procedure. She looks forward to being a supportive partner on your journey.
Dr. Nazarian’s approach to your treatment starts with patient listening. Then, after a complete and thorough examination, she will review whether you are a good candidate for the procedure and explain your treatment options and realistic expectations with you. If you are not a good candidate for a procedure, Dr. Nazarian will be honest and explain why. What Dr. Nazarian will not do is pressure you into having unnecessary, unsafe, or additional surgeries. Dr. Nazarian believes that being a physician is an honor and a privilege – a profession that cannot be without ethics. After all, a plastic surgeon must be a sound doctor first.
Dr. Nazarian is trilingual and speaks English, Spanish and Farsi.

name: Nazarian Plastic Surgery
bio:
Mastaneh is an experienced injector and laser practitioner. She is passionate about creating a personalized treatment considering your specific skin type, treatment goals and your availability for downtime. We have every technology available here at Nazarian Plastic Surgery to accommodate your needs.
Mastaneh Haykani is a certified physician assistant through the National Commission of Certification of Physician Assistant. She has completed her master of science degree at Loma Linda University with the highest honors. She specialized in dermatology.
Mastaneh Haykani is a dynamic, proactive, enthusiastic individual who utilizes her skills, knowledge, energy and passion to provide quality care for patients.

name: Neem Medical Spa & Wellness Center
bio:
Website-Short bio

Dr. Rosy Sandhu is the founding director of Neem Medical Spa and a staff physician at Melrose Wakefield Hospital and Lawrence Memorial Hospital. Dr. Sandhu is a board-certified internal medicine physician with 10 years of hospital medicine experience. She has a special interest in anti-aging and aesthetic medicine and has had years of training in advanced cosmetic procedures and medical weight loss.
Dr. Sandhu completed her residency in Internal Medicine at Rochester General Hospital in New York and has been practicing medicine for over a decade. She is certified in Aesthetics and Medical Weight Loss by the International Association for Physicians in Aesthetic Medicine. Dr. Sandhu is a member of the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine and American Society of Bariatric Physicians, and her leadership in healthcare is why she was chosen for the VIP Woman of the Year Circle by the National Association of Professional Women (NAPW).
Apart from her career in medicine, Dr. Sandhu is married and has a four-year-old daughter who is the love of her life! She loves to take her to the beach or the zoo and enjoys spending time with her family and friends.
Dr. Sandhu’s vision is to make Neem Medical Spa the ultimate wellness destination in the Northeast region. Her center offers a vast array of anti-aging, rejuvenating, weight loss, and wellness services that combine the latest advances in western technology for aesthetic treatments, such as state-of-the-art laser treatments, radio-frequency-assisted body contouring and skin tightening, physician-directed weight loss, Bio-Identical Hormone Replacement Therapy, dermal fillers and injectables, and chemical peel treatments. Given her eastern roots and interest in Ayurveda, the ancient holistic science from the East, she brings the benefits of time-proven Neem-based natural wellness treatments that are incorporated in many of the skin care treatments.

name: Neera Bhatia MD
bio:
I pride myself on my commitment to patients. My commitment manifests itself through a compassionate disposition and a self-demanding approach. I treat each patient as I would a member of my own family. I draw on my significant experience as a clinician, and I stay up to date with current treatment options.
I am committed to the education of future doctors for San Antonio and the country. For the past thirty years, I have served as a clinical professor in obstetrician/gynecology at the University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio. 

This commitment forms the basis for my experience as a physician.  My fundamental promise to you: I pledge to build an enduring relationship with you.

name: Neighborhood Medical Care
bio:
Dr. Russell Phillips grew up in Oklahoma, where he attended both college and medical school.  Following completion of his medical training, Dr. Phillips moved to Texas in 1990.  He understands the illnesses and injuries common to the great southwest.

Before attending the University of Oklahoma State University College of Osteopathic Medicine and Surgery, where he received his medical diploma, Dr. Phillips attended undergraduate studies at Oklahoma State University in Stillwater. 

Dr. Phillips is Board Certified in Family Practice by the American Osteopathic Board of Family Practice (AOBFP).  As a proud father of two, he has a fond appreciation for the need to keep all the members of a family happy and healthy. 

Dr. Phillips' is a lifelong fan of the cinema.  Some of his favorite films include the George Lucas Star Wars series, and of course his family loves anything Disney.

name: NeuLogics Wellness and Medical Spa
bio: Dr. Love’s primary interests are in Age Management, Preventive Health Care, Cosmetic Medicine, Medical Laser Skin Therapies, Bio-Identical Hormone Replacement Therapy and Bariatric Medicine. His medical degree is from the Edward Via College of Osteopathic Medicine at Virginia Tech. He completed his Internship training in Emergency Medicine at CAMC, finished Residency training in Internal Medicine at Camden Clark Medical Center and completed his Fellowship training in Advanced Aesthetic (cosmetic) Medicine through the University of Southern Florida School of Medicine A4M program. He is actively training in Anti-Ageing Regenerative Medicine and Stem Cell Medicine through the University of Southern Florida School of Medicine.

name: NeuroSpine Institute
bio: Mark joined NeuroSpine Institute in the spring of 2013, when he and Dr. Greg Phillips moved their practices to NSI.  Mark is a graduate of the University of West Florida where he received his undergraduate degree (Magna Cum Laude) a Bachelor of Science in Sports Science. He then obtained a Masters in Sports Medicine with emphasis in exercise physiology.  He went on to get a Master of Health Science degree from the Department of Physicians Assistant Studies.  He has worked as an Athletic trainer for many years and volunteers for many local sporting and high school events including the Olympic Trials. He is very excited to provide pellet therapy through BioTE and loves hearing the positive feedback from patients and how it’s changed their lives.  Mark is a veteran (Navy, Hospital Corpsmen), having served 10 years in the military including Operation Desert Shield and Storm. He also works on his cooking skills and brings delicious left-overs to work that make the rest of us drool.

name: New Directions Health and Wellness
bio:
When choosing a specialty in medical school, Scott Smith, MD, searched for one that allow him to develop lasting, deep relationships with his patients. This search led him to obstetrics and gynecology. He enjoys working in a specialty where many of his patients are young, healthy and excited. 
Dr. Smith is a board certified physician specializing in obstetrics and gynecology. He earned his medical degree from Texas Tech University School of Medicine in Lubbock. He remained at Texas Tech for his residency in the Department of Obstetrics & Gynecology, during which he became Administrative Chief Resident.

Outside of medicine, Dr. Smith enjoys fishing and being outdoors.

name: New Horizons Med Spa
bio:
A Diplomate of the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Dr. Villa has been in private practice as an Ob/Gyn since 1991. He has received numerous awards and appointments throughout his career, including a fellowship from the American Cancer Society, department chairmanships in several hospitals, and inclusion in Who's Who in Health and Services and the International Who's Who in Medicine. He has published articles on such topics as gynecologic cancer and ectopic pregnancy.
Dr. Villa earned his medical degree in 1987 from the University of South Florida College of Medicine, where he went on to complete his Obstetrics and Gynecology residency, becoming chief resident in his final year. Dedicated to mastering the latest cutting-edge procedures, he has continued to undergo specialized training in urogynecology, laparoscopic gynecologic surgery, laser treatments and other advanced techniques.
Dr. Villa's professional memberships include:
?	Fellow, American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists
?	Fellow, American College of Surgeons
?	Fellow, International College of Surgeons
?	American Medical Association
?	American College of Physician Executives
?	Arizona Medical Association
?	Maricopa County Medical Association
?	East Valley Ob/Gyn Society
?	Society of Laparoendoscopic Surgeons
?	American Institute of Ultrasound in Medicine
?	American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine
Hospital affiliations:
?	Chandler Regional Hospital

name: New Life Medical Group
bio:
Dr. Roy Schmidt’s extensive training and decades of experience speak for themselves. Dr. Schmidt focuses on improving the quality of life for his patients and giving them hope for a future without pain or the least amount of pain possible. Dr. Schmidt and his staff at New Life Medical Group are committed to providing patients with exceptional, individualized care in a comfortable, professional, and innovative environment. Dr. Schmidt is your complete long-term solution to pain, not simply masking it with short lived solutions.
He runs an elite practice that specializes in pain management, but realized long ago that he could offer more ground-breaking treatment options than any other pain clinic. His goal to offer state-of-the-art alternatives in one location led him to integrate the use of Hyperbaric oxygen therapy (HBOT) and regenerative therapies. HBOT is the only non-hormonal treatment approved by the FDA for biologically repairing and regenerating human tissue. He also specializes in regenerative therapies like prolotherapy, platelet rich plasma (PRP) and cell therapy/autologous stem cell therapy to help his patient’s bodies restart the healing process naturally.
Dr. Schmidt is a Board Certified anesthesiologist and completed training at the Cleveland Clinic and Baystate Medical Center, affiliated with Tufts University. He received his Doctor of Medicine from Loma Linda University in Loma Linda, Calif. He completed his Bachelor of Science in Biochemistry at Andrews University in Berrien Springs, Mich. His certifications include ASIIP accreditation in opiod administration and coding, suboxone detoxification accreditation, advanced training in implantable devices (spinal cord stimulation and intrathecal pumps), stem cell therapy and hyperbaric medicine.
He is a member of the American Society of Interventional Pain Physicians, the American Association of Orthopaedic Medicine (AAOM), the North American Neuromodulation Society, the American College of Hyperbaric Medicine and the International Hyperbaric Medicine Society.

name: New Life Medical Group
bio:
Alex Walker is a Board Certified Adult Nurse Practitioner with a passion for preventive medicine and improving quality of life. He believes in truly listening to each patient and individualizing each patient's care. 
After more than 10 years in cardiology and 4 years in primary care, he joined Dr. Schmidt and his team at New Life Medical Group because of their dedication to compassionate, professional healthcare that integrates innovative medical treatment options such as HBOT (hyperbaric oxygen treatment), PRP (platelet rich plasma), stem cell treatment, bioidentical hormones, and more. 

Alex and the staff at New Life Medical Group are committed to providing patients with exceptional, individualized care in a comfortable, professional, and innovative environment. 
Alex earned his Master's in Nursing at Vanderbilt University and his BSN at Union University

name: New Life Medicine
bio: Dr. Samara is a native of Poland and immigrated to United States with her parents at age 9. She currently lives in Yukon, Oklahoma. She received Bachelor degrees in Science and Business from Oklahoma City University in 1996. She studied medicine at University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center School of Medicine and graduated in 2004. She completed a 3 year Family Medicine residency at OU in 2008. She achieved this with the support of her husband and family, for which she is grateful every day. She started working for St. Anthony’s Medical Group since her residency completion.  She works as a family physician with a functional medicine approach and striving to help patients regain the best function of mind and body while focusing on preventive medicine.

name: New Life Surgical Associates
bio: Dr. Sharma has spent the majority of his career focusing on helping patients find their way to a new and more fulfilling self.   Being in the medical field for over 20 years Dr. Sharma found his passion in Bariatric Surgery and Health/Wellness of his patients.   As a skilled, experienced internationally renowned surgeon he has helped thousands of patients’ become healthier and happier!     He has carried that passion over into a Health and Wellness program at his practice.   As the Medical Director at New Life Wellness and Aesthetics his goal is to address the medical issues that may be preventing patients from being the healthiest, happiest, most fulfilled version of themselves.

name: New Medical Health Care
bio: Dr. Secrist received his undergraduate degree from Indiana University and his medical degree from A.T. Still University. Dr. Secrist has extensive experience in family practice, emergency medicine, and industrial medicine. He joined New Medical Health Care in 2005. He is board certified in family practice.

name: New Medical Health Care
bio: Dr. Simon completed his Doctor of Chiropractic degree from Cleveland Chiropractic College in Kansas City, Missouri and received his B.S. degree in nutrition from Park College. He practiced as a chiropractor in Sedalia, Missouri before obtaining his Doctor of Osteopathy degree from the University Of Health Sciences College Of Osteopathic Medicine. He was a family practice physician with the Via Christi Riverside Health System, where he served on the hospital board. He joined with Dr. Greg Lakin to open New Medical Health Care in October of 2003. He is board certified in Family Practice, is a certified Independent Medical Examiner, a Medical Review Officer and is a Fellow in the American Academy of Medical Acupuncture. Dr. Simon is also DOT National Certified Medical Examiner and enjoys providing complimentary medicine including homeopathy and prolotherapy and is a trained Reiki Master.

name: New Power Medicine
address: 1700 Dr. Martin Luther King Jr St.North, Suite C
bio:
Dr. Douglas Nelson is one of two Chief Executive Officers for The Lio Mission and New Power Medical Center. A Board Certified Physician for 15 years, with exceptional leadership qualities and a strategic vision focused on improving the future of healthcare; A physician dedicated to taking time with each valued patient to uncover the cause behind their stressors whether physical, emotional or spiritual in nature. 

An Iowa born native and Nova Southeastern University Alumnus, Dr. Nelson earned his Doctorate of Osteopathic Medicine after obtaining a Bachelor’s degree of Medicine and Surgery from the University of Science, Arts and Technology.
He is a member of the Hillsborough County Osteopathic Medical Society and 
Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine. 

When not at work, Dr. Nelson is an avid reader and participates as a member of the American Osteopathic Association to aid in establishing annual nonprofit clinics in Jamaica.

name: New U Medspa
bio:
Dr. Syed is an American Board Certified Doctor with extensive experience in both outpatient and inpatient medicine.  He has been trained at University of South Alabama, in Mobile Alabama and Good Samaritan Hospital in Phoenix, Arizona.

Dr. Syed has been practicing medicine for more than 10 years and has been practicing Anti-Aging and Hormone therapy for many years specializing in thyroid disorder and weight loss management.  Dr. Syed is proactive and outspoken in the balancing of hormones in bringing significant improvement to patients lives.

name: NeWellness
bio:
Dr. Orlando Suris is a diplomat and a fellow of the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. He is the lead team physician at New Wellness.
Dr. Suris earned his medical degree from the University of Texas Medical School at San Antonio and served as Chief Resident of Obstetrics and Gynecology at Medical Center Hospital. 
He’s passionate about hormones and an active member of the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine. He is currently pursuing a board certification and fellowship in functional medicine.
Dr. Suris is a member of the American Association of Gynecologic Laparoscopists, the Bexar County Medical Society and the Texas Medical Association. He is married and has three children. He is also an avid outdoorsman.

name: NeWellness
bio: Kate was born and raised in New York and has been living in San Antonio with her husband, dog, and cat for the last 3 years. She obtained her Bachelor’s degree in Psychology at Brown University where she was a 4-year varsity athlete. She went on to obtain her Bachelor of Science in Nursing and then her graduate degree as a Family Nurse Practitioner at Columbia University.

name: Next Health
bio:
Megan Retterath is a board certified Nurse Practitioner in Family Medicine. She received her Masters Degree and graduated with honors from the University of North Dakota. She is also a member of the Sigma Theta Tau Honor Society.
Prior to enrolling for her studies for an advanced degree, Megan spent 8 years in emergency/ trauma medicine, where she dedicated a majority of her time to teaching trauma education. Her ER experience illustrated the gap between medical and preventative care and how the mind/body connection was often ignored. These gaps encouraged Megan to pursue an advanced degree to develop a practice that integrates medicine and environmental interaction within the body to promote optimal health and disease prevention. In addition to her professional education, Megan received formal training and advanced clinical expertise at the Institute of Functional Medicine.

name: Next Health
bio:
Dr. Darshan Shah is a health and wellness specialist, well known surgeon, published author, tech entrepreneur, and founder and CEO of Beautologie and Next|Health.  As an expert on all body systems, he has performed over 10,000 surgical procedures, including trauma surgery, general surgery and plastic/reconstructive procedures. As a health and wellness specialist, he has advised thousands of patients on how to optimize their well-being and extend their lifespan, culminating in the creation of Next|Health, the "Apple Store" of Health and Wellness offering healthspan and lifespan extending technology and treatments in a beautiful, welcoming environment.

Dr. Darshan Shah started his training at an accelerated MD program at the age of 15 at the University of Missouri and earned his medical degree at the age of 21, becoming one of the youngest doctors in the United States.  After surgical training in central California, Dr. Shah then continued his training at the Mayo Clinic, one of the most prestigious medical institutes in the county. After earning his board certification, he went on to open medical/surgical centers throughout California, as well starting innovative tech companies, creating patented medical devices, as well as advising dozens of startups in medicine, finance, and tech.  Dr. Shah's belief in continual education and self-improvement has earned him alumni status at Harvard Business School, Singularity University and other prestigious institutions.

Dr. Darshan Shah is the oldest of three children. He is very close to his family and attributes his success to the values of hard work, passion for everything you do, and relentless tenacity taught to him by his parents.
He lives in Malibu, California with his wife, and two children and loves to travel, exercise, and has a passion to continuously educate himself and others.

name: Next Health Century City
bio:

name: North Atlanta OB GYN
bio: Dr. Godwin completed her undergraduate degree at Xavier University. She received her medical degree from Medical College of Georgia and completed her residency at Washington Hospital Center in Washington, D.C. Dr. Godwin is a native of Atlanta. She joined North Atlanta OBGYN after more than two years in practice at Emory University. Dr. Godwin is certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. Helping women understand their bodies as they move through various stages of life is her greatest reward. Dr. Godwin provides compassionate, individualized care based on evidence based medicine with each patient encounter.

name: North Atlanta OB GYN
bio: Dr. Rosenberg received his undergraduate and medical degrees from Emory University. He then completed his residency at the Emory University School of Medicine. Dr. Rosenberg is certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. He strives to address each patient's individual needs, encouraging women to take an active role in their health care decisions.

Dr. Rosenberg is certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. He strives to address each patient's individual needs, encouraging women to take an active role in their health care decisions.

name: North Austin Urology
bio: Dr. Mistry is a Texas native. He received his medical degree from Baylor College of Medicine in Houston, TX, where he also completed his residency in Adult and Pediatric Urology. Dr. Mistry played a critical role in the development of the DaVinci™ Robotic Prostatectomy program at Baylor. In addition to prostate cancer, Dr. Mistry specializes in the treatment of male infertility and managing the impact of low testosterone on men’s health.

name: North Florida Women's Care
bio:
Arthur Clements, M.D., Ph.D., is a native of Tallahassee, where his father also practiced obstetrics and gynecology for over 40 years.  Dr. Clements received his Bachelor of Science from the University of Florida and his Ph.D. from Florida State University in Nutritional Biochemistry.  He completed his medical training at the University of Monterrey and residency at Tulane University where he received the Dr. Lee and Dr. Bohm teaching award and served as the Administrative Chief Resident at Charity Hospital. 

Dr. Clements has served as Chairman of the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology at Tallahassee Memorial Hospital.  He is a Diplomat of the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Diplomat of the National Board of Medical Examiners and the District 12 Section 1 Chair of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists.  He is a member of the American Medical Association, Florida Medical Association, Florida Obstetrics and Gynecology Society, Capital Medical Society, Conrad Collins Society New Orleans, and the American Association of Gynecologic Laparoscopists.  Dr. Clements’ public service included being appointed by a member to the Florida Cabinet to serve as the state of Florida OB/GYN representative to the Neurological Injury Compensation Association, which administers funds to care for neurologically injured babies.  He also volunteers his professional time to serve as a board member of the Florida Obstetrics and Gynecologic Society, where he is the past President.  He serves on the faculty of Florida State University Medical School as the Education Director of Obstetrics and Gynecology.  He has been recognized as one of Americas Top Obstetricians and Gynecologists. 

Dr. Clements enjoys the outdoor activities North Florida has to offer.  He and his wife, Patricia Clements, Ph.D., have two outstanding daughters, Claire and Meredith.

name: North Florida Women's Physicians of Gainesville, LLC
bio:
Tracey Botha, M.D. has been with CWH since 2005. Born and raised in Johannesburg, South Africa, she attended Florida State University, medical school at University of Florida and completed her OB-GYN residency at Arnold Palmer Hospital in Orlando.
Dr. Botha specializes in high and low-risk obstetrics, well-woman care, minimally invasive laparoscopy, management of abnormal Pap smears and adolescent gynecology.

name: North Florida Women's Physicians of Gainesville, LLC
bio:
Dr. Delker was born and raised in the Panama Canal Zone, where her father was an engineer. She attended the University of Florida, University of Miami School of Medicine and completed her OB-GYN residency training at UF. She then served as faculty in the OB-GYN department of UF.
Dr. Delker specializes in obstetrics, performing minimally invasive surgery, managing abnormal Pap smears and providing gynecology services from adolescence to menopause.

name: North Florida Women's Physicians of Gainesville, LLC
North Fulton Internal Medicine Clinic
bio: Robert A. Young, PA-C, joined our practice in July of 2002. A native Atlantan, he attended the University of Georgia where he received his B.S.A. degree. In 1984, he graduated with honors from the physician assistants program at the Medical College of Georgia and is board certified by the National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants.

name: North Fulton Internal Medicine Clinic
bio:
Christine Trahan, PA-C, CDE, CDFS 

lived in California and Oregon before she discovered the friendliness of the south. She joined the practice in November 2003. She graduated summa cum laude from So. Oregon State College in 1983 with a degree in psychology. She is a board certified Physician Assistant, graduating with honors from the University of Oklahoma in 1996. She is a Certified Diabetes Educator and Certified Diabetic Foot Care Specialist. Before moving to Georgia, she was practicing in rural clinics in Oklahoma and Mississippi, specializing in Diabetes and wound care.

name: North Fulton Internal Medicine Clinic
bio:
Dr. Priddy, a native of Tennessee, completed his undergraduate work and medical degree at Emory University in Atlanta and his residency at the University of Rochester in New York. Certified by the American Board of Internal Medicine and a member of the American College of Physicians, he has been practicing medicine in the Atlanta community since 2001. He resides with his wife, Dr. Mary Anne Valdecanas of the Laureate Medical Group, and their Great Pyrenees, Uma. In his spare time he enjoys photography and Yoga.
We are excited to have him join our practice, bringing his vast experience and expertise to our patients, beginning December 1, 2016.

name: North Hills Family Medicine
bio:
Dr. Renato Geralde was born in the Philippines in 1969. In that same year he and his family immigrated to the United States. The Geralde family lived in many places including Jersey City, Chicago, and Houston. They eventually settled in the Southern California area in 1986. Dr. Geralde obtained his Bachelor’s Degree in Biological Sciences at the University of California at Irvine (UCI). In 1992 he was commissioned as a 2LT in the US Army reserves as he enrolled in medical school. He earned his Doctor of Osteopathy (D.O.) medical degree from the Chicago College of Osteopathic Medicine (CCOM) in 1996. Dr. Geralde then entered into active duty by going to Tripler Army Medical Center in Honolulu, Hawaii to complete his Family Medicine Internship and Residency.

Dr. Geralde’s accomplishments, awards, and accolades are many. He graduated on the Dean’s list from UCI and with Honors at CCOM. He has completed the Officer’s Basic Course, Combat Casualty Care Course, Brigade Surgeon’s Course, Aerospace Medicine Primary Course, Commanders Course, and the Survival-Escape-Rescue & Evade Course. He has served as the Academic Chief Resident of his residency training program. He is also board certified and a member of the American Board of Family Medicine, the Uniformed Services of Family Practice, and the American Medical Association.

In addition to serving in Hawaii, Dr. Geralde’s military career has included two assignments in Germany. He was first stationed in Schweinfurt Health Clinic where he served as the Medical Director. He then became the Commander of the Giebelstadt Health Clinic. Dr. Geralde left active duty in 2002 but served in the U.S. Air Force as a flight surgeon at Lackland AFB. He has received the Army Achievement Medal, Army Meritorious Service Medal, and the Air Force Achievement Medal.

Having served in the military, Dr. Geralde realizes the important influence that physical fitness has on a person’s mental and physical health. He strives to assist families to achieve and maintain optimal health, growth, and development. Dr. Geralde accomplishes this goal by taking an integrative approach that encompasses the patient, the patient’s illness, and the patient’s overall physical and mental health.

Dr. Geralde opened North Hills Family Medicine in Stone Oak in 2005, Westover Hills in 2011, and Schertz in 2014.

name: North Hills Family Medicine
bio:
Dr. Dean Earp was born and raised in El Paso, Texas. He attended the University of Texas at Austin where he received a Bachelor of Arts in Biology, graduated Summa Cum Laude and Phi Beta Kappa. He earned his Doctor of Medicine from the Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center in Lubbock, Texas and completed three-years of specialty training in Family Medicine at the Mayo Clinic in Scottsdale, Arizona. While at the Mayo Clinic, Dr. Earp spearheaded several humanitarian efforts including a medical mission to the Republic of Haiti and received the Mayo International Health Plan Scholarship. Prior to joining North Hills Family Medicine, Dr. Earp spent 5 years in outpatient practice in Phoenix, Arizona.

Dr. Earp is board certified in Family Medicine and has special interests in preventative health, sports medicine, pediatric care, and the treatment and prevention of headache syndromes. Dr. Earp also provided parenting advice on BabyFirstTV, a nationally broadcast cable television program.

Dr. Earp’s pride and joy is his family. He is married and has a young daughter, son and two cats. He is an avid Texas Longhorns fan and attends multiple games each year with his family.
 
In 2004, he completed his residency training at the Christus Santa Rosa Family Medicine Residency Program in downtown San Antonio. He has been practicing in the Stone Oak area since 2004 and joined North Hills Family Medicine in April of 2007. He integrates his knowledge of the musculoskeletal system, current medical information, and a dependable base of specialty consultants to promote healthy living and prevention of chronic disease.

Dr. Naron speaks Filipino and medical Spanish. He enjoys spending time with his family and friends, working out, and playing basketball and golf.

name: North Hills Family Medicine
bio:
Dr. Naron was born in the Philippines in 1976. His family immigrated to Houston, TX when he was 13 years old. He graduated summa cum laude from Alief Elsik High School in 1993. He obtained his premedical education at the University of Texas in Austin, where he graduated with High Honors with a Bachelor of Arts in Biology.

In 1997, he started medical school at the University of Texas Health Science Center in San Antonio, and has lived in San Antonio since. In medical school, Dr. Naron developed special interests in sports medicine, orthopedics, hypertension, diabetes, and preventive care.

He chose the specialty of Family Medicine with the goals of preventing disease and treating patients from childhood to adulthood. He enjoys developing lasting relationships with his patients and their families.

name: North Hills Family Medicine
bio:
Stephanie Benton is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner (FNP) with a strong background in cardiac-vascular diseases and disorders. As an APRN, Stephanie is licensed by the Texas State Board of Nursing to provide healthcare at an advanced level, seeing patients of all ages. Also board certified in Cardiac Vascular Nursing, Stephanie is passionate about partnering with her patients to help identify and reduce risk factors associated with the development of chronic conditions such as high blood pressure and diabetes.
Stephanie hails from Augusta, Georgia. After graduating from Augusta State University, she became a licensed Registered Nurse (RN) in 2001. As one of the top students in her class, Stephanie was chosen to visit ASU’s sister nursing school in Takarazuka, Japan, representing the university as a student ambassador. Upon her return, Stephanie moved to Atlanta, GA, and served as a charge nurse and clinical preceptor for the Coronary Intensive Care Unit in Atlanta’s only Magnet Award Hospital.
In 2003, Stephanie and her husband relocated to San Antonio. Before joining North Hills Family Medicine, she worked in a large cardiology group, serving as a physician extender and clinical research coordinator. Never one to stop learning, Stephanie earned both her Bachelor and Master of Science degrees in Nursing from Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center, graduating with highest honors, summa cum laude. It was during these academic pursuits that Stephanie discovered a passion for delivering holistic, comprehensive healthcare…so she followed her heart, which led her to become a Family Nurse Practitioner at North Hills Family Medicine.

name: North Hills Internal and Integrative Medicine
bio:
Dr. Henry J. Van Pala, Yale University trained and board certified Internal Medicine physician and board certified Gastroenterologist, serves as the Medical Director for North Hills Internal & Integrative Medicine and also the Medical Director for the Assure Wellness Group. 

Prior to attending medical school, Dr. Van Pala earned a degree in Pharmacy from St. John’s University School of Pharmacy in New York, New York in 1974. Dr. Van Pala practiced as a registered Pharmacist for two years, specializing in compounding pharmacy. In 1980, Dr. Van Pala graduated from Michigan State College of Human Medicine and proceeded to train for five years in the Yale University School of Medicine residency and fellowship program from 1980 to 1985. Dr. Van Pala first became licensed to practice medicine in 1983 and is board certified in Internal Medicine and Gastroenterology. Dr. Van Pala perfected his desire to achieve medical excellence by passing the challenging Internal Medicine Maintenance of Certification Exam in 2010 and the rigorous Full Certification Exam in Gastroenterology in 2013, a remarkable feat considering Dr. Van Pala first became licensed to practice medicine over thirty years ago. Over the years, Dr. Van Pala has maintained his expertise by completing 2,500 hours in Category 1 Continuing Medical Education. 

From 2012 to 2013, Dr. Van Pala spent an additional year in advanced Internal Medicine and Gastroenterology training at Georgia Regents University, formerly known as Medical College of Georgia, in Augusta, Georgia, which afforded him the opportunity to interact with research and medicine at a level only a leading academic institution can provide. At Georgia Regents University, Dr. Van Pala trained to master the most modern medical technologies and treatment systems and received additional, comprehensive training in the fields of gastroenterology, cardiology, pulmonology, infectious disease, endocrinology, nephrology, rheumatology, general internal medicine, critical care medicine, and geriatrics. Dr. Van Pala recently completed a difficult restorative medicine course and became a fellow-candidate among an elite group of physicians in a program entitled A4M, the American Academy of Anti-Aging and Regenerative Medicine. 

Dr. Van Pala has also become an expert in men and women’s wellness, hormonal therapy, nutrition balance assistance, and, most notably, creative, integrative, and highly personal weight loss solutions. Dr. Van Pala’s philosophy is that in order to understand and treat the patient as a whole, he must not only innately understand the complexities of modern medicine, but also must address deficiencies in the individual and diagnose and correct the underlying problem. Dr. Van Pala is uniquely qualified to diagnose and care for the complete patient in an integrative manner, utilizing modern treatments to help patients lose weight and become hormonally balanced, helping them restore their stamina and sexual vitality, and enabling them to live more rewarding and satisfying lives. Because of his academic, internal medicine, and gastroenterology training and specialization, as well as his passion for proving a holistic treatment approach for each of his patients that few doctors possess, combined with his years of intense clinical and real-life experience, Dr. Van Pala is well qualified to treat today’s most complicated medical problems in an integrative manner, his patients’ overall health and wellness his primary focus.

Dr. Van Pala is licensed to practice medicine in North Carolina, South Carolina, Georgia, and Virginia.

name: North Hills Internal and Integrative Medicine
North Hills Internal and Integrative Medicine
bio:
Jessica Allyn, MSN, APRN, AGNP-C
	I am a graduate of Duke University's Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner program.  I completed my degree in 2016 graduating with a 4.0 GPA. I have over 10 years of nursing experience in the inpatient setting.  A majority of my nursing career was spent in a level 1 surgical/trauma ICU where I cared for complex patients with multiple comorbidities. I decided to become a Nurse Practitioner so that I could focus on a more proactive and holistic approach to health.  I am committed to providing excellent evidence-based, comprehensive and individualized care to my patients. I feel privileged and grateful for the opportunity to serve my patients as their primary care provider.  
	On a personal note, I grew up in Saratoga, NY and moved to NC in 2011.  On my days off I enjoy spending time with my husband, son and 2 dogs.  I love exploring everything the area has to offer.

name: North Scottsdale Laser and Skin Care
bio:
Dr. Riyana Chinoy, BSc (Kinesiology), NMD is a graduate of the prestigious Simon Fraser University, in Burnaby, British Columbia. Her undergraduate Bachelor of Science degree is in Kinesiology with a focus on Exercise, Human Nutrition and Metabolism. She later went on to receive her Doctorate in Naturopathic Medicine from Southwest College in Tempe, Arizona. Dr. Chinoy has completed her Level 1 (Certificate Course) and Level 2 (Diploma Course) training in Aesthetic Medicine 10+ years ago, in addition to Mesotherapy and other advanced level courses in Aesthetic Medicine, such as PDO thread-lifts (Novathreads), PRP, vampire facelifts and much more. She specializes in Anti-Aging, Women’s Medicine, Acupuncture, Aesthetic Medicine, Botanical Medicine and Holistic Nutrition. Dr. Chinoy also serves on the Board of Directors and as a Nutritional & Nutraceutical Formulation Advisor of G30 Challenge Inc. — A Vancouver, BC based Nutraceutical and Fitness Company. She completed a residency in Internal Medicine in Phoenix, Arizona.
Dr. Chinoy has attended and continues to attend many conferences and seminars regularly throughout the year to further her knowledge in the field of Nutrition, Anti-aging, Bio-Identical Hormones Replacement Therapy (BHRT), Aesthetics, Women’s Medicine and several other areas of medicine.
Her passion is helping others to achieve optimal health and wellness using the least invasive and most natural methods. Her favorite naturopathic philosophy is to educate, inspire rationale, hope and encourage self-responsibility for health (Doctor as Teacher). In her spare time, she reads, draws, paints, hikes, and participates in meditation and yoga for a balanced mind-body-soul.
Dr. Chinoy is affiliated with the American Association of Naturopathic Physicians (AANP), Arizona Naturopathic Medical Association (AzNMA), State of Arizona Naturopathic Physicians Medical Board (AZND), Texas Association of Naturopathic Doctors (TXAND), American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine (A4M), American Academy of Aesthetic Medicine (AAAM), Endocrine Association of Naturopathic Physicians (EndoANP) and the Oncology Association of Naturopathic physicians (OncANP ).

name: North Suburban Physicians Group
bio:
Dr. Elena completed a Residency in Physical Medicine & Rehabilitation and Internal Medicine at Loyola University Medical Center and The University of Illinois at Chicago.  There, she focused on acute and chronic pain syndromes, headaches, musculo-skeletal and neurologic pain syndromes.
Dr. Elena has extensive knowledge and experience in General Medicine, Cardiology, Pulmonology, and Endocrinology. Dr. Elena is a member of numerous professional societies, including The Association of Academic Physiatrists and The Physiatrist Association of Spine Sports and Occupational Rehabilitation.

name: North Texas OB/GYN Associates
bio:
Thomas S. Fliedner, M.D. is a Board Certified Obstetrician and Gynecologist who specializes in comprehensive wellness and healthcare for women.  He has been serving the Flower Mound and Lewisville communities since 2000.  He obtained his medical degree in New Jersey and completed his residency at University of Texas Southwestern/Parkland Hospital in Dallas.  Parkland's obstetrics and gynecology residency program is considered one of the finest training programs in the United States, and the volume of deliveries performed at the hospital routinely ranks among the highest in the nation.
His practice focuses on high and low risk pregnancies, pregnancy planning, contraception, abnormal uterine bleeding, infections, pelvic pain and urinary control concerns.  Dr. Fliedner uses the latest technology, and is proficient in the da Vinci robot system.  The da Vinci Surgical System is a sophisticated robotic platform designed to expand a surgeon's capabilities and offers a state-of-the-art minimally invasive option for major surgery.

Dr. Fliedner strives for a partnership with his patients, one in which they are a part of the decision-making process in their healthcare needs.
In his spare time, he enjoys spending time with his three children, family and friends.  His hobbies include politics, reading, and exercise.
I enjoy the relationship I have with each patient. Together we find the best treatment options, whether this is a healthy baby during a high-risk pregnancy, finding the right birth control method, resolving bladder problems, or treating heavy bleeding in the least invasive way.  My goal is your best health.  I would like to help you.

Medical Education
College: East Carolina University, Greenville, NC
Medical: New Jersey Medical School, Newark, NJ
Residency: Parkland Memorial Hospital, Dallas, TX

Certification
Certified:  American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology: originally certified in 1998 and recertified continuously to present.

name: North Texas OB/GYN Associates
bio:
Cheryl Smitherman was born and raised in Fort Worth Texas where she resides with her husband of 29 years and her three children. She obtained a Bachelor of Arts Degree in English from Texas Woman’s University in 1989 and was a public-school educator for 7 years. She achieved a Bachelor of Science in Nursing Degree from Texas Woman’s University in 1998 and has 17 years of experience as a Labor & Delivery Nurse, Women’s Services Educator, and Labor & Delivery Manager.  
She obtained her Doctor of Nursing Practice Degree from Baylor University and was licensed as a Certified Nurse-Midwife by the Texas Board of Nursing in 2013. She became an Associate Professor in the undergraduate program at Baylor University’s Louise Herrington School of Nursing and opened a prenatal clinic in Arlington for underprivileged women where she provided prenatal care. She came to Denton County in 2014 where she has provided midwifery and women’s health care for the past three years.
Cheryl comes to North Texas Obstetrics & Gynecology Associates with a wealth of experience and a passion for women’s health.  As an educator and Certified Nurse-Midwife, she believes in a collaborative partnership with her patients and their families. Her mission is to support women and their families through education and informed decision-making.  Her belief is that all women deserve quality health care across the lifespan, and her mission is to provide patient-supported health care in a compassionate and healing environment.

name: Northeast Georgia Gynecology, LLC
bio: Dr. Coleman is a Georgia Licensed Physician trained in Obstetrics and Gynecology. Born and raised in Gainesville, Georgia, she attended North Hall High School and was Valedictorian of the class of 1986. She did her pre-med studies at North Georgia College (now known as University of North Georgia). She completed medical school at Medical College of Georgia (now known as Augusta University). Dr. Coleman completed her Internship at Community Hospital in Roanoke, Virginia in association with University of Virginia.  She completed her residency in OB-Gyn at Humility of Mary Medical Center in Youngstown, Ohio.

name: Northern California Wellness, Inc.
bio:
Dr. Dunbar began her healthcare journey at Pacific Union College where she received a Bachelor of Science degree as well as a certification in Age Management. She went on to attend Loma Linda University School of Medicine where she received her MD degree in 1998. She is double board certified in Preventive Medicine and Public health.  

Her belief that many diseases could be prevented by leading a healthy lifestyle led her to pursue a residency in Preventive Medicine. She completed her residency while also completing a Masters of Public Health (MPH) in nutrition.
After finishing residency, Dr. Dunbar attended continuing medical education programs focused on lifestyle medicine and bioidentical hormone therapies (BHRT). She completed the course requirements and received certification in Age Management Medicine from Cenegenics Medical Institute. 

Dr. Dunbar has been in private practice in the greater Sacramento area since 2008. She says the most rewarding part of her job is seeing the dramatic results that many of her patients experience through a combination of lifestyle changes, hormone optimization, and aesthetic treatments.

Her practice focuses on helping men and women of all ages achieve their health goals through nutrition, fitness, and hormone optimization. In addition, she provides a variety of aesthetic treatments that complement the health and wellness goals of her patients. Treatment programs are individualized for each patient. Her goal is to have each patient look and feel their best.

Doctor Cheree Dunbar MD, and Team of Medical Professionals at Northern California Wellness of El Dorado Hills Look Forward to Serving You 4 Days a Week.

name: Northern Colorado Laser & Skin
bio: Regina Miles received her undergraduate degree as well as her Masters of science in nursing from the University of Northern Colorado. She has worked in a variety of settings including the emergency room, wound care, burn care, intensive care and hyperbaric medicine. She is board certified as a family nurse practitioner through the ANCC.  She loves Colorado and enjoys hiking, skiing, snowshoeing, fishing, camping and baseball. Regina believes in sitting down and  listening to her patients. She strives  to help patients in a holistic manner and is very passionate about improving their quality of life.

name: NuYou Med Clinic
bio:
We started this clinic because my patients were fatigued with the lack of energy.  They had loss of memory and difficulty thinking at times.  They displayed irritability, anxiety, and depression-like symptoms.  They were having decreased loss of muscle strength with joint pain.  Along with these symptoms, they lacked sexual desire and performance.  I knew their hormones were to blame but the medicines offered by the conventional medical community had potential side effects or even caused heart attacks, stroke, DVT’s and cancer and I didn’t really see them as effective.
I searched for a long time to find the right solution that would be safe for my patients, be effective and reverse all the symptoms they were experiencing.  I found it in Bioidentical Hormone Therapy or BHRT for short.  These hormones, along with some supplements, allowed my patients to regain energy and muscle strength while feeling younger and happier.  They had increased mental clarity and ability to lose weight again.  It restored or increased their sex drive and performance while decreasing their joint and muscle pain.  It’s been a great experience and we are just starting out.  I can not wait to see what else happens.
Call to speak to a representative and see if Balanced Hormone therapy is Right for you.

name: NW Hormone Balance Corp
bio:
Brittany Moyer received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Sacramento State University in 1996 and her Master in Science as a Family Nurse Practitioner from WSU Vancouver in 2007. Her medical experience has been mostly in the emergency department and urgent care.
Brittany feels fortunate to have had a 10-year military career in which she traveled the world gaining an amazing appreciation for many cultures and family dynamics. Those experiences have made an impact on her ability to connect with and treat a variety of people.
In addition to her work, Brittany enjoys being outdoors with her family, doing anything that makes them laugh. She believes in random acts of kindness and not sweating the small stuff.

name: Oak Hills Med Spa
bio:
One of the most important decisions you will ever make for your family and their well-being is who you choose to care for their health on a day-to-day basis. Though trauma or emergencies demand specialized equipment and lightning fast reactions, a family practitioner must be ready to handle the medical concerns of your family every day. 

Tyler’s own Hope Short, MD, specializes in family medicine in protecting what’s most important to you. She has been voted Bscene's Magazine Best of 2012 for Tyler, and has received their awards for five years running. 

Dr. Short is a native of Tyler, graduating from Robert E. Lee High School before attending Texas Christian University for her bachelor’s and UT Tyler for her master’s degree. She received her medical degree from the University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio in 1996. 

Dr. Short then completed her residency in family practice at John Peter Smith Hospital in Ft. Worth. Dr. Short has been practicing in Tyler for 12 years and has a private practice where she handles everything from complete physicals to childcare, colposcopies, pap smears and minor skin procedures. She is a member of the Texas and American Medical Associations, the Smith County Medical Society, and the American Academy of Family Physicians. 

Active in the community, Dr. Short is a member of Marvin United Methodist Church and has been involved with the Cattle Barons’ Gala, the Junior League of Tyler, the Symphony League and the Smith County Republican Party. Dr. Short serves on the ETMC Cancer Committee, and enjoys tennis, running, snow skiing and scuba diving.

name: Oak Tree Wellness
bio:
Dr. Thomas F. Drost, MD, ND, FACS first realized his calling as a physician at the age of eleven before entering junior high. He was very taken by the lives and practices of several family physicians in the small town where he grew up in southern Nevada and was encouraged by his parents to pursue the medical profession. He attended the University of Wyoming on a varsity football scholarship, earning a BS in Zoology/Physiology (premed). He then attended and graduated from the University of Nevada, School of Medicine in 1985 and completed a general surgery residency and trauma fellowship at the University of South Florida in 1991.
Dr. Tom served four years as a surgeon for the U. S. Army as a Major where he served both abroad and, in the U.S., During this time he experienced the ins and outs of a public health system, based upon the model of disease prevention used to maintain the health of the troops and their families. He then entered the world of a private surgical practice in Las Vegas, Nevada. It took only four short and painful years for him to come to the conclusion that medicine, and the way it was being delivered, was not the same as it was during his boyhood years. He feels the overall health of our society is deteriorating into chronic illness, patient and physician satisfaction are at an all-time low, and many previously successful therapies for many illnesses are no longer working or effective. Dr. Tom decided he would find a better way to deliver health care or quit!
Dr. Tom left a successful surgical practice in Las Vegas to enroll at Bastyr University in Kenmore, Washington, one of five accredited naturopathic universities in North America. While practicing general surgery with a Seattle group, he earned a post graduate degree in Naturopathic Medicine. Dr. Tom Drost is currently a licensed physician and board-certified surgeon in the state of Illinois practicing environmental medicine, men’s health, IV therapies and specializing in chronic conditions. His goal is to optimize and bring clients' health back into focus and helping them to live and experience a better quality of life. His practice of environmental medicine includes cleansing/detoxification, allergy elimination, and treating toxic exposures. He completed additional training in environmental medicine under one of the nation's leading experts, Dr. Walter Crinnion. Dr. Tom combines the principles of conventional medicine with naturopathic principles, using such modalities as botanical medicine, IV nutrition and chelation, nutritional supplementation and lifestyle modification. Dr. Tom has expanded his interest in men’s health by implementing a comprehensive men’s health program. Dr. Tom is a respected physician in his community and maintains open and cooperative relationships with other physicians and health professionals of all disciplines.
In his spare time, he enjoys travel, sports, exercise, spending time with his daughter and his dogs, working in the garden, and the hobby of collecting Lionel toy trains.

name: OB GYN Partners, St. Francis
bio:
Dr. Sylvester McRae is an experienced Gynecologist who takes pride in providing his patients a level of care that is second to none. He has always striven to make sure that the options available to patients in other areas, are available to Columbus.

In addition to Obstetrics, Dr. McRae has been a pioneer in Minimally Invasive Surgery including Laparoscopic as well as Robotic Surgery. He is the leading physician in Georgia and the region with Single Site Robotics, which allows for fibroids  and other  procedures to be done through a one inch incision through the navel.

Bioidentical hormone replacement provides the opportunity for physicians to provide hormonal replacement in a manner that is more natural than any preparation currently available. Dr. McRae and his staff are proud to be able to provide this service to patients in Columbus, Georgia and the surrounding areas.

name: OB-GYN Medical Office-Dr. Jesus M. Seda
OB/GYN Associates of Saint Augustine
bio:
Dr. Karen Toppi is a partner with OB/GYN Associates of St Augustine. Her office is in Palm Coast. She has been practicing gynecology only since 2004. She is well known for her individual based compassionate care for her patients and was named Top Doc of Volusia/Flagler Counties by the News Journal. 
She has been a proponent of HRT and has been prescribing Bio identical HRT since the late 1990’s. She now is strictly office based and is devoting more time to menopause and Bio identical HRT. After much research, she has chosen BioTE as her sub dermal pellets of choice due to their purity and proven results with over 65,000 patients. She looks forward to helping you achieve optimum health and wellness.

Academic Background:
    B.S., Indiana State University
    M.D., University of Chicago Medical School
    Residency, Medical College of Virginia/Virginia Commonwealth University
    Fellowship, Emory University of Atlanta Georgia in Advanced Pelvic Surgery
When not caring for her patients Dr. Toppi enjoys being on the water with her paddleboard or kayak and has recently started a nonprofit organization, Hope to Help Foundation to integrate holistic modalities to those with cancer.

name: OB/GYN North Dallas
bio:
Originally from Idaho, Steven R. MacDonald, MD graduated from the University of Idaho with a B.A. in philosophy and zoology. He received his medical degree in 1993 from Northwestern University Medical School in Chicago. Dr. MacDonald completed his residency training in obstetrics and gynecology at McGaw Medical Center of Northwestern University. 
Dr. MacDonald joined OB/GYN North Dallas in 1999 after working for the Public Health Service on an Indian reservation in Montana.
Dr. MacDonald specializes in routine and high-risk obstetrical care and gynecological care. He is board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a Fellow of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists. He serves on the Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital Plano committees, has been a past chair of several committees, and is current chair of the Women’s and Infants’ Committee.
Dr. MacDonald resides in Dallas and enjoys spending time with his wife and three daughters.

name: OB/GYN North Dallas
bio: Angela Watson, MD, will be joining our practice in January 2017. Dr. Watson graduated from the University of Texas Medical Branch in Galveston and completed her residency training in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Texas Southwestern Medical Center in 2008. She has been in private practice in Arlington for the past eight years. Dr. Watson is Board Certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is skilled in all aspects of obstetrics and gynecology, including minimally invasive laparoscopic and robotic procedures. She recently relocated to Frisco with her husband and two children.

name: OB/GYN North Dallas
bio:
Originally from Oklahoma, John Paul Roberts, MD graduated from Stanford University with a B.A. in human biology. In 1991, he received his medical degree from the University of Oklahoma College of Medicine. Following medical school, he completed his residency training in obstetrics and gynecology McGaw Medical Center at Northwestern University in Chicago.
Dr. Roberts began practicing in the Dallas area in 1995. He specializes in routine and high-risk obstetrical care and patient-centered gynecological care. Dr. Roberts is board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. He is a Fellow of the American Congress of Obstetricians and Gynecologists and a member of the American Medical Association, the Texas Medical Association, the Texas Association of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, and the Dallas County Medical Society. He is currently on the board of directors of Genesis Physicians Group in Dallas. He previously served as chairman of the Obstetrics and Gynecology Department at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital Plano.
You can visit Dr. Roberts’ website at www.jprobertsobgyn.com.

name: OB/GYN North Dallas
bio:
Dr. Darrell Robins MD – OB/GYN North Dallas 

A Dallas, Texas native, Dr. Robins graduated from the University of Texas Austin and received his medical degree from the University of Texas Medical Branch in 1988. He completed his residency training in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School / Parkland Hospital.
Dr. Robins began practicing in the Dallas area in 1992. He is board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology. His areas of interest are multiple pregnancies, laparoscopic surgery, pelvic reconstruction, and endometrial ablation. Dr. Robins performs da Vinci® single-site robotic surgery for hysterectomy and other gynecological procedures.
Dr. Robins has been married for over 25 years and has two daughters and a grandson. He enjoys golf and art collecting.

name: OB/GYN North Dallas
bio:
A Frisco, Texas native and Texas A&M University graduate, Dr. Burt received his medical degree from the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School in 1998. He completed his residency training in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School / Parkland Hospital.
Dr. Burt joined OB/GYN North Dallas in 2002. Board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Dr. Burt maintains his appointment as clinical professor of obstetrics and gynecology at UT Southwestern. He serves on numerous hospital committees, including the Credentials, Surgical Services, and Peer Review committees. His areas of interest include complicated, high-risk pregnancies and operative gynecology including single-site da Vinci robotic surgery. He is the current chairman of the Obstetrics and Gynecology Department at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital Plano.
Dr. Burt is an avid fly fisherman and outdoorsman. He enjoys spending his time with his wife and two children. He is also fluent in Spanish.
You can visit Dr. Burt's website at www.randalljburtmd.com.

name: OB/GYN North Dallas
bio:
Born in Christiansted, St. Croix, U.S. Virgin Islands and raised in Texas, Dr. Taylor received her degree in biology at Texas A&M University. After obtaining her medical degree from the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School in 2005, Dr. Taylor completed her residency training in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Texas Southwestern Medical School / Parkland Hospital. Dr. Taylor is board certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a trained da Vinci robotic surgeon. 
Dr. Taylor joined OB/GYN North Dallas in 2009. She resides in Frisco, Texas with her husband and two children. Her interests include running, biking, and other outdoor activities.

name: OB/GYN of Central Florida
bio: Dr. Orrego Graduated from Universidad de Caldas in Colombia. He did Internal Medicine Residency in New York City at Metropolitan Hospital (a NY Medical College affiliated hospital). He went on to graduate from Mt. Sinai School of Medicine ObGyn program in Jersey City Medical Center. Since 2002 Dr. Orrego provides care to our community at Orrego Center for Women’s Health. Dr. Orrego is Board Certified, is a Fellow of The American Congress of Obstetrics and Gynecology. His main interest is in Minimally Invasive Gyn surgery with the DaVinci system.Dr. Orrego is married and in his spare time he enjoys his family, playing soccer, tennis and fishing.

name: OB/GYN of Central Florida
bio: Carolyn is a Board-Certified Physician Assistant who has worked closely with Dr. Orrego for the past 13 years to provide quality, comprehensive healthcare to women from Adolescence to Menopause. She received her Bachelor’s degree from Capital University in Columbus, Ohio, graduating Magna Cum Laude. Carolyn received her Master’s in Physician-Assistant studies from the University of Florida in 2002. She has 15 years of experience with special focus in women’s healthcare and Adolescent Medicine. Previously, she worked in Family Practice for two years before starting womens health. Carolyn is married and has two beautiful children.
