name: OB/GYN of SWLA
bio:
Dr. Gisele McKinney is a native of Chicago, Illinois who relocated to the warmth and beauty of Cajun Country and has been in Southwest Louisiana for 10 years.  A graduate of Spelman College in Atlanta, Georgia, she obtained her Bachelors of Science in Chemistry.  Dr. McKinney, worked in synthetic fuels research for 2 years prior to going to medical school where she received her Medical Degree from the University of Illinois, at Chicago. A practicing Obstetrician and Gynecologist for 14 years, performing all aspects of women’s health, she became interested and specializing in hormonal therapy about 2 years ago.  After research and seminars, Dr. McKinney who also uses bio-identical hormones, began to see the ultimate benefits in a balanced hormonal status.

Let BioTE open new possibilities for you as it has for many others.

name: OBGYN Associates of Laredo, P.A.
bio: Dr. Dagoberto Gonzalez is from Laredo, Texas.  He attended Texas A&M University and graduated with a degree in Biomedical Science.  He then continued to further his education at the Texas A&M Health Science Center where he received his Medical Doctor degree.   He continued his education by joining the United States Air Force and attending a residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology in San Antonio, Texas.  After completing the residency, he continued as an associate professor for the military medical school and as an attending physician teaching residents in the field of obstetrics and gynecology.  After eight years, he separated as a Major in the Air Force and moved his family to Laredo, Texas where he currently resides.  He is in private practice in Laredo.

name: Obie L. Stalcup, M.D. Prevention for Life
OC Medical Tustin
bio:
Anti-aging, functional, and regenerative medicine, general medicine, aesthetics
Practicing medicine since 1992
Dr. Arturo Portales trained at the Ohio University College of Osteopathic Medicine graduating in 1989. After residency, he worked in emergency medicine for 15 years. He became board certified in emergency medicine in 1997. Despite working in a variety of emergency department settings, he did not find the work fulfilling because he felt that there had to be more than a “band aid” approach to helping people fight disease. What Dr. Portales found in practice was that conventional medicine is disease oriented but fails to address the underlying issues of the individual. He also found that a patient’s lifestyle and nutrition were seldom if ever addressed. In the acute care setting, this approach saves lives. However, in the chronic care setting, this approach fails miserably. Chronic disease represents 78% of the total healthcare expenditures in the U.S and despite the billions spent, people are not any healthier.
Dr. Portales has since sought out other methods to deliver quality healthcare to patients where the root causes are addressed. What he learned through many hours of study is that diseases are multi-factorial and healthcare must be approached with an open mind. This means integrating other methods of healthcare delivery with an ultimate goal of optimizing a patient’s health. He found that each patient represents a unique set of circumstances and this necessitates an individualized approach to each and every patient.
Dr. Portales’ approach involves complete hormonal evaluations including testosterone, estrogen, and progesterone. He also assesses thyroid function and adrenal function. Other issues assessed include nutritional status, overall toxic load, emotional stressors, and gut function.
Dr. Portales is Board Certified by the American Academy of Anti-aging Medicine in Anti-Aging, Regenerative, and Functional Medicine. He completed his Fellowship training in Anti-aging, Regenerative, and Functional Medicine in 2011 (FAARM). He continues to pursue a Masters in Metabolic and Nutritional Medicine at the University Of South Florida College Of Medicine.
Last  year, Dr. Arturo Portales also won the www.vitals.com Patient’s Choice Award and the Compassionate Doctor Recognition award .

name: OC Sports and Wellness
bio:
Dr. Sunshine is a Bay Area native and attended college at Stanford University. He is a graduate of the Keck School of Medicine at the University of Southern California and completed his residency in Family Medicine and fellowship in Sport Medicine at Kaiser Permanente Fontana Medical Center. Since graduating in 1999, Dr. Sunshine has been practicing both Family Medicine and Sports Medicine and is board certified in both specialties.
Like many other physicians, Dr. Sunshine went into medicine to help others. His father is a physician and still loves going into work everyday. His father inspired him to pursue a similar career path and work ethic. During the past 15 years, Dr. Sunshine has established a fulfilling career cultivating personal relationships with patients and their families.
About My Medical Practice
As a physician, he makes it a point to connect with his patients and heartily encourage them to live a healthier life. Not only does he appreciate solving clinical problems but finds it rewarding to help patients create lifestyle changes that improve their well-being. Many of his patients are able to achieve health goals simply through regular exercise and sensible, consistent nutrition.
Dr. Sunshine strives to be a resource and an inspiration to my patients. He lives a lifestyle that he preaches daily to his patients. Hippocrates was quoted as saying, “Let food be thy medicine and medicine thy food.” Dr. Sunshine believes we can improve our health simply by living a healthier lifestyle through proper nutrition and regular exercise.
Our health is our number one asset. He emphasizes this point to his patients and helps them understand that prevention of illness is more important, cost-effective and rewarding than treating disease. He believes that the four pillars of good health are proper sleep, stress reduction, daily exercise and proper nutrition.
Dr. Sunshine cares for a wide variety of athletes and weekend warriors in his practice. He has served for years as the team physician at Concordia University where he has also taught General Medicine courses to athletic training students. He has focused his work on regenerative medicine using ultrasound guidance to perform platelet rich plasma and prolotherapy injections with very high success rates in healing troubling sports injuries.
He is also been a volunteer faculty member at the Keck School of Medicine at the University of Southern California since 2005 where he has the opportunity to mentor 3rd and 4th year medical students interested in family and sports medicine.

name: Old Town Medical
bio:
DR. JOE ETTER, D.O. is a board certified internal medicine physician.  Dr. Etter received his undergraduate degree in Kinesiology at Dallas Baptist University.  He attended medical school at the University of North Texas in Ft. Worth and finished his residency in Internal Medicine at Plaza Medical Center in Ft. Worth, Texas, where he served as chief resident in 2006.  Dr. Etter started Burleson Old Town Medical Center in August of 2006.  
Specializing in chronic disease has been a mainstay in Dr. Etter's practice. In addition to conventional approaches to diagnosis and treatment, he routinely incorporates functional and homeopathic remedies as the patient desires. Dr. Etter is committed to wellness and prevention, and strongly encourages his patients to address any nutritional deficiencies and exercise.  
Dr. Etter married his high school sweetheart, Shelby, in 1995. They have two girls, Ella and Hattie.  In addition to spending time with their children, Dr. Etter and Shelby enjoy traveling, experiencing new things, and are very active in their home church.

name: Old Town Medical
bio:
AUSTIN BURNETT is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner. Austin graduated with his BSN in 2007 from Abilene Christian University and has been practicing in the Burleson area since he graduated with his Master's from Hardin Simmons University in 2010. Prior to obtaining his advanced degree, he worked as a Registered Nurse in the ER at Hendrick Health System in Abeline, TX.
Thoughtfully caring for patients medical needs from diabetes, hypertension, minor injuries, and upper respiratory infections is something Austin is very passionate about. He has also been trained to help balance patient's hormones using BioTe hormone replacement therapy.
Austin has been married to his wife Brittney since Feburary 2016 and they are very active in their church home. Austin enjoys hunting, cycling, and working outdoors during his time off.

name: Old Town Medical
bio:
STEPHANIE "PAIGE" BRISCOE NORRIS, RN, MSN, FNP-C has been with Burleson Old Town Medicine since August of 2013.  She has been a Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner since 2009, and has worked in Family Practice and Urgent Care in this role.  
Prior to obtaining her advanced degree, a Masters of Science in Family Nurse Practitioner Studies from Baylor University, she worked as a Registered Nurse since 2003.  Her background in Nursing includes Dialysis, Hospice, and Urgent Care.  She holds a Bachelor of Science in Biology from Tarleton State University in 2000, and an Associates of Science in Nursing from Southwestern Adventist University in 2003.
She has served on medical missions with trips to the Dominican Republic, Honduras, Ethiopia, Malawi, and Romania.  She and husband, Chris, live in Cleburne with their son, Evan.  They attend StoneWater Church in Cleburne, and enjoy spending time with family.

name: Olga Joukovski, MD, PA
bio:
Dr. Olga Joukovski is Board Certified in Internal Medicine.
She received her medical education at St. Petersburg State Medical University, Russia, graduating in 1991. She completed her Internal Medicine Residency at Lincoln Medical and Mental Health Center / New York Medical College, USA, graduating in 1997.
 
Her philosophy is to treat, manage, and educate patients on their medical conditions. Her emphasis is on healthy habits, preventive measures and educating the patient to enable them make informed decisions about their healthcare.
 
As an Internal Medicine practitioner, she provides a full range of services to her patients. She helps patients transition to a healthy lifestyle while equipping the patient with the necessary information to maintain their new lifestyle. She uses her education and training to focus on treating, teaching, and managing patients' chronic conditions.

name: Olga Pereira @ Women's Wellness
bio: Dr. Pereira completed her doctor in medicine degree in 2008 from Ponce School of Medicine. In 2013, she graduated from her OB Gyn residency in San Juan City Hospital. Dr. Pereira did a year as chief resident in the same institution and continues as faculty at San Juan City Hospital. After graduation, she became part of a well-known group practice, San Juan Medical Associates. Since then, her practice has been diverse with obstetrics and gynecologic patients, as well as an increase in the number of patients requesting hormonal replacement therapy, anti-aging alternatives and esthetics treatment.

name: Olympus Movement Performance
bio:
I started my career in medicine serving my community as a Paramedic Firefighter for 10 years. As my interest in medicine grew I attended the University of Washington School of Medicine Physician Assistant Program graduating with honors in 2004. I chose to work in multiple areas of medicine including hematology/oncology with stem cell transplantation. In 2008, I completed a critical care fellowship from Oregon Health Sciences University. I provided care as an internist and in the ICU as well as volunteering in the homeless veterans’ clinic, and traveling to Mexico for medical mission work, until a debilitating accident in 2010. 
After years of pain, multiple surgeries, and countless procedures to repair fractures, nerve and soft tissue damage I sought out regenerative medicine experts. I was fortunate to experience first-hand the incredible capability of ultrasound diagnostics and the effects of regenerative medicine with cellular therapy and PRP injections. 
After regaining my health, I focused my education to support the evolving practice of cellular therapy, and regenerative medicine. In 2015 I became the first Physician Assistant to complete the Emergency Medicine Fellowship in Ultrasound, at the University of California Irvine School of Medicine and continued to volunteer teaching medical students and residents the clinical capabilities of ultrasound diagnostics. Since 2014 I have traveled all over southern California working with doctors preforming injections and utilizing ultrasound. 
My less conventional path continued, and I obtained training in bio-identical hormone replacement methods. I am passionate about bringing a full sense of vitality to our patients and utilized regenerative medicine for chronic pain, neuropathy, joint conditions, sexual health, erectile dysfunction, urinary incontinence and anorgasmia. I find the combination of therapies to improve relationships and quality of life for many of my patients.
In November of 2017 West 2 North medical solutions opened its 4th location in San Marcos, California and I finally found my home and team to implement my dream of helping more people with cellular therapy and PRP.
I am passionate about treating the whole patient and acknowledge that life stress and hormone imbalances play a key role in the body’s inability to heal and can cause disease.  Our team is committed to assisting our patients,’ and community, in reaching their goals of healing, and continued health and longevity.

name: Olympus Movement Performance
bio:
Kimberly Marshall, is a certified family nurse practitioner with specialized experience and professional practice in pediatric emergency medicine, adult emergency medicine, urgent care and family practice. From a young age she has been passionate about fitness, healthy lifestyles and children. She has been able to bring the things she is passionate about into her professional practice. Her personal practice is focused on both conventional and complementary medicine. She is excited to be a part of the Olympus Movement Performance team. She feels OMP is the perfect integrative setting where disciplines work together to improve the overall health and fitness of each person seeking improvement. 
Kimberly is a native of Phoenix, Arizona. In her spare time she enjoys spending time with her family and her dog, traveling, hot yoga, hiking, running, cycling, SUP, swimming and basically anything outdoors!

name: Optima Medical Hormone Replacement
bio:
Joleen Lake has been a certified family nurse practitioner in Omaha, Nebraska since 2008. She began her nursing career in 1992 as a graduate of College of St. Mary. She completed her bachelor of science in nursing, graduating cum laude, in 1994 at College of St. Mary. Joleen has worked in a variety of nursing areas including oncology, women's health, medical aesthetics, and as a college instructor. While teaching at Clarkson College she also obtained her master of science in nursing degree in 2008. Joleen has a strong interest in bio-identical hormone replacement and has placed an emphasis on wellness and preventive medicine in her practice. She is a member of Sigma Theta Tau, Nebraska Nurse Practitioners, and the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.
www.OptimaMedical.us

name: Optima Women's Healthcare
bio:
Vandna Jerath, MD, FACOG, earned her Bachelor of Science degree from the University of Denver in 1990 and her Doctor of Medicine degree from The George Washington University School of Medicine in 1994. She completed her obstetrics and gynecology internship and residency at the University of Colorado Health Sciences Center and Hospital in 1998. She has been board certified in obstetrics and gynecology since 2001 and is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.
Dr. Jerath practiced obstetrics and gynecology for 11 years in Westminster, CO at Colorado Ob-Gyn Associates prior to relocating her practice to Parker, CO and opening Optima Women’s Healthcare, which is a relaxing, spa-like setting where she provides personalized, compassionate healthcare for women. She has currently been in practice for 16 years and been a physician for 20 years.  
Dr. Jerath strives to care for each patient individually and personalizes her attention and care to meet your needs. She treats each patient with respect, compassion, empathy and dedication while maintaining focus on the concerns and conditions that may require evaluation and treatment. She provides comprehensive ob/gyn care and has a particular interest in high risk obstetrics, minimally invasive and laparoscopic gynecologic surgery, and bio-identical hormone pellet therapy.
Dr. Jerath is passionate about women’s healthcare issues and actively promotes patient education and community outreach. Using healthcare social media to engage, educate, enlighten, and empower women, patients, colleagues, and the community, she has become a healthcare social media pioneer and expert locally. Dr Jerath is one of the first physicians in Colorado actively participating in and building an extensive healthcare social media network. She has done healthcare social media presentations and/or consulting for several hospitals, medical societies, practice management organizations, and healthcare colleagues. She was also featured on Denver 9News by Cheryl Preheim as the Social Media Doctor. 
Dr. Jerath enjoys playing tennis, hiking, attending the theater, concerts, political discussions, and other cultural events. She has previously completed several triathlons, half-marathons, and one marathon. She is also a Denver Broncos football fan and can often be found in the stands cheering. One of her greatest passions is to travel and she has had many memorable adventures and some of her favorite destinations include India, South Africa, Italy, Panama, Cambodia, and Costa Rica. She has lived in Colorado since 1981 and loves everything it has to offer.
Her patients describe her as compassionate, insightful, communicative, diligent, caring, highly-skilled, energetic and personable. Her favorite inspirational quote is by Maya Angelou, “My mission in life is not merely to survive, but to thrive; and to do so with some passion, some compassion, some humor, and some style.”  This is the manner in which she lives her life both personally and professionally.

name: Optimal Aging Institute
bio:
Dr. Brian Gerber M.D. is a Board-Certified Urologist and a diplomate with the American Board of Urology. He has been in practice in the northwest suburbs since 1998 and in Elgin since 2000. His practice is in general urology, specializing in BPH, prostate cancer, erectile dysfunction, bladder issues (UTI, cancer, over-active bladder), kidney stones, as well as hormone replacement.
Dr. Gerber received his medical degree from Northeastern Ohio Universities College of Medicine in 1992 and completed his two years of General Surgery and four years of Urology Residency at The University of Illinois at Chicago in 1998.
Several years ago, he noticed he was slowing down due to fatigue and lack of energy. He began to study and research aging with ways to slow it down and in some cases reverse it. After he saw the results in himself as a patient his passion in the field grew to help others optimize and slow their aging process.
Dr. Gerber was trained in Age Management Medicine at the Cenegenics Education and Research Foundation, and he is a member of the Age Management Medical Group (AMMG) and is the Medical Director and founder of Optimal Aging Institute. The Institutes goal is to have you look and feel younger while living longer by using evidence-based hormone optimization, nutrition, exercise, and supplements.

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio:
Dr. Williams earned his B.A. in Philosophy from Emory University in Atlanta. He then went on to graduate from The Ohio State University College of Medicine. He completed his internship in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Arizona Health Sciences Center. He then completed a residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center here in Oklahoma City.
Dr. Williams is an affiliate of Oklahoma Sports Science and Orthopedics, specializing in Gynecology. He is Board Certified by The American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. Dr. Williams is chief of staff of Northwest Surgical Hospital. His professional memberships include The American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology. He is a past President of the Oklahoma County Obstetrics and Gynecology Society.
He enjoys reading science fiction and exercising. His favorite activities involve family ski and snowboarding trips with his wife and their four boys, Noel, Calvin, Hugo and Gideon. Dr. Williams describes himself as intense and empathetic. He enjoys reflective thinking upon complex issues affecting his patients and laughing at himself. He is a non-conformist and often wonders why people focus on form over substance to their expense.

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio:
Abbey Ronck, PA_C, earned her master’s in Health Science as a Physician Assistant at University of Oklahoma Physician Associate Program.  Soon thereafter, she joined Optimal Health Associates as a Physician Assistant.  She is board certified by the NCCPA and scored in the 99th percent on the national certification exam (PANCE).  Before attending OUHSC, she received her bachelor’s degree in 2007 from Oklahoma State University in Nutritional Sciences where she graduated cum laude.  She is a member of the American Academy of Physician Assistants as well as the Oklahoma Academy of Physician Assistants.

“It is a privilege to work with women of all ages and to have the opportunity to provide care from adolescence to menopause,” she adds.  “I feel that our practice provides the important combination of intellect and empathy that is so vital to good medicine."

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio:
Christina (Tina) Telcocci, PA-C, graduated from the Physician Associate program at the University Of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center here in Oklahoma City. She earned her Master of Health Science degree with Special Distinction.
Prior to joining Optimal Health Associates in 2009, Tina worked ten years for a premier interventional pain management practice. Her empathy and understanding of patients’ needs is all too personal.
“In March of 2006, I was diagnosed with Stage IIB Hodgkin’s Lymphoma,” she recounts. “I was blessed to have access to wonderful medical care at every stage of my diagnosis and treatment. I cannot even imagine going through such a frightening and uncertain time without all the excellent physicians, nurses, and other medical staff I came into contact during that time.”
After six months of chemotherapy and two months of radiation treatment, Tina was cancer free. But she’d gained a lesson for her life’s work.
“My personal goal is to treat each of my patients with the same respect and compassion that I received and that they deserve. I want to provide each with guidance and understanding of their medical conditions.”
“Whether you are facing a life-threatening cancer, a life changing event such as menopause, a fertility issue, or you come in for a normal healthcare maintenance visit, I would like to help provide a calm, stable, and safe environment for you to discuss your concerns.”

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio:
Patricia Hall, PA-C, earned her master’s degree in Health Science as a Physician Assistant at the University of Oklahoma Physician Associate Program. She is board certified and scored in the 99th percentile on the national certification exam. Prior to beginning her graduate program, she earned her bachelor’s degree from the University of Oklahoma in Nutritional Science.
Prior to joining Optimal Health Associates in 2013, she worked as a Family Practice Physician Assistant in Akron, Ohio. “Because of my experience in the primary care setting,” she says, “I enjoy seeing our patients whose needs may fall beyond the realm of gynecology.”
“My goal is to work with patients to address their concerns and help them reach their emotional and physical goals all while providing the most comfortable environment possible,” she adds. “I feel very fortunate to be a part of such a caring, knowledgeable healthcare team that strives to provide each patient with the highest level of care and respect.”

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio: Benjamin J. Barenberg, M.D., FACOG, is a board certified Gynecologic Surgeon and fellowship trained Urogynecologist. Dr. Barenberg assists both male and female patients in need of advanced hormone replacement therapy including BHRT Pellet Therapy. Dr. Barenberg earned his medical degree from the University of Texas in Galveston and completed his residency training at Loyola University Medical Center in Chicago, IL. He furthered his education with fellowship training in Female Pelvic Medicine and Reconstructive Surgery at the University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center in Oklahoma City. During fellowship training, Dr. Barenberg received his Masters of Science degree in Clinical and Translational Research from the University of Oklahoma Graduate College. Dr. Barenberg is the founder of Genesis Wellness which is Oklahoma’s first and only concierge wellness service. Genesis Wellness takes pride in restoring patients’ hormonal and physical balance in the privacy and comfort of their home.

name: Optimal Health Associates
bio:
Dr. Sandler obtained a B.S. in Zoology from the University of Michigan. He completed his medical school education at the University of Texas Health Science Center in San Antonio. His residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology was performed at the University of California, San Diego.
Dr. Sandler developed the bulk of his clinical experience practicing at the Scripps Clinic Medical Group in La Jolla, CA. He is Board Certified by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a Fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.
In the past 15 years, Dr. Sandler, led Shared Wellness, LP. Shared Wellness helps physicians and other health care providers incorporate wellness and weight loss programs into their practices. His deep experience advocating health and wellness, including, as well as a desire to provide complete healthcare for women, including advanced hormone replacement therapy, within the specialty of Gynecology, led to his decision to join Optimal Health Associates.
Dr. Sandler and his wife, Susan, have three children, Tasha, Ben and Jeremy, and they can’t get enough of their granddaughter, Harper. While they enjoy theater, music and travel, their most rewarding activity is spending time together as a family on the slopes skiing and on the beach.

name: Optimal Hormone Health
bio: Born and raised in Salt Lake City Utah, Monica Olsen Bell knew early on that she wanted to dedicate herself to a rewarding career in medicine. In 1998 Monica graduated from Westminster College with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing.  Monica continued her education at the University of Utah,  graduating Magna Cum Laude, with a doctorate in Nursing Practice. As a board-certified Acute Care Nurse Practitioner she is committed to working with patients in a collaborative therapeutic relationship. Monica specializes in bio-identical hormone therapy individually tailored for men and women to achieve optimal health. Utilizing the most recent medical literature to responsibly guide treatment, Monica dedicates herself to patient safety first, which remains the cornerstone of her preventative clinical practice.

name: Optimal Hormone Health & Wellness
bio: Michelle is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner.  She obtained her Master of Science Degree in Nursing from the University of Texas Health Science Center-Houston, where she graduated with honors. She is a member of the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners, North Harris Montgomery Advanced Practice Nurse Society, and Sigma Theta Tau Nursing Honor Society. Michelle’s passion is health and wellness and she tries to live what she teaches. As an avid fitness enthusiast, she enjoys weight training, boxing classes with her husband, and any type of activity with her three children. She encourages patients to be pro-active with their health and focuses on health promotion and disease prevention through diet and exercise, making healthy, balanced lifestyle choices, and through the use of bio-identical hormones. Michelle believes in treating the whole patient and will always “dig a little deeper” to help patients get to the source of their symptoms. She also encourages the use of dietary supplements to help restore balance and support the body’s natural ability to heal itself.  Michelle is continually expanding her knowledge in the area of age management preventative medicine by attending specialty conferences, symposiums, and training seminars.

name: Optimized Wellness
bio:
Jordan Bernard is a family nurse practitioner board certified through the American Association of Nurse Practitioners. She graduated with a Masters of Science in Nursing from the University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences in 2015. 

Jordan currently works in regenerative and physical medicine and is excited to expand her professional expertise to hormone pellet therapy. She enjoys partnering with patients to improve their health and knowledge base. Jordan has previously worked in primary care implementing innovated projects relating to Transitional Care Management in Tyler, Texas prior to moving to Colorado.

Optimum Medical Weight Control and Family Wellness
bio: Kevin Morgan is a native of Port Arthur, Texas and has lived in Bridge City, Texas for the past 28 years.  He graduated from Lamar University with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing.  He worked in Critical Care with pediatric and adult patients for 5 years, the last three of which were also spent obtaining a Master’s degree in Nursing and specializing in Family Medicine.  He has spent the last ten years also specializing in Nutrition and Weight Loss and is highly sought after in this area of expertise.  When he is not helping his clients achieve their best, Kevin enjoys doing anything artistic which includes bodybuilding, playing guitar, singing, drawing, and gourmet cooking.

name: Optimum Medical Weight Control and Family Wellness
Optimum OB-GYN
bio:
Dr. Rebeca Velázquez, has a medical practice in Hato Rey, Puerto Rico. She specializes in Obstetrics and Gynecology and has over 10 years of experience in the field of medicine. Dr. Velázquez obtained her medical degree in 2004 in Universidad Central del Caribe. She completed her Ob-Gyn Residency program in 2008 at the San Juan City Hospital in Centro Medico. Is affiliated with the Ashford Prebisterian Hospital in Condado area and is an attending physician in Clinics for the Women in Fajardo, Cupey and Trujillo Alto area. She is a certified doula physician since 2015. Dr. Velazquez specializes in bio-identical hormone replacement, having attended conferences and obtained certification in bio-identical hormone replacement, pellet therapy. Dr. Rebecca Velazquez is accepting new patients at her co-founded medical office and practice location: Optimum OB/Gyn, 268 Hato Rey Center Bldg. suite 1000 Ave. Ponce de Leon, Hato Rey PR. (787) 266-7261 . She is available for appointments, preventive care, medical care as well as ongoing patient care.

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
With her background in Public Health, Dr. Norene Norris-Walsh is able to provide patient education in maternal - fetal care, preventive medicine, and stress reduction. She has served as assistant clinical professor at the University of California, Irvine Medical Center.
"With evolving complexities of a woman`s life, depending on which stage of life she is in, there exists a specific practice of medicine unique to each woman."
At Saddleback Memorial Medical Centers she has served on numerous committees including the Perinatal Committee, Emergency Department Committee, and Physician Wellness Committee.
Her undergraduate training was performed at University of San Diego. She then traveled to New Orleans where she simultaneously earned a Masters degree in Public Health with her medical degree at Tulane University. Dr. Norris-Walsh completed her residency training at UCLA-Harbor. She is a Diplomat of the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and a fellow of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology.
Dr. Norris-Walsh is happily married and has three wonderful children. There is never a dull moment at their home.
Languages:  French, Spanish

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
With more than 20 years of experience performing gynecological surgeries, Dr. Marc L. Winter has invested his energy in developing and offering less invasive procedures to his patients. Not only does Dr. Winter see referrals from outside Orange Coast Women`s Medical Group, but he also gives lectures, publishes papers and instructs other doctors on minimally invasive gynecological techniques.
Dr. Winter has been practicing in Laguna Hills since 1989. He specializes in robotic surgery and has experience performing complex hysterectomies, myomectomies and sacrocolpopexies with the use of the da vinci robotic surgical system. He has worked extensively with the use of graft materials to enhance pelvic reconstructive surgery (treating bladder, rectal, uterine, and vaginal prolapse).
Dr. Marc Winter has performed over 400 robotic surgeries at Saddleback Memorial Medical Center (SMMC) in Laguna Hills. Dr. Winter and SMMC have been designated one of only twenty-three epicenters, or national training sites in robotic gynecologic surgery for Intuitive Surgical, the maker of the da Vinci robot. At the SMMC training ground, Dr. Marc Winter teaches surgeons nationwide the latest in robotic surgical techniques. Patients can expect the most advanced care and excellent clinical outcomes.
Dr. Winter completed his residency training at the University of California at Irvine College of Medicine where he is currently an Assistant Clinical Professor.
Professional Affiliations:
Diplomat, American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology
Fellow, American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists
American Association of Gynecological Laparoscopists
Society of Laparoendoscopic Surgeons
Orange County OB/GYN Society

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio: Carolyn is certified in women’s health and has been a Nurse Practitioner at OCWMG since 1994.  She decided to specialize in women’s health when she was a Registered Nurse (RN) in Labor and Delivery and felt she could help women in good times and in difficult times.

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
Beverly has a Master’s degree in nursing and has been a Nurse Practitioner since 1983.  She has been with the practice since the beginning, working for OCWMG doctors May and Audell since 1990. She is proud to share that Dr. Audell and Dr. May delivered her children at Saddleback Memorial.

Beverly takes pleasure in treating, educating and interacting with patients. She enjoys working with outstanding doctors, nurses and staff. “If you don’t love your job, then why are you doing it?”

Her hobbies include socializing and going to lunch with good friends.

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
Dr. Raffo received a Bachelor of Science degree from Agnes Scott College (a small women`s college in Georgia). She received her medical degree from University of California, Irvine, where she also completed her residency training. Dr. Raffo has been in practice with Orange Coast Women`s Medical Group since 1997.

"The excitement and diversity of obstetrics and gynecology is what attracted me to this specialty. I find it very rewarding to help my patients with their individual medical needs. Part of my responsibility as a physician is to provide education and options to my patients. I believe each patient has the right to be the ultimate decision maker in her own care. This can only be achieved if she understands the necessary information and has a mutually trusting relationship with her doctor."

"The rewards of educating and caring for women of all ages are immense. It is a privilege to be part of that unforgettable moment in a woman’s life as she gives birth. The close relationships I have formed with many of my patients bring me great satisfaction. As we journey through life’s experiences together, it is gratifying to play a role in women’s healthcare. Being a mother and a wife helps me relate to many of the issues my patients face."

Dr. Raffo has a special interest in high-risk obstetrics and laparoscopy. Originally from Alabama, she has been a resident of Orange County since 1985. She lives locally with her husband and two sons.

"Entertaining friends and family brings me great enjoyment. I also enjoy traveling. Much of my free time is spent watching my boys play sports, particularly football and baseball. A new passion of mine is exercising. I finally started to practice what I preach and I am feeling the benefits of more energy what all of us need more of."

Professional Affiliations:
American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology
American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists
American Association of Gynecological Laparoscopists
Society of Laparoendoscopic Surgeons

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
Angelika Priestley, M.D. was born and raised in Southern California. She graduated from the University of California, Irvine with a Bachelor of Science Degree in Biology and Bachelor of Arts in Psychology. Dr. Priestley attended medical school at Ross University and completed her obstetrics and gynecology residency at Franklin Square Hospital in Baltimore, Maryland.

Dr. Priestley then joined a private practice in Tucson, Arizona where she specialized in minimally invasive procedures including robotic surgery.

"I find the most reward in serving patients through significant moments in their lives, such as the joys of first pregnancy to the changes of menopause and every challenge in between."

Dr. Priestley is married with two children. She enjoys traveling, cooking, yoga and spending time with her family at the beach.

Languages: German and Greek

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
Dr. Susan Mendelsohn has been in private practice in the Laguna Hills area since 1990. She says the excitement, warmth and feeling in her heart of being the first one to actually touch a new life and bring it safely into the world will never change.

"I chose obstetrics and gynecology because I could relate to women on a one-to-one basis, and I wanted to be able to go through life changes with them from childbearing through menopausal years."

She has a special interest in advanced laparoscopic surgery, including hysterectomy and myomectomy. At Saddleback Memorial Medical Center, Dr. Mendelsohn is a member of the Women`s and Children`s Case Review Committee and has served on Memorial Care`s Best Practice Team since its inception.

Dr. Mendelsohn graduated with honors from New York University School of Medicine. She completed postgraduate training at Mount Sinai Hospital in New York. A diplomat of the American Board of Obstetrics & Gynecology and a Fellow of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, Dr. Mendelsohn`s professional affiliations include American Medical Association, American Medical Women`s Association, and American Associates of Gynecological Laparascopy.

She is the proud mother of three children who keep her busy in her free time with school and sports activities.

Professional Affiliations:

Diplomate, American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology
Fellow, American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists
American Association of Gynecological Laparoscopists
Society of Laparoendoscopic Surgeons

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
Dr. O`Toole feels that the patient should play an active role in making decisions of her own medical care. She is especially noted for her interest in women`s health, including but not limited to infertility, osteoporosis, and menopause, as well as the challenge of obstetrics.
After earning her Bachelor of Science degree in Zoology at California State Polytechnic University, Pomona, she attended the University of Health Sciences, at Chicago Medical School. She received her medical degree in 1985, and then completed an internship in internal medicine at L.A. County USC Medical Center and her residency in Obstetrics & Gynecology at the Women`s Hospital at L.A. County USC Medical Center. Following the completion of her residency, Dr. O`Toole moved to Orange County and began her Obstetrics and Gynecology practice. Board certified in obstetrics and gynecology, Dr. O`Toole is a member of the North American Menopause Society.
Born in Greenville, Mississippi, Dr. O`Toole had the opportunity to live in different areas all over the United States, as well as the Orient while she was growing up. Dr. O`Toole is now married and has a son and a daughter. She enjoys many activities and sports, including running, swimming, and skiing. She is an avid reader and loves to bake. She looks forward to living in the Orange County area, caring for her patients, for many years.
Professional Affiliations:
Diplomate, American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology
Fellow, American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists
North American Menopause Society

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
As a board certified physician in obstetrics and gynecology, Dr. Elizabeth Johnsons interests include minimally invasive gynecologic surgery, management of abnormal Pap Smears/ Colposcopy, adolescent medicine, menopause management and general obstetrics. She works hard to involve her patients in a dynamic discussion about their health care needs and strives to provide comprehensive, evidence - based medicine, and surgical options to women throughout all phases of their lives. 
"I find listening to patients, and ensuring that they are active participants in their care, provide the most successful treatment path." 
Dr. Johnson completed her premedical education at the University of Colorado in 1995. After working in research at The Children`s Hospital of Philadelphia for two years, she attended the University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine where, in 2001, she earned her medical degree with an area of concentration in women`s health and the Luba Robin Goldsmith Award for excellence in obstetrics and gynecology. She went on to complete her OB/GYN residency at Northwestern University in 2005. There she was recognized for excellence in resident teaching, research and compassionate patient care. 
Dr. Johnson and her family have made San Clemente their home.  Dr. Johnson provides excellent patient care to the residents of her community and she enjoys contributing to the growth of the Talega office.
Professional Affiliations:
Diplomate, American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology
Fellow, American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists

name: Orange Coast Hormone Pellet Therapy
bio:
Enjoying all aspects of women's health, Teresa Whitman became board certified as an NP after completing the Women's Health Care Nurse Practitioner Program at Harbor/UCLA. Previously working in labor and delivery at Long Beach Memorial Hospital, Teresa then began working as an NP in women's health, practicing for the last seventeen years in Newport Beach. Finding ultrasound to be a significant asset, Teresa also earned certification in obstetric and gynecologic ultrasound.
Teresa's interests include adolescent health, pregnancy and recurrent pregnancy loss, routine gynecologic care including annual examinations and contraception, and menopause concerns including traditional and "bio-identical" hormone replacement therapy and maintenance of healthy bone density.
Living in Orange County with her husband Mike, Teresa enjoys family ski trips with their two children and gardening.

name: Orange Coast OBGYN
bio:
Caroline Conner, M.D.
Dr. Caroline Conner earned her medical degree at University of Texas at Houston, and completed her residency at University of California, Irvine. Dr. Conner is board certified in Obstetrics and Gynecology and is a member of the American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology and the American Medical Association.
She provides a full range of obstetrical and gynecological care and specializes in minimally invasive surgical techniques including robotic surgery and endometrial ablations. She has been practicing in the Orange County area for approximately ten years.
Her patients like her non-intimidating nature and feel comfortable discussing their personal needs in her office. She is a native Texan and likes spending time experiencing the outdoors. She also enjoys taking care of her young daughter Aspen.

name: Oregon Derma Center
bio: Dr. Jessica Black graduated from the National College of Naturopathic Medicine She has published The Anti-inflammation Diet and Recipe Book and co-authored Living with Crohn’s and Colitis; A comprehensive Naturopathic’s Guide to Health and Wellness with Dede Cummings.  Dr. Black specializes in women’s medicine including natural hormone balancing and childhood wellness.  Because of her thirst of knowledge she continues to study and research treatment ideas to improve people’s health and became a certified BioTE physician.  She takes pride in educating her patients about pellet therapy and why it’s so safe and effective.  Come see Dr. Black and start feeling your best today!

name: Oregon Derma Center
bio: Dr. Jason Black did his medical training at the National College of Naturopathic Medicine.  He specializes in treating many complex pain conditions and focuses on restoring the health of damage tissue resulting from injuries or inflammation.  Dr. Jason is skilled in multiple therapies to reduce pain including Prolotherapy and trained in effective injection therapy for fat reduction and aesthetic procedures.  Dr. Jason knows the importance of hormonal balance to pain patients, providing optimal health care and disease prevention.  He knows pellet therapy is the superior delivery method to feel your best.  Becoming a certified BioTE physician, Dr. Jason is not just adding years to your life, but adding life to your years.

name: Orthopedic & Physical Medicine Associates
bio:
David W. Duffner, MD, MBA David W. Duffner, MD, MBA, is an orthopedic surgeon specializing in spinal surgery with 28 years of experience. Dr. Duffner currently serves as medical director of the Spine Services Program and has been recognized as a Top Doctor in his specialty for the past six years in a row by Castle Connolly Medical Ltd., conductor of a peer-nominated survey as published in Palm Springs Life.
Prior to moving to the desert, Dr. Duffner served as president of a large orthopedic group in Tyler, Texas which he founded in 1990. Drawing on his successful practice and experience in Texas, he established the Spine Patient Assessment (SPA) program at ICON – a multidisciplinary approach in a peer-reviewed setting to provide treatment decision support and documentation for optimal patient care and risk management.
Operating on a philosophy that for most spine conditions surgery is the last resort, not the first, Dr. Duffner places a key emphasis on proper patient selection and optimizing the right treatment for a given patient. He has a phrase he likes to share with surgery patients: “The decision is more important than the incision.”
While Dr. Duffner enjoys the complexities and technical aspects of spine surgery, he is most concerned with how the patient feels – how has the surgery positively impacted their life. To this end, he has extensive experience in patient outcome studies and has been instrumental in improving outcome tracking at ICON – proudly reporting five years of data meeting or exceeding national database benchmarks.
Dr. Duffner earned his Medical Degree from the University of Oklahoma. He served his residency in orthopedics at Texas A&M. He also has received fellowship training in adult reconstructive orthopedics at the University of Basel in Switzerland. Additionally, he earned a Master of Business Administration degree from the University of Houston.
Dr. Duffner is a fellow of the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons (AAOS), a founding member of the North American Spine Society (NASS), and a member of the Riverside County Medical Association. He has published and lectured extensively on reconstructive orthopedics and spine surgery.
At Desert Regional Medical Center, Dr. Duffner currently serves as chief of orthopedics and chairman of the Bioethics Committee. Previously, he served as chair of the Department of Surgery for four years and was a member of Desert Regional Medical Center’s Governing Board for three years.
Dr. Duffner and his wife, Jana, live in Palm Springs. In his leisure time, he enjoys golf, hiking and other outdoor sports.

name: Orthopedic Specialists
bio:
Dr. Williams is originally from a small town in rural Maine. He attended Syracuse University for pre-med and then Medical School at the Kirksville College of Osteopathic Medicine in Kirksville, Missouri. After graduation, he did a whole year internship at Suncoast Hospital in Largo, then completed his Orthopedic residency in Queens, NY. After residency, Dr. Williams completed a one year fellowship in Hand and Microvascular Surgery at the University of Miami, Jackson Memorial Hospital in Miami, Florida.
Dr. Williams provides treatment options in all areas of general orthopedics and fracture problems. He provides many non-operative as well as operative treatment options for a vast number of accident related injuries. Dr. Williams has had additional training for the treatment of non-surgical neck and back related problems. 
Dr. Williams currently serves as the Chief of Surgery at Helen Ellis Memorial Hospital in Tarpon Springs, and the Chief of Orthopedics at Trinity Surgery Center in New Port Richey. In addition, he is a speaker for Ascension Orthopedics for surgeries to replace the MCP, PIP and CMC joints in the hand.
Dr. Williams, his wife Samantha, and their children live in Tarpon Springs with their pets. In his spare time, he enjoys working on automobiles, watching motor sports, ice hockey and football games.

name: Ovation Med Spa
bio:
Dr. Asra Oberoi has been in practice since 1996. She opened one of the first medical spas in the Houston area and is passionate about helping people look and feel their best, through the latest non-invasive cosmetic treatments and hormone optimization programs. Dr. Oberoi is fully trained and certified as a BioTE® specialist for bio-identical hormone replacement therapy, and is the Medical Director for Ovation Med Spa in Houston, TX, recently nominated as one of the Best Aesthetic Practice’s in the USA. In addition to BioTE® bio-identical hormone replacement therapy, Ovation Med Spa offers the latest advances in non-surgical Skin Rejuvenation and Body Contouring, Laser Hair Removal, as well as standards like Botox, and cosmetic fillers.  
 
Educational Background
 
•	Undergraduate – Texas Tech University, Lubbock, TX 1984-1987, B.S. Chemistry
•	Graduate – Texas Tech University, Lubbock, TX 1987-1989, M.S Cell and Molecular Biology
•	Medical School – Texas Tech University School of Medicine, Lubbock, TX 1989-1993, Medical Doctor
•	Internal Medicine Residency -Scott and White Memorial Hospital, Temple, TX, 1993-1996
•	Endocrinology Fellowship – The University of Texas Medical Branch, Galveston, TX 1996-1998
 
Organizations
 
•	Texas Medical Association
•	Indo-American Foundation
•	American Academy of Aesthetic Medicine
•	American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine

name: Oxford Obstetrics & Gynecology Associates
bio:
Julie Harper received her undergraduate degree from the University of Mississippi with a B.A. in psychology. She continued her education and received her medical degree from the University of Tennessee Health Science Center in Memphis. While in medical school, she was awarded Alumni Achievement Award in Clinical Medicine in 1999 for excellence in medical arts and sciences and dedication to the highest ethical and professional standards. Dr. Harper completed her residency in obstetrics and gynecology at the University of Alabama in Birmingham. She was elected Administrative Chief Resident in 2002-2003 and received the Charles E. Flowers Jr. Award for Excellence in Teaching in 2000-2001. Previously, Julie Harper was in private practice with Memphis Obstetrics and Gynecology Associates and served on the DeSoto Surgery Center Medical Advisory Board. Dr. Harper is a board certified Fellow of ACOG.
Hobbies: Dr. Harper's hobbies include keeping up with her two college kids and two younger kids, who are involved in travel swim, baseball, soccer and basketball. 
 
Family: Dr. Harper is married to James D. Harper, an attorney with Harper Whitwell. They have four children. 
 
Interesting Fact: She is a third-generation physician. Her mother and grandfather both graduated from UTHSH and practiced medicine together in Memphis.
 
Favorite thing about her job: She enjoys working with women through all aspects of their life, from the adolescent stage to menopausal years. She says, “I am privileged to get to partner with them in health and starting their families along this journey.”

name: P.L. Allen Health and Wellness Center
bio:
Dr. Patrick Allen, a native Texan, began a successful private practice in Fort Worth and North Richland Hills Texas in 1999. He is on staff at North Hills Hospital and Harris HEB Hospital. Dr. Allen is a graduate of the University of Texas Health Science Center at San Antonio; he completed his residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Oklahoma University of Health Science. He is a Diplomat in the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology and Board Certified and a fellow in the American College for Obstetrics and Gynecology. He is very dedicated to providing exceptional healthcare to women. He is very excited to have brought the DaVinci Robot to North Hills Hospital for less invasive gynecologic surgery.
Dr. Allen and his wife have three daughters and live In Keller Texas. They are very active in their parish church. He is a competitive Master swimmer and a guitar enthusiast.

name: P.L. Allen Health and Wellness Center
bio:
Marie T. Murphy, CNM was born and raised in Ireland. After receiving her RN license she moved to Scotland where she graduated in 1983 as a Midwife. Marie used her education to pursue her love of travel, first practicing Midwifery in Abu Dhabi, then in London, UK, Perth, Australia and in Saudi Arabia. For Marie working in such diverse areas of the world helped enrich her understanding and build a respect for the cultural traditions of women around the world.

Marie is a very unique person; her professional and personal life experiences have given her a wonderful ability to relate to women in every stage of their lives. She has worked in private practice since 1997. In 2000, she joined Dr. Patrick Allen in his OB/GYN practice located in North Richland Hills and Fort Worth.

Being a Certified Nurses Midwife, Marie provides all aspects of in office gynecological and prenatal care with special emphasis on patient education, health and wellness promotion and disease prevention.

name: P5 Performance
bio:
Dr. Ravi B Patel is a board certified physician in Internal Medicine. He also completed his specialization in Geriatric Medicine in New York City and moved back home to Dallas in 2005. He has been recognized in D Magazine as one of the Best Doctors in Dallas for three consecutive years. Dr. Patel has served on multiple hospital committees as well as Chief of Staff for an acute rehabilitation hospital for two years. He has also participated in a medical mission trip to Honduras to provide care to over 1,400 patients.
His journey as a physician, practicing in various hospitals from New York City to Texas, has exposed him to the challenges of the current care of the patient. Dr. Patel has seen that the ultimate care of the patient is by looking beyond traditional boundaries and providing a multidisciplinary approach. His inspiration comes from seeing the value of getting a head start in proper healthcare from a younger age by embracing a more preventative lifestyle.
Dr. Patel strives to be a role model to his patients, emphasizing good health along with proper nutrition and fitness. As such, he leads a very active life and loves playing baseball and soccer with his children. Dr. Patel has also found fun ways to incorporate fitness into his family’s daily routine and you will often find his children at the gym with him

name: Pacific Hair Institute
bio:
Dr. Elliott grew up in Omaha, Nebraska, the fourth generation in medicine. He attended Johns Hopkins University Undergraduate, University of Nebraska College of Medicine for medical school, and University of Iowa Hospitals, Department of Dermatology for Residency.
He was trained in hair transplantation in 1971, while a Dermatology Resident. Over the years, he invented many things which advanced the process of hair transplantation. He has always been at the forefront of the latest technology. You can rest assured that the techniques used at Pacific Hair have been and will continue to be the latest technology available.
Dr. Elliott is a Diplomate of the American Board of Hair Restoration Surgery. He began his interest in Endocrinology by reading the Merck Manual in his grandfather’s office (the Endocrinology section) when he was 9 years old. He has always been fascinated by the many effects that the endocrine system has in controlling the human body.
He was trained in bioidentical hormone replacement by Dr. Neal Rouzier in the 1990s. He has practiced bioidentical hormone replacement for his patients since. He has recently been additionally certified by Dr. Gary Donovitz’s BioTE company for the insertion of pellets containing either testosterone or Estradiol, which are an improved method of delivering constant blood levels of hormones (which exceed the ability of hormones delivered through the skin).
Dr. Elliott lives in Orange County and is the founder of Pacific Hair Institute and Pacific Longevity Institute.

name: Paradise Wellness
bio: Dr. Kristine Sarna is a board-certified Family Physician specializing in wellness and anti-aging services. She is an Arizona native, having completed her medical school education at the University of Arizona in Tucson and her Family Practice Residency at Good Samaritan Hospital in Phoenix. Dr. Sarna is also Board Certified in Integrative Holistic Medicine and holds certification in Medical Acupuncture from UCLA School of Medicine. Dr. Sarna enjoys treating patients of all ages. She believes in providing natural options for our patients to improve their health, including vitamin and nutraceutical therapies as well as acupuncture and lifestyle modifications. Dr. Sarna has specialized training in Bioidentical Hormone Replacement Therapy for men and women. Dr. Sarna is co-owner of Norterra Family Medicine and Paradise Medspa & Wellness, our sister office, providing cosmetic skin care and wellness services.

name: Paragon Infusion Centers
bio: Michelle Chien has had a passion for helping people with their medical needs. She earned her Master of Science degree in Nursing from Texas Woman’s University.  She is a board certified Family Nurse Practitioner. She believes in preventative health care and has a special interest in bio-identical hormone replacement therapy.  She currently works for Paragon Innovative Infusion Center, which is known to provide a high quality level of patient care. She takes her time to understand her patient’s concerns and explain the medical terms in understandable way. She enjoys traveling and spending time with her family.

name: Paramount Medical Consulting Inc.
bio:
Dr. Jorge R. Brothers specializes in urology, and has over 46 years of experience in the field of medicine. He was born and raised in Mexico City. He graduated from The National University of Mexico with his medical degree in 1970. He completed two years of residency in general surgery at the University of Louisville in Kentucky and then transferred to Tulane in New Orleans to complete four years of urology training. He is a member of the American Urological Association and Texas Medical Association. Dr. Brothers has been an active urologist in the Lubbock community over 30 years. He is affiliated with numerous hospitals in Lubbock. He continues to accept new urology patients. He offers the no scalpel vasectomy. His special interests include hormone replacement therapy and prostate cancer. His passion for years has been implanting penile prosthesis. 

Stacy Brothers was born in Lubbock, Texas. She graduated as a registered nurse with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing from Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center in 1995. Her nursing career began in urology  where she became board certified in urology at the registered nurse level. As her passion for urology evolved she decided to advance her education. Stacy graduated with a Master of Science in Nursing and from the Family Nurse Practitioner program from Texas Tech University Health Sciences Center. She is certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners.  She is the president of the West Texas chapter of Society of Urologic Nurses and Associates. Her passion for years has been helping couples with hormone replacement therapy. 

The Brothers are happily married with one daughter who cheers on varsity for the Lubbock Cooper Pirates, cheers on platinum at Raider Extreme, and dances on diamonds for Studio X. Jorge and Stacy enjoy spending time with family and friends, cooking, and travelling.
